Pan Shiji or Chew Shyh - Ji ( Chinese : 潘世姬 ; born 29 July 1957 ) is a Taiwanese composer , writer and music educator .

William Crean ( born 16 December 1951 ) is a Roman Catholic bishop in Ireland .
Moinina Fofana ( born 1950 in Bullom , Bonthe District , Sierra Leone ) is a Sierra Leonean former military commander who was the leading general in the Kamajors militia and director of the Civil Defence Forces ( CDF ) during the Sierra Leone Civil War .
Sandro Nocentini ( born 5 February 1966 ) is an Italian artist , living and working in Australia .
Zhou Hexi ( born 28 October 1992 ) is a Chinese professional Go player .
Boniface Natter ( 24 April 1866 ) , christened Anthony , was a German Benedictine Monk who became the first Abbot of the newly reformed Benedictine Abbey of Buckfast in Devon , England .

Albert Trim ( 6 October 1875 -- 11 July 1954 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Nanna Hänninen ( born in 1973 in Rovaniemi , Finland ) is a photographic artist who has worked as a professional since 1998 .

Saskia Wickham ( born 14 January 1967 ) is an English actress best known for playing Dr. Erica Matthews in the ITV television drama series Peak Practice between 1996 and 1998 .
Juan Oropeza Riera ( 24 April 1906 -- 29 November 1971 ) was a Venezuelan lawyer , diplomat , writer , educator and political scientist .
Andrew Steiner ( 22 August 1908 , Dunajská Streda -- April 2009 ) , also known as Endre Steiner and André Steiner ) was a Czechoslovak and American architect .

Lynda O'Connell ( born 1981 in Cork ) is a camogie player and an accountant , winner of All Ireland camogie medals in 2002 and 2005 and 2008 and 2009 .
Richard Gisser ( born 11 July 1939 in Vienna ) is an Austrian demographer who held leading positions at his country 's statistical office until his retirement .
Muhammad ibn Ali ibn Abi Talib , also known as Muhammad ibn al - Hanafiyyah ( 15 AH -- 81 AH ; c. 636 -- 700 A.D ) and surnamed Abu'l - Qasim was an early Muslim leader .
Charlotte Wankel ( 12 May 1888 -- 2 August 1969 ) was a Norwegian painter regarded as one of the first Norwegian cubist and painters of abstract art .
Fitton Gerard , 3rd Earl of Macclesfield ( 15 October 1663 -- 26 December 1702 ) was a British peer , styled Hon . Fitton Gerard until 1701 .
Sheila Waters ( born 1929 ) is a calligrapher and teacher .
Nathaniel Woodard ( 21 March 1811 -- 25 April 1891 ) was a priest in the Church of England .
Victor C. Anderson ( 1882 - -1937 ) was an American painter and illustrator , primarily known for his rural life scenes and landscapes , whose works were featured in Life and other magazines of the early 20th Century , and who produced a wide range of illustrations for books as well as oil paintings .
Marco Milesi ( born 30 January 1970 ) is a former Italian racing cyclist , who rode professionally between 1994 and 2006 .
Valdas Trakys ( born 20 March 1979 ) is a Lithuanian footballer , whose last club was FK Atlantas .
Qi Yu ( Chinese : 齐玉 ; born April 1961 ) is a Chinese politician serving since 2015 as the deputy head of the Organization Department of the Communist Party of China .
LaRuby May ( born 1975 ) is a Democratic politician and African American lawyer who represents Ward 8 on the Council of the District of Columbia in Washington , D.C. She won the Ward 8 special election on May 10 , 2015 , succeeding Marion Barry , who died in office on November 23 , 2014 .
Robert E. Pierre ( born 1968 in Franklin , Louisiana ) is a longtime reporter and editor at The Washington Post .

Gunther Hartmann ( born 7 December 1966 in Leutkirch ) is a German clinical pharmacologist and immunologist .

Shola Adewusi ( born 1963 ) is a British actress of stage , screen and radio .

Nathaniel Whittock ( born 26 January 1791 , died 1860 ) was a Victorian topographical engraver , who published bird's - eye views , e.g. of York ( 1856 ) , Oxford ( 1834 ) , Melbourne , Australia ( 1854 ) , Hull ( 1855 ) , and London ( 1845 , 1849 , 1859 ) .

Wyatt Outlaw ( 1820 -- February 26 , 1870 ) was the first African - American Town Commissioner and Constable of the Town of Graham , North Carolina .
Kathleen Ferguson ( born in Derry in 1958 ) is an Irish author known for The Maid 's Tale .

Jim Falk ( born 26 October 1946 ) is a physicist and academic researcher on science and technology studies .
Arlyne Brickman ( born 1934 ) is a former mafia informant and prostitute .
Helge Kringstad ( born 10 July 1943 ) is a Norwegian banker , civil servant and politician for the Labour Party .
Sir John Thomas Gilbert ( b. in Dublin , 23 January 1829 ; d. there , 23 May 1898 ) was an Irish archivist , antiquarian and historian .
Jonny Owen ( born Jonathan Tudor Owen on 4 July 1971 ) is a Welsh producer , actor and writer who has appeared TV shows including Shameless , Murphys Law and My Family .
Yusuf Ali Chowdhury ( 1905 - -1971 ) , commonly referred to as Mohan Mia , was a prominent Bengali Muslim politician in South Asia .
Sergey Chuykov ( born on 4 September 1980 ) is an Azerbaijani futsal player who plays for MFK Progress as a forward .
Edmond Novicki ( born 20 September 1912 , date of death unknown ) was a Polish - born French football player who played with RC Lens , US Valenciennes , SC Fives and Olympique Lillois , as well as the French national team .

Alessandro Specchi ( 1668 -- November 16 , 1729 ) was an Italian architect and engraver .
Augustine Podmore Williams ( 22 May 1852 - 17 April 1916 ) was an English mariner who gained notoriety in the 1880s as the result of a scandal on the high seas .
Mahmoud Taha ( Arabic : محمود طه‎ ) ( born 1942 ) is a Jordanian artist , potter and ceramicist who is credited for improving the writing and calligraphy skills of many students in Jordanian schools .
Lijah Perkins ( born 22 January 1977 ) in Birmingham , United Kingdom is a professional basketball player , currently signed to Worthing Thunder , playing as a Power forward or Centre .
Joseph Park ( born c. 1969 ) is a Korean American investment banker that founded Kozmo.com in 1997 .
Heinz Lorenz ( 7 August 1913 -- 23 November 1985 ) was German dictator Adolf Hitler 's Deputy Chief Press Secretary during World War II .
Ernst Fasan ( born 1926 ) is an Austrian lawyer and a recognized authority in space law , including Metalaw .
Michael Januario ( born in 1984 ) better known by his stage name M - Dot is an Italian - American rapper .
Amy Mathews ( born 29 March 1979 ) is an Australian television , film and theatre actress .
Raja Dina Nath Madan ( Razdan ) ( 1795 - 1857 ) aka Diwan Dina Nath or Dina Nath , who was a Kashmiri , rose to the position of the Privy Seal and finance minister ( Diwan ) in the Punjab empire of Maharaja Ranjit Singh .
Nicholas Guy ( fl . 1612 -- 1631 ) was one of the first settlers at the London and Bristol Company 's Cuper 's Cove , colony in Newfoundland , and was the father of the first English child born in Newfoundland and subsequently all of the country of Canada .
Barbara Tate ( 2 June 1927 - -12 November 2009 ) was a British artist and writer , perhaps best known for her bestselling book West End Girls , which was published shortly after her death .
Suzy Spafford , also known as Suzy Spafford Lidstrom ( born 1945 ) , is an American cartoonist best known for drawing whimsical animal characters .
Rocco Palmo ( born 1983 ) is a Roman Catholic commentator and writer living in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania .
Jackie Brookner ( 1945 -- May 15 , 2015 ) was an ecological artist , writer , and educator .
Luca Curatoli ( born 25 July 1994 ) is an Italian sabre fencer , team world champion in 2015 and team silver medallist at the 2015 European Championships .
Patrick Kariuki Muiruri ( born 5 December 1945 ) served in the Kenyan parliament for 10 years ( 1997 - -2007 ) representing Gatundu North Constituency .

Ajit Bhattacharjea ( 1924 -- 4 April 2011 ) was veteran Indian journalist , newspaper editor and campaigner for democratic rights , and the Right to Information Act .

Rosalind Halstead ( born 18 July 1984 in Islington , London ) is an English actress , model , and dancer .

Edward King Fordham ( 1750 - -1847 ) was an English banker and political reformer .

Michio Ihara ( born 1928 , Paris ) is a Japanese kinetic sculptor , educated in Japan who was influenced by the work of George Rickey .

Donald Bruce Dawe AO ( born 15 February 1930 ) is an Australian poet , considered by some as one of the most influential Australian poets of all time .
Jeff Hayenga ( also known as Jeffrey Hayenga ) is an American actor , born in 1950 in Sibley , Iowa .
Conny Van Dyke ( sometimes credited as as Connie Van Dyke ) is a singer and actress , born September 28 , 1945 in Nassawadox , Virginia to Benjamin and Charlotte Elizabeth Van Dyke .
Mar - Zutra II was a Jewish Exilarch who led a successful revolt against Persia in the year 495 CE and achieved seven years of political independence in Mahoza .
Marian Moszoro Մարիան Մոշորո ( born in 1974 in Rosario , Argentina ) , Polish economist , in 2005 - 2006 he was Undersecretary of State , Deputy Minister of Finance of Poland , the youngest ever in the history of the Ministry .
John Stuart , 12th Earl of Moray ( 25 January 1797 -- 8 November 1867 ) , styled The Honourable John Stuart between 1810 and 1859 , was a Scottish soldier and politician .
Lewanika ( 1842 - -1916 ) ( also known as Lubosi Lewanika or Lewanika I ) was the Lozi Litunga ( king or paramount chief ) of Barotseland from 1878 to 1916 ( with a break in 1884 - 5 ) .
Belinda Bromilow ( born 21 May 1975 ) is an Australian actress who is best known for her roles in the television series Spirited , Packed to the Rafters and Talk to Me .

David Gamper is an American composer ( born in Findlay , Ohio , in 1945 , died September 27 , 2011 ) He has been a member of Pauline Oliveros 's Deep Listening Band and the duo See Hear Now .
Henry Hacking ( 1750 - -1831 ) , seaman and explorer , was an early settler in New South Wales , Australia .
Anosh Irani ( born 1974 ) is an Indian - Canadian novelist and playwright .
Karl - Martin Rammo ( born 6 June 1989 ) is an Estonian sailor , born in Tallinn .
Karol Szwedowski ( 1889 - 1941 ) entitled to Korwin coat of arms was a Polish builder , contracted to work at Westerplatte .
Priyanka Bhanushali ( born 7 January 1993 ) is an Indian singer and songwriter , who performs under the stage name Priyanka Pripri .
Manuel Gutiérrez ( born 8 April 1920 ) was a Mexican football leaguedefender .
Hedi Turki ( born 15 May 1922 ) is a Tunisian artist of Turkish origin .
Michael Findlay ( 1938 - -1977 ) , along with his wife Roberta Findlay , directed and produced numerous sexploitation movies .
Jane Ridley ( born 15 May 1953 ) is an English historian , biographer , author and broadcaster , and Professor of Modern History at the University of Buckingham .
Louis - Ovide Brunet ( 10 March 1826 -- 2 October 1876 ) was a French - Canadian botanist and Roman Catholic priest , and is considered one of the founding fathers of Canadian botany .
Kim Conley ( born 14 March 1986 in Slough , United Kingdom ) is an American track and field athlete , who competes in middle and long distance track events .

Andrew Golota ( born Andrzej Gołota ; 5 January 1968 ) is a Polish former professional boxer .

Pete Vuckovic ( born 1971 , Devon , England ) is a British singer - songwriter of Serbian descent .

Kevin Shea ( born 1973 in the Twin Cities metropolitan area , Minnesota ) is a jazz drummer .
Yu Linxiang ( Chinese : 喻林祥 ; pinyin : Yù Línxiáng ; born January 1945 ) is a retired general ( shang jiang ) who served as political commissar of the People 's Armed Police of China .

Samuel Phelps ( born 13 February 1804 , Plymouth Dock ( now Devonport ) , Plymouth , Devon , died 6 November 1878 , Anson 's Farm , Coopersale , near Epping , Essex ) was an English actor and theatre manager .
Pierre Albarran ( 18 May 1893 -- 24 February 1960 ) was a French auction and contract bridge player and theorist , and a tennis player .
István Fekete ( January 25 , 1900 -- June 23 , 1970 ) was a Hungarian writer , author of several youth novels and animal stories .
Adriana Bisi Fabbri ( 1881 - -1918 ) was an Italian painter .
John Cleland ( baptised 24 September 1709 -- 23 January 1789 ) was an English novelist best known as the author of Fanny Hill : or , the Memoirs of a Woman of Pleasure .
Albert Langen ( 8 July 1869 -- 30 April 1909 ) was a German publisher and founder of the satirical publication Simplicissimus .
Sebastian Sailer ( 12 February 1714 in Weißenhorn -- 7 March 1777 in Obermarchtal ) , born Johann Valentin Sailer , was a German Premonstratensian Baroque preacher and writer .
Heinz Neumann ( 6 July 1902 -- 26 November 1937 ) was a German politician from the Communist Party ( KPD ) and a journalist .
Luciano Benetton ( born 1935 ) is an Italian billionaire businessman , one of the co - founders of Benetton Group , the Italian fashion brand .
Mireille Guiliano ( born April 14 , 1946 , in Moyeuvre - Grande , France ) is a French - American author .
Cláudio Manuel da Costa was born in the city of Vargem do Itacolomi ( nowadays Mariana ) , to Portuguese João Gonçalves da Costa and Brazilian Teresa Ribeiro de Alvarenga .
Alija Izetbegović ( Bosnian pronunciation : ( ǎlija ǐzedbegoʋit͡ɕ ) ; 8 August 1925 -- 19 October 2003 ) was a Bosnian politician , activist , lawyer , author , and philosopher who in 1990 became the first Chairman of the Presidency of Bosnia and Herzegovina .
Jean - Charles Marchiani , ( born August 6 , 1943 ) is a French prefect and politician .
George Pitt , 1st Baron Rivers ( 1 May 1721 -- 7 May 1803 ) was an English diplomat and politician .
Temistocle Solera ( 25 December 1815 -- 21 April 1878 ) was an Italian opera composer and librettist .
Marc - Adolphe Guégan ( 1891 - -1959 ) was a French journalist and poet who was an early exponent of Japanese haiku in the French language .
Eva Badura - Skoda ( née Halfar ) is a German / Austrian musicologist .
Baldur Ragnarsson ( born 25 August 1930 ) is an Icelandic poet and author of Esperanto works .
Nora Zaïdi ( Nora Mebrak - Zaïdi ) , born on July 6 , 1965 in Bethoncourt ( French département of Doubs ) , daughter of an Algerian textile toiler , is a French activist who seated in the European Parliament from 1989 to 1994 .
Patrick Gaubert ( born 6 July 1948 in Paris ) is a French politician and was a Member of the European Parliament for the Île - de - France through 2009 .
Richmal Crompton Lamburn ( 15 November 1890 -- 11 January 1969 ) was initially trained as a schoolmistress but later became a popular English writer , best known for her Just William series of books , humorous short stories , and to a lesser extent adult fiction books .
Rudolf von Scheliha ( May 31 , 1897 - December 22 , 1942 ) was a German diplomat executed by the Nazis during World War II . Scheliha was born in Zessel , Oels , Silesia ( now Cieśle , Gmina Oleśnica , Poland ) , as the son of a Prussian squire .
Sir Henry Harpur , 6th Baronet ( 1739 -- 10 February 1789 ) was an English Tory politician who represented the constituency of Derbyshire .
Saleema is an Indian actress acts prominently in Malayalam .
Cesáreo Fernández Duro ( Zamora , 25 February 1830 - Zamora , 5 June 1908 ) was a Spanish naval captain , writer , scholar and historian .
Jean - Guillaume , baron Hyde de Neuville ( 24 January 1776 -- 28 May 1857 ) was a French aristocrat , diplomat , and politician .
Professor Jacques Cauvin ( 1930 -- 26 December 2001 ) was a French archaeologist who specialised in the prehistory of the Levant and Near East .
Jean - Marie Messier ( born 13 December 1956 ) is a French businessman who was Chairman and Chief Executive of the multinational media conglomerate Vivendi ( formerly Vivendi Universal ) until 2002 .
António Ferreira Gonçalves dos Reis , known as António Reis ( 1927 - -1991 ) , was a Portuguese film director , screenwriter and producer , poet , sculptor and ethnographer .
Peter Landau ( born 26 February 1935 in Berlin ) is a German jurist , legal historian and expert on canon law .
Bartolomeo Pacca ( 27 December 1756 , Benevento -- 19 February 1844 ) was an Italian Cardinal , scholar and statesman as Cardinal Secretary of State .
George Duncan Painter OBE ( 5 June 1914 -- 8 December 2005 ) , known as George D. Painter , was an English author most famous as a biographer of Marcel Proust .
Philippe Poirrier , born in 1963 , is a French historian , specialist in French contemporary cultural history .
Erich Böhme ( February 8 , 1930 -- November 27 , 2009 ) was a German journalist and television host .
Waldemar von Wasielewski ( 10 December 1875 -- 28 February 1959 ) was a German writer who specialized in the occult , Goethe research , and the history of music .
Herman Branover ( Hebrew : ירמיהו ברנובר‎ ; born 1931 ) is a Russian Israeli physicist and Jewish educator .
Richard Knolles ( c. 1545 -- July 1610 ) was an English historian , famous for his account of the Ottoman Empire , the first major description in the English language .
Joseph Agricol Viala ( 22 September 1780 , Avignon -- 6 July 1793 , Caumont - sur - Durance ) was a child hero in the French Revolutionary Army .
Antonio Gamoneda ( born May 30 , 1931 ) is a Spanish poet , winner of the Cervantes Prize in 2006 .
Joaquín Fernández Prida ( 1865 in Oviedo , Spain - 1942 in Madrid , Spain ) was a Spanish lawyer and politician who served as Minister of State in 1922 , during the reign of King Alfonso XIII of Spain .
Arthème Camille Matignon ( 3 January 1867 -- 18 March 1934 ) was a French chemist noted for his work in thermochemistry .
Paul Sérieux ( French : ( se.ʁjø ) ; 1864 - -1947 ) was a French psychiatrist who was a native of Paris .
Erlend Loe ( born 24 May 1969 in Trondheim ) is a Norwegian novelist , screenwriter and film critic .
HA Schult , born Hans - Jürgen Schult on June 24 , 1939 in Parchim , Mecklenburg is a German installation , happening and conceptual artist known primarily for his object and performance art and more specifically his work with garbage .
Lucian Scherman ( born October 10 , 1864 in Posen , died May 29 , 1946 in Hanson , Massachusetts ) was a German Indologist , curator of the Ethnology Museum in Munich , and also a professor at the University there .
Pietro Garinei ( 1 February 1919 -- 9 May 2006 ) was an Italian playwright , actor , and songwriter .
Francesco Benozzo ( born 22 February 1969 ) is an Italian poet , musician and philologist .
Christoph Köler or ( in Latin ) , Christophorus Colerus ( 1602 - 1658 ) was a German poet and writer .
Albert François Cevert Goldenberg ( 25 February 1944 -- 6 October 1973 ) was a French racing driver who took part in the Formula One World Championship .
Norman Pace ( born 17 February 1953 in Dudley , Worcestershire ) is an English actor and comedian , best known as one half of the comedy duo Hale and Pace with his friend and comic partner Gareth Hale .
Antón Arieta - Araunabeña Piedra ( born 6 January 1946 ) , known as Arieta , is a Spanish retired footballer who played as a striker .
Edward John Payne ( 22 July 1844 -- 26 December 1904 ) was an English barrister and historian specializing in colonial history .
Herbert Vorgrimler ( 4 January 1929 -- 12 September 2014 ) was a Catholic theologian and author who has written 33 books published in English , most of them translated from his over 90 books in German .
Helmut Andreas Paul Grieshaber or HAP Grieshaber ( 15 February 1909 - 12 May 1981 ) was a German artist .
Henry Ingram , 7th Viscount of Irvine ( 30 April 1691 -- 4 April 1761 ) , styled The Honourable Henry Ingram until 1736 , was an English landowner and politician .
Giacomo Devoto ( 19 July 1897 -- 25 December 1974 ) was an Italian historical linguist and one of the greatest exponents of the twentieth century of the discipline .
Lajos Bíró ( born Lajos Blau ) ( 22 August 1880 -- 9 September 1948 ) was a Austro - Hungarian novelist , playwright , and screenwriter who wrote many films from the early 1920s through the late 1940s .
Jacques Anne Joseph Le Prestre de Vauban ( 10 March 1754 , in Dijon -- 20 April 1816 ) was a French general of the Ancien Régime and the French Revolutionary Wars .
Barbara Petzold ( born August 8 , 1955 ) is a former East German Cross - country skier who competed during the 1970s and early 1980s .
Gerhard Kofler ( February 11 , 1949 in Bolzano - November 2 , 2005 in Vienna ) was an Austrian - Italian writer .
José Antonio Ortega Lara ( Montuenga , parish of Madrigalejo del Monte , Burgos , 1958 ) is a former Spanish prison officer who was kidnapped by the separatist organization ETA for 532 days between 1996 and 1997 .
Édgar Alexánder Campos Mora ( born September 17 , 1977 ) , better known as Alex Campos , is a Colombian Christian singer that is popular in Latin America and in Spanish speaking countries .
Ernest Grandidier ( 1833 --1912 ) was a French industrialist , naturalist and art collector .
Sir Nicholas Grimshaw , CBE , PPRA ( born 9 October 1939 ) is a prominent English architect , particularly noted for several modernist buildings , including London 's Waterloo International railway station and the Eden Project in Cornwall .
Taku Mayumura ( Mayumura Taku , 20 October 1934 - ) is a Japanese science fiction writer who won the Seiun Award for Novel twice .
Sir Charles Morgan , 1st Baronet ( 25 April 1726 -- 7 December 1806 ) was an English Judge Advocate - General .
John Gauden ( 1605 -- 23 May 1662 ) was an English Bishop of Exeter then Bishop of Worcester and writer , and the reputed author of the important Royalist work Eikon Basilike .
Rocío Delgado ( born July 21 , 1977 in Huesca ) is a Spanish freestyle skier , specializing in ski cross .
Kaka Radhakrishnan ( c. 1925 -- 14 June 2012 ) was an Indian film actor who acted in Tamil language films from the 1940s onwards .
Cherubino Alberti ( 1553 - -1615 ) , also called Borghegiano , was an Italian engraver and painter .
Manuel Sanchis i Guarner ( Valencia , 1911 - 1981 ) was a Spanish philologist , historian and writer .
Antonio Miguel Parra ( born December 26 , 1982 in Palafrugell , Girona ) is a retired Spanish professional track cyclist .
Kamahl Santamaria is a foundation news anchor and journalist at Al Jazeera English , based in Doha .
Élisée Maclet ( 1881 - -1962 ) was a French impressionist painter .
Wilfride Piollet ( 28 April 1943 -- 20 January 2015 ) was a French prima ballerina and choreographer .
Oskar Pastior ( 20 October 1927 -- 4 October 2006 ) was a Romanian - born German poet and translator .
Johannes Vares ( 12 January 1890 ( O.S. 31 December 1889 ) -- 29 November 1946 ) , commonly known as Johannes Vares Barbarus , was an Estonian poet , doctor , and politician .
Iorwerth Eiddon Stephen Edwards CBE , FBA ( 21 July 1909 -- 24 September 1996 ) -- known as I. E. S. Edwards-- was an English Egyptologist considered to be a leading expert on the pyramids .
Oliviero Toscani ( born 28 February 1942 ) is an Italian photographer , best - known worldwide for designing controversial advertising campaigns for Italian brand Benetton , from 1982 to 2000 .
Wilhelm Gottlieb Tennemann ( 7 December 1761 -- 30 September 1819 ) was a German historian of philosophy .
Acislo Antonio Palomino de Castro y Velasco ( 1653 -- 13 April 1726 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque period , and a writer on art , author of El Museo pictórico y escala óptica , which contains a large amount of important biographical material on Spanish artists .
John Verney , 1st Viscount Fermanagh ( 5 November 1640 -- 23 June 1717 ) , known as Sir John Verney , 2nd Baronet between 1696 and 1703 , was an English peer , merchant and Tory politician .
Constantin Christian Dedekind ( 2 April 1628 -- 1715 ) was a German poet , dramatist , librettist , composer and bass singer of the Baroque era .
Sandro Chia ( born 20 April 1946 ) is an Italian painter and sculptor .
Dares Phrygius ( Ancient Greek : Δάρης , Dárēs ; Middle Welsh : Dared ) , according to Homer , was a Trojan priest of Hephaestus .
Charles Thurstan Shaw CBE FBA FSA ( 27 June 1914 - 8 March 2013 ) was an English archaeologist , the first trained specialist to work in what was then British West Africa .
Antonio Trashorras , born 22 September 1969 , is a Spanish screenwriter .
Nguyễn Nhật Ánh ( born on May 7 , 1955 ) is a Vietnamese author who writes for teenagers and adults .
Phạm Xuân Ẩn ( September 12 , 1927 -- September 20 , 2006 ) was a Vietnamese journalist and correspondent for Time ( magazine ) , Reuters and the New York Herald Tribune , stationed in Saigon during the war in Vietnam .
Lewis Fry Richardson , FRS ( 11 October 1881 -- 30 September 1953 ) was an English mathematician , physicist , meteorologist , psychologist and pacifist who pioneered modern mathematical techniques of weather forecasting , and the application of similar techniques to studying the causes of wars and how to prevent them .
Manfred Osten ( born January 19 , 1938 ) is a German poet and cultural historian .
Manohar Singh ( 1938 -- 14 November 2002 ) was a distinguished Indian theatre actor - director and a character actor in Hindi films .
Reverend Henry Melvill Gwatkin ( 30 July 1844 -- 14 November 1916 ) was an English theologian and church historian .
William Thomas Stead ( 5 July 1849 -- 15 April 1912 ) was an English newspaper editor who , as a pioneer of investigative journalism , became a controversial figure of the Victorian era .
Tommy Robredo Garcés ( Spanish pronunciation : ( ˈtomi roˈβɾeðo ɣarˈθes ) , Catalan : ( ɣərˈses ) ; born 1 May 1982 ) is a Spanish professional tennis player .
Josefina de la Torre Millares ( 1907 - -2002 ) was a Spanish poet , novelist , and opera singer , as well as a stage , film , radio , and television actress .
Fernando Cagigal de la Vega y Martínez Niño de San Miguel y Pacheco , 4th Marquess of Casa Cagigal ( 1756 - -1824 ) was a Spanish soldier , poet , and playwright .
Giuseppe Terragni ( Italian : ( dʒuˈzɛppe terˈraɲɲi ) ; 18 April 1904 -- 19 July 1943 ) was an Italian architect who worked primarily under the fascist regime of Benito Mussolini and pioneered the Italian modern movement under the rubric of Rationalism .
Matilde Serao ( Italian pronunciation : ( maˈtilde seˈraːo ) ; March 7 , 1856 -- 25 July 1927 ) was a Greek - born Italian journalist and novelist .
Ana de Jesús , O.C.D. , translated into English as Ann of Jesus , also known as Ann Lobera ( 25 November 1545 -- 4 March 1621 ) , was a Spanish Discalced Carmelite nun and writer .
Jean - Baptiste Gail ( 1755 - -1829 ) was a French Hellenist scholar , member of the Institut de France ( French Institute ) .
Leonardo de Benedetti ( born September 15 , 1898 in Turin , Italy ; died October 16 , 1983 ) was an Italian Jew and physician who was interned in the Auschwitz concentration camp from February 1944 until its liberation in January 1945 .
Francis Robartes FRS ( c. 1649 -- 3 February 1718 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1673 and 1718 .
John Gifford ( 1758 -- 6 March 1818 ) was an English political writer .
Juliusz Słowacki ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈjuljuʂ swɔˈvat͡ski ) ; 4 September 1809 -- 3 April 1849 ) was a Polish Romantic poet .
Zofia Helman ( born 8 March 1937 ) is a Polish musicologist and an honorary member of the Polish Composers ' Union .
José Bódalo Zúffoli ( March 24 , 1916 -- July 24 , 1985 ) was an Argentine born Spanish film actor .
William Henry Jones ( 1817 - -1885 ) , William Henry Rich Jones from 1883 , was an English Anglican priest and antiquarian .
Bertalan Szemere ( 1812 - -1869 ) was a Hungarian poet and nationalist who became the third Prime Minister of Hungary during the short period of the Hungarian Revolution of 1848 when Hungary was independent of rule by the Austrian Empire .
Arun Bali ( Punjabi : ਅਰੁਣ ਬਾਲੀ , Hindi : अरुन बाली ) is an Indian actor who has worked in numerous films and television series .
Kurt Stöpel ( 12 March 1908 -- 11 June 1997 ) was a German professional road bicycle racer .
Saeed Hajjarian ( Persian : سعید حجاریان‎‎ , born 1954 ) is an Iranian reformist political strategist , journalist , pro - democracy activist and former intelligence officer .
Ephraim Chambers ( c.1680 -- 15 May 1740 ) was an English writer and encyclopaedist , who is primarily known for producing the Cyclopaedia , or a Universal Dictionary of Arts and Sciences .
Walid Khalidi ( Arabic : وليد خالدي‎ , born 1925 in Jerusalem ) is an Oxford University - educated Palestinian historian who has written extensively on the Palestinian exodus .
Lorenzo de Rodas ( 1930 -- December 18 , 2011 ) , was a Spanish actor and film director .
Christian Baudelot ( born 9 December 1938 , Paris ) is a French sociologist based at the École normale supérieure .
Dhirubhai Thaker ( 27 June 1918 -- 22 January 2014 ) was an Indian Gujarati writer , who was best known for creating the Gujarati Vishwakosh , a 25-volume encyclopedia of the Gujarati language .
Louis Companyo ( born in Céret in 1781 and died in Perpignan in 1871 ) was a French physician and naturalist .
Edme - Sébastien Jeaurat ( 14 September 1725 -- 7 March 1803 ) was a French astronomer most notable for publishing a map of the 64 stars of the Pleiades in 1786 .
Elio Modigliani ( 13 June 1860 -- 6 August 1932 ) was an Italian anthropologist , zoologist , explorer , and plant collector .
Jean Boutière ( 1 November 1898 -- 29 January 1967 ) was a French philologist , specialist in Romance philology .
Christian Reuter ( born 1665 in Kütten ; died 1712 or later ) was a German author .
Johan Otto von Spreckelsen ( May 4 , 1929 - -March 16 , 1987 ) was a Danish architect , best known for designing the Grande Arche of La Défense in Paris .
Antonio Afonso Moreno ( 25 August 1943 -- 9 June 1975 ) , known as Tonono , was a Spanish footballer who played as a sweeper .
Basile Boli ( born January 2 , 1967 ) is a French former footballer and current television sports presenter .
Irja Agnes Browallius ( 1901 - -1968 ) was a Swedish teacher , novelist and short story writer .
Teodor Jeske - Choiński ( 27 February 1854 - 14 April 1920 ) was a Polish intellectual , writer and historian , literature critic .
Richard Ligon ( 1585?--1662 ) , a British author , lost his fortune as a royalist during the English Civil War ( 1642 - 1651 ) , and during this turbulent time in England he found himself , as he notes in his narrative , a `` stranger in my own country . ''
Xiong Zhaozheng ( Chinese : 熊召政 ; pinyin : Xióng Zhāozhèng ; born December 1953 ) is a Chinese novelist .
Andy Byatt is an English wildlife documentary film producer for the BBC Natural History Unit ( NHU ) in Bristol .
Guglielmo Ferrero ( Italian pronunciation : ( ɡuʎˈʎelmo ferˈreːro ) ; July 21 , 1871 -- August 3 , 1942 ) was an Italian historian , journalist and novelist , author of the Greatness and Decline of Rome ( 5 volumes , published after English translation 1907 - -1909 ) .
James Duffield Harding ( 1798 -- 4 December 1863 ) , was an English landscape painter , lithographer and author of drawing manuals .
Halide Edib Adıvar ( Ottoman Turkish : خالده اديب‎ ( haliˈde eˈdib ) ; sometimes spelled Halidé Edib in English ) ( 1884 -- 9 January 1964 ) was a Turkish novelist , nationalist , and political leader for women 's rights .
Jean Le Pelletier ( December 29 , 1633 - August 31 , 1711 ) was a French polygraph and alchemist .
Juraj Červenák ( born June 16 , 1974 ) is a Slovak author best known for his short stories and novels , which mix elements of sword and sorcery with historical fantasy and Slavic mythology .
Andreas Gursky ( born January 15 , 1955 ) is a German photographer and Professor at the Kunstakademie Düsseldorf , Germany .
Manlio Simonetti ( Rome 2 May 1926 ) is a major Italian expert and scholar in Patristics and the history of Biblical interpretation .
Yona Friedman ( born 5 June 1923 , Budapest ) is a Hungarian - born French architect , urban planner and designer .
François Coli ( June 5 , 1881 - presumably on or after May 8 , 1927 ) was a French pilot and navigator best known as the one - eyed flying partner of Charles Nungesser in their doomed attempt to fly the Atlantic Ocean on the aircraft known as The White Bird .
Claude Liauzu ( April 24 , 1940 in Casablanca , Morocco -- May 23 , 2007 ) , was a French historian specializing in the history of colonialism .
Claude Guéant ( born 17 January 1945 ) is a French civil servant .
Antoni Czubiński ( 22 November 1928 in Konin , Poland -- 10 February 2003 in Poznań , Poland ) was a Polish historian and director of the Western Institute ( Instytut Zachodni ) in Poznań from 1978 to 1990 .
Manuel Argüelles Argüelles ( November 10 , 1875 , in Madrid -- 1945 ) was a Spanish politician and lawyer .
Josep Bargalló i Valls ( Catalan pronunciation : ( ʒuˈzɛb bərɣəˈʎo ) ) ( born 3 October 1958 in Torredembarra , Tarragonès ) is a Catalan philologist .
Frank Castorf ( born 17 July 1951 in East Berlin ) is a German theater director and since 1992 the artistic director of the Volksbühne am Rosa - Luxemburg - Platz .
Guy Novès ( born 5 February 1954 ) is a former French rugby union player and current coach of the French national team .
Angel Orensanz ( b. Huesca , 1940 ) is a Spanish sculptor and painter who has lived in New York City since 1986 .
Henri Lachambre ( 30 December 1846 , Vagney , Vosges -- 12 June 1904 ) was a French manufacturer of balloons .
Jean Bourgogne was a French entomologist .
Pierre Trimouillat ( 1858 -- 5 January 1929 ) was a French songwriter , comedian and singer who was active in the cabarets of Paris in the 1890s .
Claude Antoine Jean Georges Napoléon Coste ( 27 June 1805 -- 17 February 1883 ) was a French guitarist and composer .
Miodrag Grbić , ( 25 December 1901 -- 30 June 1969 ) was a Serbian archeologist and custos .
Wolfgang Ratke ( also Wolfgangus Ratichius or Wolfgang Ratich ) ( 18 October 1571 -- 27 April 1635 ) was a German educational reformer .
Alphonse Royer , ( 10 September 1803 - -11 April 1875 ) was a French author , dramatist and theatre manager , most remembered today for having written ( with his regular collaborator , Gustave Vaëz ) the librettos for Gaetano Donizetti 's opera La favorite and Giuseppe Verdi 's Jérusalem .
Jochen Klepper ( March 22 , 1903 -- December 11 , 1942 ) was a German writer , poet and journalist .
Jean Charles Cazin ( May 25 , 1840 -- March 17 , 1901 ) was a French landscape painter and ceramicist .
Iris Gusner ( born Trautenau 16 January 1941 ) is a German film director and screenwriter .
Roberto Girometti is an Italian film director and cinematographer .
Otto Pöggeler ( 12 December 1928 in Attendorn -- 10 December 2014 ) was a German philosopher .
Joan Herrera i Torres ( Barcelona , Spain , 29 January 1971 ) is a Spanish Catalan lawyer and politician .
Gonçal Mayos Solsona ( born 1957 ) is a Spanish philosopher , essayist and professor at the University of Barcelona .
Luis Francisco de la Cerda y Aragón , ( El Puerto de Santa María , August 2 , 1660 -- Pamplona , January 26 , 1711 ) , 9th Duke of Medinaceli , was a Spanish noble and politician .
Christopher Headington ( 28 April 1930 -- 19 March 1996 ) was an English composer , musicologist , and pianist .
Pierre - François Bouchard ( 29 April 1771 , Orgelet -- 5 august 1822 , Givet ) was an officer in the French Army engineers who is most famous for discovering the Rosetta Stone , an important archaeological find that allowed Ancient Egyptian writing to be understood for the first time in centuries .
Rein Taagepera ( born 28 February 1933 ) is an Estonian political scientist and former politician .
Julius Faucher ( June 13 , 1820 in Berlin -- June 12 , 1878 in Rome ) was a German journalist and a significant advocate of liberalism and free trade .
Canon William Greenwell , FRS , FSA , FSA Scot ( 23 March 1820 -- 27 January 1918 ) was an English archaeologist and Church of England priest .
William George Hoskins CBE FBA ( 22 May 1908 -- 11 January 1992 ) was an English local historian who founded the first university department of English Local History .
Miquel Creus i Muñoz alias Miquel Desclot ( Barcelona , 1952 ) is a Catalan writer and translator known for his Catalan translations of works by Dante , Petrarca or Michelangelo Buonarroti .
Sandrone Dazieri ( born November 4 , 1964 ) is a popular Italian crime writer .
Zdeněk Rykr ( 26 October 1900 -- 15 January 1940 ) was a Czech painter , illustrator , journalist and theatre designer .
Nils Johan Rud ( 24 July 1908 -- 7 June 1993 ) was a Norwegian novelist , writer of short stories , children 's writer , and a magazine editor .
He Jiahong ( Chinese : 何家弘 ; pinyin : Hé Jiāhóng ) ( born May 10 , 1953 in Beijing , China ) is an expert in the field of criminal justice in China and teaches at the Renmin University of China in Beijing .
Joseph - Émile Baeteman ( September 29 , 1880 -- 1938 ) was a French missionary and religious writer .
Wilhelm Dilthey ( German : ( ˈdɪltaɪ ) ; 19 November 1833 -- 1 October 1911 ) was a German historian , psychologist , sociologist , and hermeneutic philosopher , who held Hegel 's Chair in Philosophy at the University of Berlin .
Sigrid Undset ( 20 May 1882 -- 10 June 1949 ) was a Norwegian novelist who was awarded the Nobel Prize for Literature in 1928 .
Nikita Mandryka ( born October 20 , 1940 ) is a French cartoonist of Russian origin .
Simone Michel - Lévy ( 19 January 1906 , Chaussin -- 13 April 1945 Flossenbürg concentration camp ) was a French Resistance worker .
Charles Edward Baring Young ( 19 March 1850 - 22 September 1928 ) was an English educationalist and Conservative politician .
Francesco Trevisani ( April 9 , 1656 -- July 30 , 1746 ) was an Italian painter , active in the period called either early Rococo or late Baroque ( barochetto ) .
Clement Mary Hofbauer , C.Ss . R. , ( German : Klemens Maria Hofbauer ) ( December 26 , 1751 -- March 15 , 1820 ) was a Moravian hermit and later a priest of the Redemptorist congregation .
Shamsur Rahman Faruqi ( Urdu : شمس الرحمٰن فاروقی‎ ) ( born 15 January 1935 ) is an Indian poet and one of the leading Urdu critics and theorists .
Mehmet Ruhi Su ( 20 October 1912 -- 20 September 1985 ) was a Turkish opera singer , Turkish folk singer and saz virtuoso of possibly Armenian origin .
Yemima Avidar - Tchernovitz ( Hebrew : ימימה אבידר - טשרנוביץ‎ ; October 1909 -- March 20 , 1998 ) was an Israeli author whose works became classics of modern Hebrew children 's literature .
Mathias Richling ( born 24 March 1953 in Waiblingen ) is a German actor , author , comedian and Kabarett artist .
Ernst Mally ( German : ( ˈmali ) ; 11 October 1879 -- 8 March 1944 ) was an Austrian philosopher affiliated with the so - called Graz School of phenomenological psychology .
Giancarlo Flati ( L'Aquila , May 11 , 1953 ) is an Italian painter , researcher and writer .
José Gonzalo Zulaica ( San Sebastián , Spain , 1886 - -1956 ) , better known by his pen name Aita Donostia ( Father Donostia or Father San Sebastian , because he was a priest born in San Sebastian , Donostia in the Basque language ) , was a Basque musicologist and composer .
Giovanni Toti ( born 7 September 1968 ) is an Italian journalist and politician , who has been President of Liguria since June 2015 and political counselor of Forza Italia since January 2014 .
Avraham Granot ( Hebrew : אברהם גרנות‎‎ , born Abraham Granovsky ; 18 June 1890 -- 5 July 1962 ) was a Zionist activist , Israeli politician and a signatory of the Israeli declaration of independence .
Antoine Jérôme Balard ( 30 September 1802 -- 30 April 1876 ) was a French chemist and one of the discoverers of bromine .
Nadežda Petrović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Надежда Петровић ; 11/12 October 1873 -- 3 April 1915 ) was a Serbian painter from the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Sanusi Pane ( 14 November 1905 -- 2 January 1968 ) was an Indonesian writer , journalist , and historian .
Phan Văn Hùm ( 9 April 1902 -- 1946 ) was a Vietnamese Trotskyite who took part in the Fourth International in 1922 .
George Leonardos ( Greek : Γιώργος Λεονάρδος ; born 1937 ) is a Greek author of historical novels .
Mate Balota ( 28 September 1898 -- 17 February 1963 ) , born Mijo Mirković , was a prominent Croatian poet , novelist and economist .
Joseph Zen Ze - kiun SDB ( born 12 January 1931 ) is a Chinese Cardinal of the Catholic Church , who served as the sixth Bishop of Hong Kong .
Auguste Joseph Alphonse Gratry ( usually known as Joseph Gratry ) ( 10 March 1805 − 6 February 1872 ) was a French author and theologian .
Đào Duy Từ ( 1572 - -1634 ) was a Vietnamese scholar , poet , military adviser , and mandarin who served under the reign of Nguyễn lord Nguyễn Phúc Nguyên .
Sigrid Weigel ( born March 25 , 1950 , Hamburg ) is a professor of German Literature and Director of the Centre for Literature Research in Berlin .
Stephen Rumbold Lushington ( 6 May 1776 -- 5 Aug 1868 ) was an English Tory politician and an administrator in India .
Madhu Shalini is an Indian film actress and model , who has appeared in Telugu and Tamil language films .
Valentín Parera ( 1895 - -1986 ) was a Spanish actor who appeared in both silent and sound films in the 1920s and 1930s .
Samuel Roffey Maitland ( 1792 - -1866 ) was an English historian and miscellaneous writer on religious topics .
Jean - Louis Beffa ( born August 11 , 1941 , in Nice , France ) is a French businessman .
Alain Maratrat ( born 1950 ) is French actor , theater and opera director known for his innovative interpretations and staging .
Nikolai von Michalewsky ( aka Mark Brandis ) ( January 17 , 1931 -- December 27 , 2000 ) was a German writer and journalist best known for a series of science fiction novels published between 1970 and 1987 .
Haydar Ergülen is one of the important poets of the recent generation in contemporary Turkish literature .
Andreas Bethmann is a German film director , producer , and screenwriter .
Dominique Ané ( born 6 October 1968 ) , better known as `` Dominique A , '' is a French songwriter and singer .

Air Commodore Eric Burchmore , CBE , ( 18 June 1920 -- 11 October 1994 ) was a Royal Air Force officer with a long and distinguished career .
Luke McNamee ( April 4 , 1871 - -December 30 , 1952 ) was a United States Navy Admiral , businessman , and the 10th and 12th Naval Governor of Guam .
Roland R. Wright ( 30 March 1919 -- 19 October 2015 ) was a Brigadier General of the United States Air Force who was a pilot during World War II , the Korean War , and the Vietnam War .
Erich Handke ( 2 November 1920 -- 11 November 1987 ) was a highly decorated Oberfeldwebel in the Luftwaffe during World War II . He was also a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross ( German : Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes ) .
John P. Jumper ( born February 4 , 1945 ) is a retired United States Air Force general , who served as 17th Chief of Staff of the United States Air Force from September 6 , 2001 to September 2 , 2005 .
Captain Harry Godfrey Massy - Miles MC ( 1886 -- 26 April 1918 ) was a British Army medical officer who was awarded the Military Cross for valour in the First World War .
The Grenadiers are an infantry regiment of the Indian Army , formerly part of the Bombay Army and later the pre - independence Indian Army , when the regiment was known as the 4th Bombay Grenadiers .
Captain Sir Houston French CVO ( 27 March 1853 -- 11 June 1932 ) was a British Army officer and an officer of the Yeomen of the Guard .
Ernest Russell Lyon ( 19 December 1922 -- 27 July 1944 ) was a Flying Officer in 234 Squadron of the Royal Air Force during part of World War 2 .
William D. Catto is a United States Marine Corps major general who is the Chief of Staff of the United States European Command .

Helmut Kapp ( born as Konstanty Kapuścik ) was a member of the Gestapo during World War II . He was killed in 1943 by a partisan death squad in Jędrzejów , Poland .

General Sir John Jeremy Mackenzie GCB , OBE , DL ( born 11 February 1941 ) is a former British Army General who became Deputy Supreme Allied Commander Europe .

The river then drains southwards through Moora , flows westerly before joining with the Moore River East near Mogumber , then flows in a westerly direction over the Edengerie Cascade , through the northern edge of the Moore River Nature Reserve , then through the Gingin Scarp , discharging into the Indian Ocean at Guilderton .
The Amisk River is a river in east - central Alberta in the basin of the Beaver River ( Canada ) .

The Appomattox River is a tributary of the James River , approximately 157 miles ( 253 km ) long , in central and eastern Virginia in the United States , named for the Appomattocs Indian tribe who lived along its lower banks in the 17th century .
The Haine ( French : Haine , Dutch : Hene , German : Henne ) is a river in southern Belgium ( Hainaut ) and northern France ( Nord ) , right tributary of the river Scheldt .
The Gediz River ( Turkish : Gediz Nehri , Turkish pronunciation : ( ˈɡediz ) ) is the second - largest river in Anatolia flowing into the Aegean Sea .

The Wisłoka is a river in south - eastern Poland , a tributary of the Vistula river , with a length of 164 kilometres ( 102 miles ) ( 26th longest ) and the basin area of 4,110 square kilometres ( 1,587 sq mi ) .
The Ohio River , which streams westward from Pittsburgh , Pennsylvania , to Cairo , Illinois , is the largest tributary , by volume , of the Mississippi River in the United States .
The Chichester River rises in the Chichester Range below Barrington Tops and east of Careys Peak , and flows generally southeast , joined by the Wangat River , before reaching its confluence with the Williams River at Bandon Grove , north northwest of Dungog .

Tobins River , a perennial stream of the Hastings River catchment , is located in the Northern Tablelands and Mid North Coast districts of New South Wales , Australia .
The Port River ( 34 ° 45′S 138 ° 30′E ) is the western branch of the largest tidal estuary on the eastern side of Gulf St Vincent .

The Keele River is a tributary of the Mackenzie River , about 410 kilometres ( 250 mi ) long , in the western part of the Canadian Northwest Territories .
The Mun River ( Thai : แม่น้ำมูล , rtgs : Maenam Mun , IPA : ( mɛ̂ːnáːm muːn ) ) , sometimes spelled Moon River , is a tributary of the Mekong River .
The Wilge River ( Afrikaans : Wilgerivier , meaning `` willow river '' ) is a tributary of the Vaal River in central South Africa .
The Calabar River in Cross River State , Nigeria flows from the north past the city of Calabar , joining the larger Cross River about 8 kilometres ( 5.0 mi ) to the south .
The Red Volta is a river that flows through the Upper East region of North Ghana and the international border of North Ghana flowing about 320 km to join the White Volta in the Upper East region of North Ghana and arising in Burkina Faso .
The Liswarta is a river in south - central Poland , a tributary of the Warta river .
The Onyx River is an Antarctic meltwater stream which flows westward through the Wright Valley from Wright Lower Glacier and Lake Brownworth at the foot of the glacier to Lake Vanda , during the few months of the Antarctic summer .
The Bukhan River ( North Han River ) is a tributary of the Han River that flows through both North and South Korea .
The Michelsbach is a tributary of the River Rhine in the German region of South Palatinate .

Xtreme 4x4 is a half hour series airing on Spike TV that began in January 2005 as part of Spike 's weekend Powerblock line up .
MTV Halo - Halo is a Filipino music video television program owned by MTV Pinoy , a 24-hour music / entertainment television network owned by MTV Networks Asia Pacific .
Road Hockey Rumble is a half - hour reality series produced by Paperny Entertainment and broadcast on OLN .
The Superior Sex was a Canadian game show television series which aired on CBC Television in 1961 .
Tattingers ( later Tattinger 's ) is an American comedy - drama series that aired by the NBC television network as part of its 1988 fall lineup .
Airport Live was a live television programme broadcast on BBC Two over four nights from 17 June 2013 .
Wendell & Vinnie is an American sitcom television series that premiered on Nickelodeon on February 16 , 2013 and ran until September 22 , 2013 .
King & Maxwell is an American drama television series that debuted on June 10 , 2013 , and aired on TNT .
Volcano Live was a live television programme broadcast on BBC Two from 9 July 2012 .
Spotlight on Film was a Canadian film informational television series which aired on CBC Television in 1969 .
The Disney 's Friends for Change Games are Olympic - based televised games aired on the Disney Channel and part of the station 's Friends for Change initiative .
A Brush with Fame is a light hearted ITV daytime television show , featuring a nationwide search to find Britain 's best amateur portrait painter .
W.E.B. is an American TV series that aired for less than a month on NBC in 1978 .
Reef Doctors was an Australian television drama series that premiered on Network Ten on 9 June 2013 .
Time Was is a documentary television series that premiered on HBO on November 11 , 1979 .
First Outlook was a morning weather program produced by The Weather Channel , an American television station .
Vinterkrysset is a wintertime spin - off variation on Sommarkrysset , the program has been broadcast in two rounds on TV4 .
You Should Be So Lucky ! was a BBC children 's television programme broadcast in 1986/87 .
Time Team is a British television series that originally aired on British Channel 4 from 1994 to 2014 .
Pig Goat Banana Cricket ( also abbreviated as PGBC ) is an American animated television series created by Dave Cooper and Johnny Ryan for Nickelodeon .
Playboy Prime is an adult reality compilation series of Playboy TV programming .
Alcanzar una estrella ( `` To reach a star '' ) is a Mexican telenovela first broadcast on Canal de las Estrellas in 1990 .
Kabhi To Milenge is an Indian television series that aired on Zee TV based on the story of a woman who has been wrongly convicted for the murder of her own husband .
The PBA on Vintage Sports was a presentation of Philippine Basketball Association games by Vintage Sports , a sports - oriented media company on Philippine television networks Banahaw Broadcasting Corporation from 1982 to 1984 , People 's Television Network from 1984 to 1995 , and Intercontinental Broadcasting Corporation from 1996 to 1999 .
Kyle XY is an American science fiction television series produced by ABC Family .
Monster Warriors is an original Canadian television series , which airs on YTV in Canada , and also on Jetix since April 2006 in the United Kingdom .
Cool McCool was an animated series that ran on NBC from September 10 , 1966 to August 30 , 1969 with three segments per show , running to 60 segments in all .
El Juramento ( The Promise ) is the title of a Spanish - language telenovela produced by the United States - based television network Telemundo .
It 's Not Easy Being Green is a television series on BBC Two starring Dick Strawbridge and focusing on how to live an environmentally friendly , low impact life .
Medcezir ( English : `` Tide '' ) is a Turkish teen drama television series first aired on Star TV from September 13 , 2013 .

Graduados ( English : The Graduates ) is a 2012 Argentine telenovela which was broadcast by Telefe from March 12 to December 19 .

Canadian Authors is a Canadian biographical television series which aired on CBC Television in 1978 .
Fabulous Funnies is a Filmation cartoon series on NBC that ran for one season in 1978 ; it features animated versions of newspaper comic strips and attempted to teach moral lessons to children .
No Béarla is a four - part documentary style programme broadcast on Irish language television channel TG4 and produced by Dearg Films RTÉ / TG4 .
Wunderkind Little Amadeus , commonly referred to as Little Amadeus , is a German animated television series ( known as `` The Adventures of Young Mozart '' ) that debuted on PBS Kids Go ! on September 7 , 2008 through March 1 , 2009 .
This Hour Has Seven Days is a controversial CBC Television newsmagazine which ran from 1964 to 1966 .
Jack 's Big Music Show is an American musical children 's television series originally airing on the Nick Jr. television network .
Hasratein ( Desires ) is an Indian television soap opera that was telecast on Zee TV in the mid 1990s .
Motormouth was a Saturday morning children 's television series that was produced by Television South and aired across the ITV network for four series , running between 3 September 1988 and 4 April 1992 .
Ritmo Deportivo ( translated as Sporty Rhythm in English ) is a weekly television series airing Saturdays at 5pm/4C on Spanish - language network Telemundo , part of the NBC Deportes line of programming .
The World Around Us was an Australian documentary television series that aired on the Seven Network between 1979 until 2006 .
Maging Sino Ka Man ( lit . Whoever You May Be ) was a critically acclaimed Filipino primetime drama series that premiered on ABS - CBN on October 9 , 2006 .
I Just Want My Pants Back is an American comedy - drama that premiered with a special sneak peek on August 28 , 2011 on MTV , with the series airing the new episodes beginning on February 2 , 2012 .
That Peter Kay Thing is a series of six spoof documentaries shown on Channel 4 in January 1999 .
Butternut Square was a Canadian children 's television series which aired on CBC Television between October 19 , 1964 and February 10 , 1967 .
Alan Watts on Living was a Canadian television miniseries which aired on CBC Television in 1971 .
Saving Kids is an Australian medical documentary television series that screened on Network Ten in 2008 .
Lemur Street is a British television show produced by Oxford Scientific Films for Animal Planet International which is based on the successful format of Meerkat Manor .

The 7 O'Clock News was the main news programme , broadcast each weekday at 7:00pm , on British digital television channel BBC Three between 9 February 2003 to 2 December 2005 .

Maalaala Mo Kaya ( English : `` Would you remember ? '' ; abbreviated as MMK ) is a Philippine drama anthology series broadcast on ABS - CBN every Saturday evenings after Dance Kids and before Pilipinas Got Talent ( season 5 ) and is hosted by Charo Santos - Concio .
Emergency Vets is a reality television series that airs on the U.S. cable network Animal Planet .
Stroker and Hoop is an American Adobe Flash animated television series on Cartoon Network 's late night programming block , Adult Swim .
Inspector George Gently ( titled George Gently for the pilot and first series ) is a British television series produced by Company Pictures for BBC One , set in the 1960s and based on some of the 46 Inspector Gently novels written by Alan Hunter .
Kevin Hill is an American legal drama that aired on UPN during the 2004 - -2005 TV season .
The Ethiopian white - footed mouse or White - footed stenocephalemys ( Stenocephalemys albipes ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Khassaraporn Suta ( Thai : เกษราภรณ์ สุตา ; born December 12 , 1971 ) is a Thai weightlifter who competed in the women 's 58 kg at the 2000 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal with a combined lift of 210.0 kg .

Harry Plate ( * 18 October 1853 in Hanover ; † 29 April 1939 in Hanover ) was a German tinsmith and long time member of the Hanover chamber of artisans .

Lee Kok Cheong ( 1939 -- December 14 , 1993 ) was the Head of the English Proficiency Unit at the National University of Singapore .

Giovanni Carestini ( c. 1704 in Filottrano , near Ancona -- c. 1760 ) was an Italian castrato of the 18th century , who sang in the operas and oratorios of George Frideric Handel .

Hans - Wilhelm Koepcke ( 13 June 1914 in Saatzig , German Empire -- 21 November 2000 in Hamburg , Germany ) was a zoologist , ornithologist , and herpetologist .

Moses ibn Tibbon ( born in Marseille ; flourished between 1240 and 1283 ) was a Jewish physician , author and translator in Provence .

Wilhelm Michel ( born in Metz on 9 August 1877 ; died in Darmstadt on 16 April 1942 ) was a German writer who won the 1925 Georg Büchner Prize .
Stanisław Ossowski ( Lipno , 22 May 1897 -- 7 November 1963 , Warsaw ) was one of Poland 's most important sociologists .
Frantsishak Alyakhnovich ( March 9 , 1883 , Vilnius -- March 3 , 1944 , Vilnius , Belarusian : Францішак Аляхновіч , Polish : Franciszek Olechnowicz , Czech : František Olechnovič ) was a Belarusian writer , journalist and Gulag survivor of Polish and Czech origins .

George Grosz ( July 26 , 1893 -- July 6 , 1959 ) was a German artist known especially for his caricatural drawings and paintings of Berlin life in the 1920s .

Daniel Sturgeon ( October 27 , 1789 -- July 3 , 1878 ) was an American physician , banker and Democratic party politician from Uniontown , Pennsylvania .

Béla Miklós was born into a Székely primipilus family in Budapest on 11 June 1890 .

Archbishop Paulo Lopes de Faria died on July 16 , 2009 , in Belo Horizonte at the age of 78 .

Eberhard Fraas was born in Stuttgart , the son of Oscar Fraas ( 1824 - -1897 ) , a curator and professor at the geological and paleontological department of the Württemberg Royal Natural Cabinet .
Olivier Greif ( 3 January 1950 , Paris -- 13 May 2000 , Paris ) was a French composer of Polish - Jewish parentage .

Louis de Cormontaigne ( 1696 at Strasbourg -- 1752 in Metz ) was a French military engineer .
Muhammad Ahmad Mahgoub ( 17 May 1908 in Aldewem city at the age of seven he came to Khartoum -- 1976 ) was a foreign minister , then Prime Minister , of Sudan and an important writer who has published several volumes of poetry in the Arabic language .
After graduating with a law degree from Faculte de droit de Paris and from HEC Paris , Jacques Dauphin re - opened the Parisian - based office created by his father Eugene Dauphin in 1921 who closed it during WWII to prevent any collaboration with the Nazis .
William Henry Eustis ( 1845 -- November 30 , 1928 ) was the 17th mayor of Minneapolis , Republican nominee for Governor of Minnesota in 1898 , and a philanthropist .
Martin Benka ( 21 September 1888 , Kostolište -- 28 June 1971 , Malacky ) was a Slovak painter and illustrator .
Ethel Bailey Higgins ( 1866 - -1963 ) was an American botanist and the curator of botany at the San Diego Natural History Museum from 1943 to 1957 ; she continued to serve as associate curator from 1957 to 1963 .
Julia Clara Catherine Maria Dolores Robins Norton Birk Olsen Hitchens ( December 25 , 1907 in San Antonio , Texas -- August 1 , 1973 in Orange County , California ) , better known as Dolores Hitchens , was an American mystery novelist who wrote prolifically from 1938 until her death .
Tertius Bosch ( 14 March 1966 in Vereeniging , Transvaal -- 14 February 2000 in Westville , KwaZulu - Natal ) was a South African cricketer who played in one Test and two ODIs in 1992 .
Josef Sudek ( 17 March 1896 , Kolín , Bohemia -- 15 September 1976 , Prague ) was a Czech photographer , best known for his photographs of Prague .
Károly Szabó ( November 17 , 1916 -- October 28 , 1964 ) was an employee of the Swedish Embassy in Budapest from 1944 to 1945 .
Domenico Pacini ( Marino , February 20 , 1878 -- Rome , May 23 , 1934 ) was an Italian physicist noted for his contributions to the discovery of cosmic rays .
Mohamed Arbi Zarrouk Khaznadar ( born 1760 in Le Bardo - October 29 , 1822 in Tunis ) was Prime Minister and Khaznadar ( minister of Finances ) of Beylik of Tunis .
Cenobio Paniagua y Vásques ( September 30 , 1821 , Tlalpujahua , Michoacán -- November 2 , 1882 , Córdoba , Veracruz ) was a Mexican composer .
Born Alan Ernest Caldwell in Liverpool , Storm was the singer and leader of Rory Storm and the Hurricanes , a Liverpudlian band who were contemporaries of the Beatles in the late 1950s and early 1960s .
Colin Jordan died at his Pateley Bridge home on 9 April 2009 .
Astolfo Petrazzi ( 1583 - 1653 or 1665 ) was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly in his hometown of Siena , but also Spoleto and Rome .
Christina Carpenter or Christine Carpenter ( fl . 1329 - -1332 ) was a 14th - century anchoress or recluse in the village of Shere , Surrey , in southern England .
The Fabri family moved to the Soviet Union in 1932 , where Ernst Fabri edited a German - language newspaper in Moscow .
Issoufou Saidou - Djermakoye ( born July 10 , 1920 in Dosso , Niger , and died June 30 , 2000 in Paris ) was a politician from Niger who was elected to the French Senate in 1958 .
Albert van Schendel ( 21 September 1912 in Lage Zwaluwe -- 12 April 1990 in Muret , France ) was a Dutch professional road bicycle racer .
Eduard Sievers ( 25 November 1850 , Lippoldsberg -- 30 March 1932 , Leipzig ) was a philologist of the classical and Germanic languages .
Thomas Underwood ( May 6 , 1863 -- May 10 , 1948 ) was a building developer and the 13th mayor of Calgary , Alberta .
Göran Tunström ( 14 May 1937 , Borgvik , Grums Municipality -- February 5 , 2000 , Stockholm ) was a Swedish author .
Johann Baptist Allgaier ( June 19 , 1763 , Schussenried -- January 3 , 1823 , Vienna ) was a German - Austrian chess master and theoretician .
Eastman Johnson ( July 29 , 1824 -- April 5 , 1906 ) was an American painter and co - founder of the Metropolitan Museum of Art , New York City , with his name inscribed at its entrance .
Alejandro Lerroux y García ( La Rambla , Córdoba , 4 March 1864 -- Madrid , 25 June 1949 ) was a Spanish politician who was the leader of the Radical Republican Party during the Second Spanish Republic .
Ewald Rohlfs ( 1911 Bremen , Germany - 1984 ) was a test pilot .
Franz Hettinger ( 13 January 1819 , at Aschaffenburg -- 26 January 1890 , at Würzburg ) was a German Catholic theologian .
His family home still stands at 440 Osgood Street in North Andover and his home in New York City , the Samuel Osgood House , served as the country 's first Presidential mansion .
Sir Sydney Walling ( 12 July 1907 -- 8 October 2009 ) was an Antiguan cricketer who played for Antigua and Barbuda during the 1930s and 1940s .
Robert Dorning died on 21 February 1989 in London of diabetes .
Jean - Pierre Ramel ( the younger ) ( 1768 , Cahors - 15 August 1815 , Toulouse ) was a French general during the French Revolutionary Wars and the First French Empire .
Sammy Davis Sr . died May 21 , 1988 , in Beverly Hills , California , at the age of 87 , of natural causes , two years before the death of his son , Sammy Davis Jr.
Andrew Heiskell ( September 13 , 1915 , Naples - July 6 , 2003 Darien , Connecticut ) was chairman and CEO of Time Inc. ( 1960 - -1980 ) , and also known for his philanthropy , including for the New York Public Library .
Onni Rajasaari ( 2 March 1910 in Hanko -- 12 November 1994 in Hanko ) was a Finnish athlete specializing in long jump and triple jump .
Blanche Honegger Moyse ( /moʊˈiːz/ ; September 23 , 1909 -- February 10 , 2011 ) was a conductor living in Brattleboro , Vermont .

Jakob Fürchtegott Dielmann ( 9 September 1809 , Frankfurt - 30 May 1885 , Frankfurt ) was a German illustrator , genre and landscape painter .

Leonardo Alenza y Nieto ( 6 November 1807 , Madrid - 30 June 1845 , Madrid ) was a Spanish painter and engraver in the Romantic style ; associated with the Costumbrista movement .
Charles Fey ( born August Fey in Vöhringen , Bavaria ) ( September 9 , 1862 --November 10 , 1944 ) was a San Francisco mechanic who is best known for inventing the slot machine .
Félicie de Fauveau ( Livorno , 1801 -- Florence , 1886 ) was a nineteenth - century French sculptor who was a precursor of the pre - Raphaelite style .
Charles Stewart Mott ( June 2 , 1875 -- February 18 , 1973 ) was an American businessman , philanthropist and the 50th and 55th Mayor of Flint , Michigan .
Herbert Dingle ( 2 August 1890 , London -- 4 September 1978 , Kingston upon Hull ) was an English physicist and natural philosopher , who served as president of the Royal Astronomical Society from 1951 to 1953 .
Anton or Antonio Maria Fabrizi or Fabrizzi ( 1594 - 1649 ) was an Italian painter , active in Perugia and Foligno in a Baroque style .

On Friday , March 27 , 1868 , at two in the afternoon , a massive crowd armed with guns and swords attempted to storm the Rova of Antananarivo , residence of Queen Rasoherina .

Jens August Schade ( 10 January 1903 , Skive , Denmark - 11 November 1978 , Copenhagen ) was a Danish poet .

Josef Oberhauser was born in Munich during World War I. He was the son of Melchior Oberhauser , and he grew up with his parents .

Samuel Comstock ( February 6 , 1680 -- October 26 , 1752 ) was a member of the Connecticut House of Representatives from Norwalk in the sessions of October 1711 , October 1714 , May 1720 , October 1723 , October 1725 , October 1726 , October 1727 , October 1728 , October 1729 , and October 1730 .
Richard S. Thompson ( December 30 , 1916 -- December 28 , 1997 ) was from 1972 to 1984 a Democratic member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from District 22 , which now includes Grant , La Salle , Winn , and Rapides parishes .
John Cameron Henry , Jr. ( born November 1 , 1974 ) is an American state legislator and business analyst from Metairie , Louisiana , who has been serving since January 2008 as a Republican member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from District 82 in Jefferson and Orleans parishes .
Frederick Temple ( 30 November 1821 -- 23 December 1902 ) was an English academic , teacher , churchman , and Archbishop of Canterbury , from 1896 until his death .
Petero Mataca ( 28 April 1933 -- 30 June 2014 ) born at Cawaci , on Ovalau Island , served as the Roman Catholic archbishop of Suva , Fiji until his resignation in 2012 .
Ramwod or Ramwold ( c. 900 in Trier ( ? ) - † 17 May 1000 in Regensburg ) was an abbot of St. Emmeram 's Abbey in Regensburg .
John Flamsteed FRS ( 19 August 1646 -- 31 December 1719 ) was an English astronomer and the first Astronomer Royal .
Charles H. O'Neill ( May 1800 -- November 8 , 1897 ) was an Irish - American politician and a Democrat who served as Mayor of Jersey City , New Jersey , from May 4 , 1868 until April 10 , 1869 , when he resigned , and again from May 2 , 1870 until May 3 , 1874 .
William Sanford Pennington ( November 7 , 1757 -- September 17 , 1826 ) was the sixth Governor of New Jersey , serving from 1813 to 1815 .

Clement Reyner D.D. ( 1589 - -1651 ) was an English Benedictine monk , who became abbot of Lamspringe in Germany .
William Longchamp ( died 1197 ) , sometimes known as William de Longchamp or William de Longchamps , was a medieval Lord Chancellor , Chief Justiciar , and Bishop of Ely in England .

Princess Phra Nang Chao Suvadhana ( Thai : สุวัทนา ; rtgs : Suwatthana , 15 April 1906 -- 10 October 1985 ) was the royal consort of King Vajiravudh ( or Rama VI ) of Siam .
Eugenia Livanos ( Greek : Ευγενία Λιβανού ; 1927 -- 4 May 1970 ) was the third wife of Stavros Niarchos .
In July 2008 , Michele Hicks married British actor Jonny Lee Miller in Malibu , California .
Fredrikke Marie Qvam ( 31 May 1843 -- 10 September 1938 ) was a Norwegian humanitarian leader , feminist and the wife of Prime Minister Ole Anton Qvam .
Eudokia Komnene ( or Eudocia Comnena ) ( Greek : Εὐδοκία Κομνηνή , Eudokia Komnēnē ) ( c. 1160 -- c. 1203 ) was a grand - niece of Byzantine Emperor Manuel I Komnenos , and wife of William VIII of Montpellier .
Stella Farentino ( born February 16 , 1962 ) is the fourth wife of actor James Farentino and she went on to become an actress herself .
Victoria Lorna Aluquin - Fernandez , better known by her stage name Lorna Tolentino , sometimes known as L.T. , an abbreviation of her screen name ( born December 23 , 1961 ) , is a Filipina actress , host , executive producer and widow of actor Rudy Fernandez .
Maria Isabel of Portugal ( Maria Isabel Francisca ; 19 May 1797 -- 26 December 1818 ) was an Infanta of Portugal who became the Queen of Spain as the second wife of Ferdinand VII of Spain .
Anna Porphyrogenita ( Greek : Άννα Πορφυρογέννητη , Russian : Анна Византийская , Ukrainian : Анна Порфірогенета ; 13 March 963 -- 1011 ) was a Grand Princess consort of Kiev ; she was married to Grand Prince Vladimir the Great .

Oryctocephalus indicus is a species of corynexochid trilobite from the Cambrian .
Callionymus kotthausi is a species of dragonet found only in the Indian Ocean off India where it occurs at depths of from 138 to 211 metres ( 453 to 692 ft ) .

Phosphuga is a genus of carrion beetles
Angelica atropurpurea , known commonly as purplestem angelica , great angelica , American angelica , high angelica , and masterwort , is a species of flowering plant that can be found in moist and swampy woodlands , mostly by riverbanks , in eastern North America .

Modelia granosa , common name the southern cat 's eye , is a medium to large species of sea snail which has a shell with a pearly interior and a calcareous operculum .

Isoperla carbonaria is a species of stonefly in the family Perlodidae .
Heliothis nubila is a species of moth of the Noctuidae family , described by Hampson in 1903 .

Phobaeticus chani or Chan 's megastick is a species of stick insect .

Impatiens halongensis is a species of the family Balsaminaceae native to Vietnam .

Rhynchobdellida , the jawless leeches , are classified as an order of the Hirudinea .

Afrocominella capensis , common name the elongate whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae .
Sepiola atlantica , also known as the Atlantic bobtail , is a species of bobtail squid native to the northeastern Atlantic Ocean ( 65ºN to 35ºN ) , from Iceland , the Faroe Islands and western Norway to the Moroccan coast .

Allophylus chartaceus ( Kurz ) Radlkofer is a plant species in the family Sapindaceae .

Olearia erubescens , commonly known as Moth Daisy - bush or Pink - tip Daisy - bush , is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
