Melica altissima , commonly known as Siberian melic grass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that was introduced to Ontario , Oklahoma and New York .
Azospirillum halopraeferens is a species of nitrogen - fixing bacteria associated with the roots of Leptochloa fusca and black mangrove .
Galium antarcticum , commonly known as Antarctic bedstraw or subantarctic bedstraw , is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family .
Rhinosimus is a genus of narrow - waisted bark beetles , usually recognized by the long rostrum on the head of an adult beetle .
In the fossil record , pollen has been found which seems to be related to the living Lactoris species .
Archaeopsittacus is a genus of prehistoric parrot .
Agrostis oregonensis is a species of grass known by the common name Oregon bent grass .
Cycadeoidaceae is a family of bennettitalean plant which flourished in the Mesozoic era .
Haplosciadium abyssinicum is a species of flowering plant in the Apiaceae ( Umbelliferae ) family ; it is the only member of its genus .
Shirakiopsis is a genus of flowering plants in the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1999 .
Eudactylina corrugata is a species of parasitic copepod found on the little skate ( Leucoraja erinacea ) and the thorny skate ( Amblyraja radiata ) that is only known from St. Andrews , New Brunswick and Woods Hole , Massachusetts .
Inermocoelotes brevispinus is a funnel - web spider species found in Bulgaria .
Peltops is a genus of bird in the family Artamidae .
Megalagrion leptodemas is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae that is endemic to the island of Oʻahu in Hawaii .
Dieteria is a North American genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family .
Umbilicaria vellea is a species of lichen in the genus Umbilicaria .
Elbretornis is an extinct genus of enantiornithine which existed in what is now Salta Province , Argentina during the late Cretaceous period .
Phyllomenia is a genus of sterrofustian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like , marine mollusks .
Aconitum columbianum is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common names Columbian monkshood or western monkshood .
Irpex destruens is a species of fungus in the family Meruliaceae .
Gerrardina is a genus of two species of trees , shrubs , and scrambling shrubs found in southeastern Africa .
Alopecurus setarioides is a species of foxtail grass that is found in France , Greece , Italy and Turkey .
Distorsio reticularis , common name reticulate distorsio , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Personidae , the Distortio snails .
Carabus exiguus evae is a black - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily , that is endemic to Qinghai , China .
Phrynocephalus versicolor , the variegated toadhead agama , is a species of agamid lizard found in desert areas of China and Mongolia .
Fritillaria anhuiensis is a Chinese species of bulb - forming plants in the lily family .
The Trombidiformes are a large , diverse order of mites .
Eucrypta micrantha is a species of flowering plant in the waterleaf family known by the common name dainty desert hideseed .
Panellus stipticus , commonly known as the bitter oyster , the astringent panus , the luminescent panellus , or the stiptic fungus , is a species of fungus in the family Mycenaceae , and the type species of the genus Panellus .
Nichollsia is a genus of isopod crustaceans from India .
Sirex juvencus is a species of wasp found in Europe , Siberia , Sakhalin Island , Japan , the Philippines , Algeria , New Zealand , and several other countries .
Being very poorly known , the Bornean peacock - pheasant was long considered to be a subspecies of the Malayan peacock - pheasant , but the two species are well - isolated geographically .
Sarcolaena is a genus of flowering plants in the family Sarcolaenaceae .
Melica smithii , Smith 's melic grass is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in such Canadian provinces as Alberta , British Columbia , Quebec , Ontario , and the US states such as Idaho , Michigan , Montana , South Dakota , Washington , Wisconsin , and Wyoming .
Hedera maderensis , or Madeiran Ivy , is a species of Ivy ( genus Hedera ) which is native to the Atlantic coast in Madeira island .
Bassarodes siriaca is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Bassarodes .
Liaoxitriton is an extinct genus of prehistoric salamanders from the Mesozoic of China .
Pseudorthonychiidae is an extinct , monogeneric ( contains only one genus ) family of fossil snails , gastropod mollusks in the clade Cycloneritimorpha ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Calandrinia breweri is a species of flowering plant in the purslane family known by the common name Brewer 's redmaids .
Inglorius is a genus of skippers in the family Hesperiidae , containing only one species , the Mediocre Skipper ( Inglorius mediocris ) .
Paradyemus nodicollis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paradyemus .
Napeogenes tolosa , the Tolosa Tigerwing , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
The Rhipsalideae are a small tribe of cacti , comprising four genera ( and around 60 species ) .
Gymnosteris is a small genus of flowering plants in the phlox family .
Clathrina intermedia is a sponge species of the genus Clathrina .
Geitodoris heathi , common name `` Heath 's dorid '' , is a species of colorful sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Dorididae .
The Muli pika ( Ochotona muliensis ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Hemaris is a genus of sphinx moths in the subfamily Macroglossinae .
The Almirante Trail toad ( Incilius peripatetes ) is a species of toad endemic to Panama .
Chianghsia is an extinct genus of monstersaurian platynotan known from the Late Cretaceous deposits of the Nanxiong Formation , southern China .
Terebra pertusa , common name the perforated auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Argostemmateae is a tribe of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family and contains about 215 species in 4 genera .
Dasia olivacea , the olive Dasia or olive tree skink , is a species of skink native to Southeast Asia .
Ixodes pacificus , the Western black - legged tick , is a species of Ixodes , a parasitic tick found on the western coast of North America .
Nanula tasmanica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails
Hygrophila gracillima is a species of plant in the family Acanthaceae .
Sanicula bipinnata is a species of plant in the carrot family known by the common name poison sanicle .
Callinectes marginatus , known as the `` sharptooth swimcrab '' or `` marbled swimcrab '' , is a species of swimming crab in the genus Callinectes .
Lessoniaceae are a family of kelp .
Octopus chierchiae commonly known as the lesser Pacific striped octopus is a species of octopus .
Trachymetopon is an extinct genus of prehistoric coelacanth .
Conomurex fasciatus , common name the lined conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Berosus metalliceps is a species of hydrophilid beetle from the United States , Mexico , the Bahamas and Cuba .
Trophodiscus almus is a species of starfish in the family Astropectinidae .
Xyris torta , the slender yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plants in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Zygia is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae .
Rimella fissurella is an extinct species of fossil sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Lasthenia coronaria is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name royal goldfields .
Centromadia parryi ( pappose tarweed ) is a species of North American plants in the tarweed tribe within the sunflower family .
Pseudomonas tolaasii is a species of Gram - negative soil bacteria that is the causal agent of bacterial blotch on cultivated mushrooms ( Agaricus bisporus ) .
Tomohammus strandi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Tomohammus .
Onykia ingens , the greater hooked squid , is a species of squid in the family Onychoteuthidae .
The Luidia sarsi is a species of starfish .
Milnesium tardigradum is a cosmopolitan species of tardigrade that can be found in a diverse range of environments .
Descurainia torulosa is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Wyoming tansymustard and Wind River tansymustard .
Metaviridae are a family of viruses which exist as retrotransposons in a eukaryotic host 's genome .
Megachile rubi is a species of leaf cutting bee in the family Megachilidae , found in the eastern United States .
Tephrodornithidae is a family of birds that includes the genera Hemipus , Tephrodornis and Philentoma .
Lotus alpinus , common name alpine bird's - foot trefoil , is a species of legume in the family Fabaceae .
Beaked whales are the members of the family Ziphiidae , which consists of 22 species .
Chaenostoma cordatum , also known by the names bacopa or ornamental bacopa ( not to be confused with the genus Bacopa ) , is one of 52 species in the genus Chaenostoma ( Scrophulariaceae ) , and is best known in its cultivated forms .
Ichthyophaga is a genus of two species of eagles , closely related to the sea - eagles in the genus Haliaeetus .
Xylodromus sassuchini is a species of rove beetle in the Omaliinae subfamily that is endemic to Russia .
Altirhinus ( /ˌæltɨˈraɪnəs/ ; `` high snout '' ) is a genus of iguanodontian ornithopod dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous Period of Mongolia .
Hydrochorea is a legume genus in the subfamily Mimosoideae .
Stegastes leucostictus is a species of damselfish found near the sea bed in shallow waters on the western fringes of the Atlantic Ocean .
Nikkasaurus is an extinct genus of therapsid .
Rhododendron occidentale , the western azalea or California azalea , is one of two deciduous Rhododendron species native to western North America ( the other is Rhododendron albiflorum ) .
Russula laeta is a brittle gill species that was first described by Julius Schäffer in 1952 .
Vulpes skinneri is a species of extinct fox in the genus Vulpes of the early Pleistocene , identified based on fossil remains dated to about 2 million years ago .
Bensoniella is a monotypic genus of plants in the saxifrage family containing the single species Bensoniella oregona ( also , B. oregana ) , which is known by the common name Oregon bensoniella , or simply bensoniella .
Vanda bensonii is a species of orchid found from Assam to Thailand .
Plasmodium lucens is a parasite of the genus Plasmodium subgenus Novyella Like all Plasmodium species P. lucens has both vertebrate and insect hosts .
Cymbiola cymbiola , common name the crown volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Kallidecthes is an extinct genus of crustacean .
Sawadaea tulasnei is a form of Powdery mildew is a species of fungus in the family Erysiphaceae .
Carex lyngbyei is a species of sedge known by the common name Lyngbye 's sedge .
Columella aspera is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vertiginidae , the vertigo snails .
Acentrogobius is a genus of gobies native to marine , fresh and brackish waters of the coasts of the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Allopathes desbonni is a species of Coral of the genus Allopathes .
Polemon fulvicollis , or the African snake - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Syritta pipiens is a very common species of European hover fly .
Micromelerpeton is an extinct genus of dissorophoidean euskelian temnospondyl within the family Micromelerpetontidae .
Perideridia lemmonii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Lemmon 's yampah and tuni .
Nanorana pleskei ( common names : Songpan slow frog , Pleske 's high altitude frog , plateau frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Atriplex bunburyana , commonly known as Silver Saltbush , is a species of saltbush endemic to Western Australia .
Sclerodactyla briareus , commonly known as the hairy sea cucumber , is a species of marine invertebrate in the family Sclerodactylidae .
Stalachtis euterpe is a species of butterfly of the Riodinidae family .
Ectopocynus ( `` strange dog '' ) is an extinct genus of small bone crushing carnivorous mammal similar to a dog of the family Canidae which inhabited North America during the Oligocene .
Gynatrix is a genus of dioecious flowering plants in the family Malvaceae , endemic to south - east Australia .
Synodus intermedius , the sand diver , is a species of fish in the lizardfish family , Synodontidae , a basal ray - finned fish in the class Actinopterygii .
Thrinax excelsa , commonly known as broad thatch , is a species of palm which is endemic to Jamaica .
Ampulex dementor is a species of cockroach wasp native to Thailand , described in 2014 by Michael Ohl of the Museum für Naturkunde in Berlin , Germany .
Ophioscincus is a genus of skink known to inhabit parts of Australia .
Lasioglossum semisculptum , also known as the Lasioglossum ( Ctenomia ) semisculptum , is a species of bees in the genus Lasioglossum , of the family Halictidae .
Buddleja thyrsoides is a lowland species endemic from southern Paraguay to the deltas of the Río de la Plata and Paraná River in Brazil , Argentina and Uruguay .
Pareuseboides albomarmoratus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pareuseboides .
Eocystites was a genus of Cambrian stem - group echinoderm of Australia and Vermont .
Sulfuricurvum kujiense is a facultatively anaerobic , chemolithoautotrophic , sulfur - oxidizing bacterium , the type species of its genus .
Byrsonima crassifolia is a species of flowering plant in the acerola family , Malpighiaceae , that is native to tropical America .
Obruchevichthys is an extinct genus of tetrapod from Latvia during the Late Devonian .
Chilostoma ziegleri is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicidae , the true snails .
Drosophila pseudoobscura is a species of fruit fly , used extensively in lab studies of speciation .
Berberis darwinii is a species of barberry in the family Berberidaceae , native to southern Chile and Argentina and naturalized elsewhere .
Nagia linteola is a species of moth in the Erebidae family , this species occurs in South Africa , Congo , Yemen , the Comoros , Mauritius , Madagascar , Indonesia ( Borneo ) , Thailand and in Australia , where it has been recorded from Western Australia , the Northern Territory , Queensland and Victoria .
Tabernaemontana cordata is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae family .
Micropterix anglica is an extinct species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Jarzembowski in 1980 .
Archaeornithomimus ( meaning `` ancient bird mimic '' ) is a genus of ornithomimosaurian theropod dinosaur from the Late Cretaceous of China , 70 million years ago .
The Latidae , known as the lates perches , are a family of perch - like fishes found in Africa , Asia and the Indian and western Pacific Oceans .
Paradoxides davidis is a species of trilobite of the Paradoxidae family .
Crusafontia is an extinct genus of Mesozoic mammal .
Pseudochondrostoma is a genus of cyprinid fish that occurs in the Iberian Peninsula .
Brachinus italicus is a species of ground beetle from the Brachininae subfamily that can be found in Italy and on the island of Sicily .
Procambarus econfinae , sometimes called the Panama City crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Hoburogekko is an extinct genus of gecko that includes a single species , Hoburogekko suchanovi , from the Early Cretaceous of Mongolia .
Dismegistus costalis is a species of true bugs belonging to the family Parastrachiidae .
Neolamprologus brevis is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it lives in snail shells , primarily of the genus Neothauma .
Pachydactylus robertsi , commonly known as the large - scaled gecko , shielded thick - toed gecko , or Rauhschuppen - Dickfingergecko in German , is an African species of gecko .
Brucella is a genus of Gram - negative bacteria , named after David Bruce ( 1855 - 1931 ) .
Trachyglanis is a genus of loach catfishes from Africa .
Craspedochiton rubiginosus oliveri is a subspecies of chiton in the family Acanthochitonidae .
Lebia maraniana is a species of ground beetles in the Harpalinae subfamily that is endemic to Spain .
Koshisaurus is a monospecific genus of basal hadrosauroid from the Kitadani Formation in Japan .
Nenga is a monoecious genus of flowering plant in the palm endemic to Southeast Asia , commonly called pinang palm .
Stenotrema florida , common name the Apalachicola slitmouth , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Polygyridae .
Calamagrostis villosa is a species of flowering plant from the Poaceae family which is native to Europe .
The Ozark big - eared bat is the largest and reddest of the five subspecies of Corynorhinus townsendii and is medium - sized and weighs from 0.2 to 0.5 ounces .
Ground spiders ( family Gnaphosidae ) include nearly 2,000 described species in over 100 genera , distributed worldwide .
Halocarpus bidwillii ( Bog Pine or Mountain Pine ) is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae .
Argyrochosma nivea is an Andean fern species in the genus Argyrochosma .
Catalepidia is a genus of a sole described species of medium - sized trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Joffrichthys is a genus of prehistoric bony fish .
Acrobasis palliolella , the mantled acrobasis moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Acrobasis .
Timbellus phyllopterus , common name : the Leafy Winged Murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Rudolfiella aurantiaca is a species of orchid occurring from Trinidad to tropical South America .
Acacia stictophylla , also known as Dandenong Range cinnamon wattle , is a species of Acacia that is endemic to Victoria , Australia .
Hemerocallis hongdoensis , common name Hongdo Island day - lily or ( in Korean ) hongdo - wonch'uri , is a plant species native to a group of small islands in the Yellow Sea , off the southwest coast of South Korea .
Colobodesmus crucis is a species of millipede in the family Sphaeriodesmidae that is endemic to San Vito , Costa Rica , where it was first discovered on 17 - -18 April 1972 by Harold F. Loomis .
Conus thomae , common name St. Thomas cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Chrysanthia viridissima is a species of beetles belonging to the family Oedemeridae subfamily Nacerdinae .
Cup orchids ( genus Brachionidium ) are a group of about 72 species of orchids , found throughout much of tropical America ( Central America , the West Indies , and South America as far south as Brazil and Bolivia ) .
Onchocerca is a genus of parasitic roundworm .
Physa fontinalis , common name the common bladder snail , is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Physidae .
Rhododendron erosum ( 啮蚀杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to eastern Bhutan , southern Tibet , and southern Xizang , China , where it grows at altitudes of 3000 - -3700 meters .
Campylobacter ( meaning `` curved bacteria '' ) is a genus of Gram - negative , microaerophilic , oxidase - positive , catalase - positive , nonfermentative bacteria .
Croton hancei Benth . , the Hong Kong croton , is a shrub or small tree , a species of Croton which is endemic to Tsing Yi Island , Hong Kong .
Hypericum cumulicola is a rare species of flowering plant in the St. John 's wort genus known by the common name highlands scrub hypericum , or highlands scrub St. John 's wort .
The Pettalidae are a family of harvestmen with 52 described species and subspecies in eleven genera .
Pogogyne is a small genus of flowering plants in the mint family known generally as mesamints or mesa mints .
Oecomys rutilus , also known as the reddish oecomys or red arboreal rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Oecomys of family Cricetidae .
Pseudocoris is a genus of wrasses native to the eastern Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Oligodon pseudotaeniatus , commonly known as the false striped kukri snake , is a species of colubrid snake .
Artocarpus integer , commonly known as cempedak ( pronounced `` chem - pe - dak '' ) , is a species of tree in the family Moraceae , and in the same genus as breadfruit and jackfruit .
Dorcadiopsis planipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Dorcadiopsis .
Oxalis incarnata is a species of flowering plant in the woodsorrel family known by the common names pale pink - sorrel and crimson woodsorrel .
Alopecosa reimoseri is a wolf spider species in the genus Alopecosa found in Hungary .
Tropidothorax leucopterus is a species of ground bugs belonging to the family Lygaeidae , subfamily Lygaeinae .
Zealanapis australis is a spider species in the genus Zealanapis found in New Zealand .
Entemnotrochus adansonianus , common name Adanson 's slit shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pleurotomariidae .
Wallenia is a genus of plant in the family Primulaceae .
Platycheirus rosarum is a species of hoverfly found in many parts of Britain and Europe .
The Bornean black magpie is a distinctive subspecies of the black magpie which is sometimes considered a full species , Platysmurus aterrimus .
Ozoroa namaquensis ( Gariep resin tree , Afrikaans : Gariep - harpuisboom ) is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Cryptoplax iredalei , the Iredale 's fleshy - chiton , is a species of chiton in the cryptoplax genus .
Gagea alberti is an Asian species of plants in the lily family , native to Kazakhstan , Kyrgyzstan and Xinjiang Province of western China .
Gastrotheca fissipes ( common name : Igaracu marsupial frog ) is a frog species in the frog family Hemiphractidae .
Curetis dentata , the toothed sunbeam , is a species of lycaenid or blue butterfly found in Asia .
Talaromyces atroroseus is a species of fungus described as new to science in 2013 .
Agave guadalajarana is a smallish Agave species endemic to Mexico .
Leptothorax muscorum is a species of ant of the genus Leptothorax that ranges through a variety of habitats throughout much of Europe , northern Asia , and North and Central America , with a particularly wide distribution in the palearctic .
Discreliotia serrata is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Tornidae .
Dorisa is a genus of parasitic protozoa in the phylum Apicomplexa .
Polyachyrus is a genus of South American plants in the gerbera tribe within the daisy family .
Subulina striatella is a species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae .
Pseudoperonospora is a genus of water moulds which includes several species known for causing downy mildew infections on plants .
Cremastra appendiculata is an orchid species in the genus Cremastra .
Onychoteuthis compacta is a species of squid in the family Onychoteuthidae , known to occur in Hawaiian waters .
Sericostola rhodanopa is a species of sedge moths in the genus Sericostola .
Idiostatus middlekaufi is an insect , one of many species of katydids in the family Tettigoniidae .
Cerastium aleuticum , common name Aleutian mouse - ear chickweed , is a plant species endemic to the US State of Alaska .
Tilesina gibbosa is a species of poacher native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean .
Lucilia mexicana is a species of green bottle blow fly of the family Calliphoridae .
Buddleja chenopodiifolia is a species endemic to the dry rocky or clay hillsides of southern Peru at altitudes of 2200 - -3100 m ; it was first described and named by Kraenzlin in 1913 .
Ruta graveolens , commonly known as rue , common rue or herb - of - grace , is a species of Ruta grown as an ornamental plant and as an herb .
Penstemon azureus is a species of penstemon known by the common name azure penstemon .
Pomacea bridgesii , common names the spike - topped apple snail or mystery snail , is a South American species of freshwater snail with gills and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae .
Listeria monocytogenes is the species of pathogenic bacteria that causes the infection listeriosis .
Cullenia is a genus of flowering plants native to India and Sri Lanka .
Epipleoneura lamina is a species of damselfly in the threadtail family ( Protoneuridae ) .
Polytrichum is a genus of mosses -- commonly called haircap moss or hair moss -- which contains approximately 70 species that cover a cosmopolitan distribution .
Bactris gasipaes is a species of palm native to the tropical forests of South and Central America .
Ichthyococcus australis is a species of the genus Ichthyococcus .
Giesbertiolus linnaei is a species of scarab beetle belonging to the Cetoniidae subfamily .
Nyctibatrachus minor is a species of frog in the Nyctibatrachidae family endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
Centrolene is a genus of glass frogs in the family Centrolenidae .
Helladia imperialis is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily that is endemic to Iran .
Acropora echinata is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by Dana in 1846 .
Eusthenica treicleiota is a species of moth in the Cossidae family and the only species in the genus Eusthenica .
Callopsis is a monotypic genus from the plant family Araceae and has only one species , Callopsis volkensii .
Lysimachia quadrifolia , the whorled loosestrife , whorled yellow loosestrife , or crosswort , is a species of herbaceous plant in the family Primulaceae .
Achariaceae is a family of flowering plants , formerly consisting of 6 species and 3 genera of herbs and shrubs endemic to southern Africa .
Nerioidea is a superfamily of Acalyptratae flies .
Semilimax pyrenaicus is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vitrinidae .
Olearia myrsinoides , commonly known as Silky Daisy - bush , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae .
Dactylostelma is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1895 .
Myrmeparmena sudrei is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Myrmeparmena .
Atrilinea is a genus of cyprinid fishes that contains only three species , all of which are endemic to China .
Myrcia margarettae is a species of shrub in the family Myrtaceae .
Callicarpa erioclona is a species of beautyberry native to Vietnam , Borneo , Sulawesi , Java , Philippines , New Guinea , and the Bismarck Archipelago .
Sartwellia is a genus of North American flowering plants in the marigold tribe within the daisy family .
Calyptraea chinensis , common name the Chinese hat snail or Chinese hat shell , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calyptraeidae , the slipper snails or slipper limpets , cup - and - saucer snails , and Chinese hat snails .
Adetomyrma cassis ( from Latin cassis , `` helm '' , referring to the shape of its genital capsule ) is a species of ant endemic to Madagascar .
Orycteropodidae is a family of Afrotherian mammals .
Iskandaria is a genus of stone loaches native to central Asia .
Dawkinsia tambraparniei is a species of cyprinid fish found in the Tambraparni River basin in the Western Ghats , Tamil Nadu , India .
Histoplasma is a genus of dimorphic fungi commonly found in bird and bat fecal material .
Ludwigia murchisonae is an extinct species of ammonites in the family Graphoceratidae , which lived during the Mid Jurassic , Aalenian age ( 170.3 - -174.1 mya ) .
Echeveria runyonii is a species of flowering plant in the sedum family , Crassulaceae , that is native to the state of Tamaulipas in Mexico .
Streptostele musaecola is a species of small air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Streptaxidae .
Thermodesulforhabdus norvegica is a species of thermophilic sulfate - reducing bacteria , the type and only species of its genus .
Dermophis occidentalis is a species of amphibian in the Dermophiidae family , endemic to Costa Rica .
Acanthosphex leurynnis , the Wasp - spine velvetfish , is a species of velvetfish native to the Indo - Pacific from India to the Gulf of Thailand .
Ulva linza Linnaeus is a green alga in the division Chlorophyta , is the type species of the genus Ulva that can be found in British Isles .
Xanthosoma sagittifolium , the arrowleaf elephant ear or arrowleaf elephant 's ear , is a species of tropical flowering plant in the genus Xanthosoma , which produces an edible , starchy corm .
Luzula acuminata , hairy woodrush , is a species of perennial plant in Juncaceae family that grows in northeastern United States and Canada .
Stephanolepis hispidus , the planehead filefish , is a species of bony fish , a ray - finned fish in the family Monacanthidae .
The Reduviidae are a large cosmopolitan family of the order Hemiptera ( true bugs ) .
Bellis annua or the annual daisy is a species of the genus Bellis .
Caymanostellidae is a family of sea stars containing six species in two families .
Fibramia thermalis , also known as the Half - barred cardinal is a species of cardinalfishes found in Indian Ocean and Pacific Ocean .
Speokokosia corneti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Speokokosia .
Pyrrhura is a genus of parrots in the Arini tribe .
Zapalasaurus is a genus of dinosaur described by Leonardo Salgado , Ismar de Souza Carvalho and Alberto C. It was named after the city of Zapala .
Euphorbia ocellata is a species of euphorb known by the common name Contura Creek sandmat .
Triphasia grandifolia or unifoliate limeberry is a species of the genus Triphasia which is closely related to the genus Citrus and according to some should be including in it .
Odontoglossum cruentum , the Blood - red Odontoglossum , is a species of orchid found from Ecuador to Peru .
Callobatrachus is an extinct genus of discoglossoid anuran amphibian from the Early Cretaceous - age Yixian Formation of Liaoning , China .
Amalda mucronata is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Olividae , the olives .
Leptauchenia is an extinct goat - like genus of terrestrial herbivore belonging to the oreodont family Merycoidodontidae , and the type genus of the tribe Leptaucheniini .
The Mongu shovelnose frog , Hemisus barotseensis , is a species of frog in the Hemisotidae family , endemic to Zambia .
It is known from a single species , the type species Hamipterus tianshanensis .
Standfussiana sturanyi is a species of owlet moth in the genus Standfussiana .
Lehua mamo or ' ohi'a ( Metrosideros macropus ) , is a species of tree in the eucalyptus family , Myrtaceae .
Anadema macandrewii is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae ,
Lipocrea epeiroides is an orb - weaving spider species found in Greece , Cyprus , Turkey , Israel , Yemen and India .
Pritchardia napaliensis is a species of palm tree that is endemic to the island of Kauaʻi in Hawaii , United States .
Neoheterophrictus sahyadri is a species in the genus Neoheterophrictus .
Salix alaxensis is a species of flowering plant in the willow family known by the common names Alaska willow and feltleaf willow .
Acrocomia media is a species of palm which is native to Puerto Rico and the Virgin Islands .
Horkelia daucifolia is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name carrotleaf horkelia .
Ephemera danica is a species of mayfly in the genus Ephemera .
Trioceros is a genus of lizards in the family Chamaeleonidae .
Pituriaspis doylei ( Doyle 's pituri shield ) was one of two known species of jawless fish belonging to the Class Pituriaspida , and is the better known of the two .
Carex acutiformis , the lesser pond - sedge , is a species of sedge .
Marigordiella parviginella is the only species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the genus Marigordiella ; family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Melica rigida is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that can be found in Argentina , Brazil ( Santa Catarina , Rio Grande do Sul ) , and Uruguay .
Hemisodorcus arrowi is a species of beetle in the family Lucanidae .
It contains the single species Geocarpon minimum , which is known by the common names tinytim and earth - fruit .
Mathildidae is a family of minute sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the informal group of the Lower Heterobranchia .
Pomacea glauca is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Ampullariidae , the apple snails .
Powichthys is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Devonian period .
Petermannia cirrosa , the only species in the genus , is endemic to the states of New South Wales and Queensland in Australia .
Lymantriini ( sometimes misspelled as Lymantrini ) is a tribe of moths of the Erebidae family .
Stenocorus schaumii is a species of beetle from Cerambycidae family that is 17 - -29 millimetres ( 0.67 - -1.14 in ) .
Proceratosaurus is a genus of small - sized ( ~3 metres ( 9.8 ft ) long ) carnivorous theropod dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic ( Bathonian ) of England .
Passiflora racemosa ( red passion flower ) is a species of flowering plant in the Passifloraceae family , native to Brazil .
Labidura riparia is a species of earwig in the family Labiduridae , formerly Forficula riparia , characterized by their modified cerci as forceps , and light tan colour .
Lethrinops altus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it occurs in areas with sandy substrates .
Pachypanchax varatraza is a species of Aplocheilid killifish endemic to Madagascar where it is found in the Menambery , Fanambana and Ampanobe rivers .
Senna occidentalis is a pantropical plant species .
Centruroides elegans is a scorpion species in the genus Centruroides found in Mexico .
The Andaman shama ( Copsychus albiventris ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Myiotrixini is a tribe of flies in the family Tachinidae from Australia .
Nasturtium gambellii ( syn . Rorippa gambellii ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names Gambel 's yellowcress and Gambel 's watercress .
Pteriidae , also called the feather oysters , is a family of medium - sized to large saltwater clams .
Conus miles , common name the soldier cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Idelinellidae is a family of fossil cockroach - like insects .
Pinus driftwoodensis is an extinct species of conifer in the pine family solely known from early Eocene sediments exposed in south central British Columbia .
Ceratonykus ( meaning ' horned claw ' ) is a genus of alvarezsaurid theropod dinosaur that existed in the late Cretaceous period .
Pyronema is a genus of fungi in the family Pyronemataceae .
Lynchius nebulanastes ( common name : Canchaque Andes frog ) is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family .
Daonella is a genus of oyster - like saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks which lived in the middle to late Triassic period .
Myrmecia loweryi is a species of the giant bull ant which is abundant to Australia .
Digitaria didactyla is a species of grass known by the common names blue couch , Queensland blue couch , blue serangoon grass , green serangoon grass , blue stargrass , and petit gazon ( in Mauritius ) .
Hypselospinus is a genus of iguanodontian dinosaur which was first described as a species of Iguanodon ( I. fittoni ) by Richard Lydekker in 1889 , the specific name honouring William Henry Fitton .
Haplochromis rufus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria where it is found over rocky substrates in the southern portion of the lake .
Gaillardiella is a genus of fungi within the Bertiaceae family .
Cayratia trifolia is a species of liana plant native to Australia and Asia .
Dipsacus laciniatus is a species of flowering plant in the honeysuckle family known by the common name cutleaf teasel .
Pseudaphya ferreri , Ferrer 's goby , is a species of goby native to the Mediterranean Sea where it occurs in inshore waters inhabiting areas with sandy substrates .
Helonias bullata ( swamp pink ) is a rare perennial rhizomatous herb native to the eastern United States , the only known species in the genus Helonias .
Cryptosporidium hominis , along with Cryptosporidium parvum , is among the medically important Cryptosporidium species .
Chaenactis nevii is a North American species of flowering plants in the aster family known by the common name John Day pincushion .
Hysterographium is a genus of fungi of uncertain placement in the class Dothideomycetes .
Plaumanniella novateutoniae is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Plaumanniella .
Coronella austriaca ( commonly known as a smooth snake ) is a non - venomous colubrid species found in northern and central Europe , but also as far east as northern Iran .
Xenohyla is a genus of frog in the Hylidae family , and are found in the Brazilian states of Bahia and Rio de Janeiro .
Euophrys omnisuperstes ( the species name means standing above everything ) , the himalayan jumping spider , is a small jumping spider that lives at elevations of up to 6,700 metres ( 22,000 feet ) on Mount Everest , making it a candidate for the highest known permanent resident on Earth .
Pamianthe is a genus of South American bulbous perennials in the Amaryllis family , subfamily Amaryllidoideae .
Uramya pristis is a species of fly in the genus Uramya of the family Tachinidae that can be found in eastern North America .
Calathus glabricollis is a species of ground beetle from the Platyninae subfamily that can be found in Bulgaria , Greece , Italy and all states of former Yugoslavia .
Adriopea pallidata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Adriopea .
Brachaspis robustus is an endangered protected species of grasshopper from South Island , New Zealand .
Dactylopus kuiteri , known commonly as the Kuiter 's dragonet , is a species of marine fish in the family Callionymidae .
Amblydoras bolivarensis is a species of thorny catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Orinoco River basin .
Brickellia diffusa is a Latin American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Dorosoma is a genus of gizzard shads , fish of the herring family Clupeidae .
Ehrharta erecta is a species of grass commonly known as panic veldtgrass .
Novomessor is a genus of ants that was described by Italian entomologist Carlo Emery in 1915 .
Hydrophyllum is a genus of flowering plants in the waterleaf family which includes several herbaceous perennials native to North America .
Atelopus chrysocorallus is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae endemic to Venezuela .
Overbeckia is a genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae containing the single species Overbeckia subclavata .
Sweta is a genus of leafhopper in the subfamily Typhlocybinae , with two .
Haliotis virginea , Virgin Paua , is a species of edible sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Neurolaena is a genus of flowering plants in the Neurolaena tribe within the daisy family .
Radix luteola is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Lymnaeidae .
Uliodon is a genus of spiders found in New Zealand and possibly Australia .
Dipterocarpus semivestitus is a species of tree in the family Dipterocarpaceae , occurring in Kalimantan and peninsular Malaysia .
Olearia astroloba , commonly known as Marble Daisy - bush , is a rare shrub species in the family Asteraceae .
Longitarsus eminus is a species of beetle from Chrysomelidae family that can be found in Asian countries such as Afghanistan , Iran , Iraq , Israel , and Turkey .
Chorisandrachne , is a genus of plants in the flowering plant family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1969 .
Trifolium breweri is mentioned briefly as being basal within the Involucrarium clade with some of the South American species that were studied .
Anaklinoceras is a genus of extinct heteromorph ammonite cephalopod that lived in marine environments in what is now Western North America during the Campanian division of the Cretaceous period .
The parrot family Psittrichasiidae consists of two subfamilies , the Psittrichasinae and Coracopsinae , which are found on New Guinea and the Indian Ocean Islands , respectively .
Botiidae is a family of cypriniform ray - finned fishes from South , Southeast , and East Asia .
Suillus bovinus was one of the many species first described in 1753 by the `` father of taxonomy '' Carl Linnaeus , who , in the second volume of his Species Plantarum , gave it the name Boletus bovinus .
Orthotylus adenocarpi adenocarpi is a subspecies of bug from the Miridae family that can be found in Benelux , Czech Republic , Denmark , France , Germany , Great Britain , Ireland , Poland , Spain , and Sweden .
Eisenia fetida ( older spelling : foetida ) , known under various common names such as redworm , brandling worm , panfish worm , trout worm , tiger worm , red wiggler worm , red californian earth worm , etc . , is a species of earthworm adapted to decaying organic material .
Actinodoria cuprea is a species of tachinid flies in the genus Actinodoria of the family Tachinidae .
Carabus lopatini is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that is endemic to Sakhalin , Russia .
Sphaeralcea grossulariifolia is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name gooseberryleaf globemallow .
Marinobacter hydrocarbonoclasticus is a species of Proteobacteria found in sea water which are able to degrade hydrocarbons .
Paravespa is an afrotropical and palearctic genus of potter wasps .
The Bambaradeniya 's shrub frog , ( Pseudophilautus bambaradeniyai ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family , endemic to Sri Lanka .
The remainder of this article discusses the disease - causing Parvoviridae viri , rather than the members of the Parvovirus genus .
Bornella stellifer is a species of colorful sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bornellidae .
The blue king crab , Paralithodes platypus , is a species of king crab which lives near St. Matthew Island , the Pribilof Islands , and the Diomede Islands , Alaska , with further populations along the coasts of Japan and Russia .
Dugesia tubqalis is a species of dugesiid triclad that inhabits springs of Morocco , Africa .
Geoplaninae is a subfamily of land planarians endemic to the Neotropical region .
Graphosoma lineatum is a species of shield bug in the family Pentatomidae .
Eccritotarsus catarinensis is a species of plant bug from Santa Catarina , Brazil .

Iris aucheri ( Aucher - Éloy iris ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Iridaceae .
Hypargyria metalliferella , the silvered knothorn , is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypargyria .
Rhododendron goodenoughii is a rhododendron species native to Papua New Guinea , particularly Goodenough Island where it grows at altitudes of 800 - 1500 m. It is a shrub or small tree that grows to 2 m in height , with leaves that are broadly elliptic , 10 × 6 cm in size .
Thelesperma megapotamicum is a perennial species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Hopi tea greenthread and rayless greenthread .
Aromobates haydeeae ( common name : El Vivero rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Aromobatidae family .
Malpolon monspessulanus , commonly known as the Montpellier snake , is a species of mildly venomous rear - fanged colubrids .
Cyrtodactylus intermedius , also known as intermediate bow - fingered gecko or Cardamon forest gecko , is a species of gecko found in Cambodia , Vietnam , and Thailand , including several national parks ( Khao Yai National Park , Khao Khitchakut National Park , Khao Soi Dao Wildlife Sanctuary and Mu Ko Chang National Park ) .
Ixia polystachya ( white - and - yellow - flower cornlily ) is an Ixia species found on hills and slopes of northwest and southwest Cape , South Africa .
Cladonia asahinae ( commonly known as the pixie cup lichen ) is a species of lichen in the family Cladoniaceae .
Caucasichthys is an extinct genus of perciform bony fish which existed in Russia during the middle Eocene epoch ( Bartonian age ) .
Ctenolepisma is a genus of primitive insects ( order Zygentoma = Thysanura s.s . )
Naucleopsis is a plant genus in family Moraceae .
Crenatocetus ( from Latin : crena , `` notch '' , and cetus , `` whale '' ) is an extinct genus of protocetid early whale containing one species , Crenatocetus rayi , that lived along the Atlantic Coastal Plain of the United States during the Lutetian in the late middle Eocene .
Cassipourea eketensis is a species of plant in the Rhizophoraceae family .
Mayriella is an Indo - Australian genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Gayophytum humile is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name dwarf groundsmoke .
Menatalligator is an extinct genus of alligatorid crocodilian .
Garrya congdonii , Congdon silktassel or chaparral silktassel , a fairly common evergreen shrub native to the northern California Coast Ranges , is one of a small biological family of approximately twenty known species in the family Garryaceae , most of which are Garrya .
Lonicera maackii ( Overgrowing Choke - plant or Amur honeysuckle ) is a species of honeysuckle in the family Caprifoliaceae , native to temperate Asia in northern and western China ( south to Yunnan ) , Mongolia , Japan ( central and northern Honshū , rare ) , Korea , and southeastern Russia ( Primorsky Krai ) .
Cardamine douglassii is listed as an endangered species by the Commonwealth of Massachusetts , and as a species of special concern by the State of Connecticut .
Pleomele forbesii , Waianae Range hala pepe or Forbes ' dracaena , is a species of flowering plant that is endemic to the island of Oʻahu in Hawaiʻi .
Spaniblennius clandestinus is a species of combtooth blenny found in the eastern central Atlantic Ocean , from Cape Verde to Angola .
Prethopalpus is a spider genus known as Goblin Spiders and are found in the Australasian tropics , including Nepal , India , Indonesia , Papua New Guinea and Australia .
Eleutherodactylus probolaeus is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the La Romana Province , Dominican Republic , at elevations of 0 - -60 m ( 0 - -197 ft ) asl .
Stromatopelminae are a subfamily of tarantulas native to West Africa and part of Central Africa .
Scaphyglottis bidentata is a species of orchid found in the American Tropics from Costa Rica to northern Brazil .
Cymopterus purpurascens is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name widewing springparsley .
Phenacolimax major is a European species of small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Vitrinidae .
Sydaphera spengleriana , the Spengler 's Nutmeg , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Paullinia pinnata is a flowering plant species in the genus of Paullinia found in South America and Africa .
Castilleja lasiorhyncha is a species of Indian paintbrush is endemic to southern California known by the common name San Bernardino Mountains Indian paintbrush .
Denisonia is a genus of venomous snakes endemic to Australia .
Amphisbaena camura , also known as the collared amphisbaenid , is a worm lizard species in the genus Amphisbaena .
Tetronarce is a genus of rays , commonly known as electric rays .
Quercus martinezii is a Mexican species of tree in the beech famiy .
Perideridia bacigalupii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common names Mother Lode yampah and Bacigalupi 's perideridia .
Paragalaxias is a genus of freshwater fish of the family Galaxiidae , endemic to Tasmania , Australia .
Cylindropuntia echinocarpa is a species of cactus known by the common names silver cholla , golden cholla , and Wiggins ' cholla .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Criserosphaeria phyllostictoides .
Cichorium pumilum ( Wild Endive ) is a Mediterranean species of plant in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Cheilanthes ( lip ferns ) is a genus of about 180 species of rock - dwelling ferns with a cosmopolitan distribution in warm , dry , rocky regions , often growing in small crevices high up on cliffs .
Allium antiatlanticum is a plant species native to Morocco and Algeria .
Podanotum is a Neotropical genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . All the species except Podanotum salaeides ( Draudt , 1919 ) are recently described .
Anomalodesmata is an order of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs .
Nothobaccharis is a genus of Peruvian flowering plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Allium feinbergii is a species of onions found on Mount Hermon , near where the three nations of Israel , Syria , and Lebanon meet .
Plesiohadros is an extinct genus of basal hadrosauroid dinosaur .
Amphiesma andreae , commonly known as Andrea 's keelback , is a species of nonvenomous colubrid snake endemic to Southeast Asia .
Limnohabitans is a genus of Proteobacteria established by Hahn et al .
Rhinoptera is a genus of ray commonly known as the cownose rays .
Lagostomus crassus is an extinct species of chinchilla that was native to Peru .
The Diogenidae are a family of hermit crabs , sometimes known as `` left - handed hermit crabs '' because in contrast to most other hermit crabs , its left chela ( claw ) is enlarged instead of the right .
Callizzia is a genus of scoopwing moths of the Uraniidae family .
Procambarus attiguus , known as the Silver Glen Springs crayfish is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Oligoryzomys chacoensis , also known as the Chacoan colilargo or Chacoan pygmy rice rat , is a rodent species from South America .
Tahina spectabilis , the tahina palm , is a species of gigantic palm that is found only in the Analalava District of northwestern Madagascar .
Climacoporus navalis , the Fleet klipfish , is a species of clinid found in subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean along the coast of South Africa where it can be found in tide pools .
Omocestus rufipes , the ' Woodland Grasshopper ' , is a species of ' short - horned grasshoppers ' belonging to the family Acrididae subfamily Gomphocerinae .
Melica mutica , twoflower melicgrass , is a grass species in the Poaceae family that can be found in southeastern United States .
Saururaceae is a plant family comprising four genera and seven species of herbaceous flowering plants native to eastern and southern Asia and North America .
Herina gyrans is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in Croatia , Spain , and Algeria .
Graptopsaltria is a genus of cicadas from East Asia .
Hibolithes is a genus of belemnite that lived from the Middle Jurassic to the Early Cretaceous , and has been found in Antarctica , Europe , South America , and New Zealand .
Petasina bielzi is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae .
Paraschistura cristata also known as the Turkmenian crested loach is a species of stone loach found only in Turkmenistan , Iran and Afghanistan in Central Asia .
Potentilla drummondii is a species of cinquefoil known by the common name Drummond 's cinquefoil .
Primula scotica , commonly known as Scottish primrose , is a species of primrose that is endemic to the north coast of Scotland , including Sutherland , Caithness and Orkney .
Volvopluteus is a genus of small to medium - sized or big saprotrophic mushrooms growing worldwide .
Right whale dolphins are cetaceans belonging to the genus Lissodelphis .
Bariamyrma ( from `` Baria '' , name of a river ; Latin hispidula , diminutive for `` hairy , bristly '' ) is a genus of ants in the subfamily Myrmicinae containing the single species Bariamyrma hispidula .
The falcons and caracaras are around 60 species of diurnal birds of prey that make up the family Falconidae .
Phyllonoma is a genus consisting of 4 species of trees and shrubs .
Musa gracilis is a species of wild banana ( genus Musa ) , native to Peninsular Malaysia .
Cicindela lepida is a species of threatened tiger beetle .
Garra phillipsi , or the Philipps ' garra , is a species of freshwater fish ) in the Cyprinidae family .
Aphrophora alni , the ' European Alder Spittle Bug ' , is a species belonging to the family Aphrophoridae .
Syrnolopsis minuta is a species of medium - sized freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Paludomidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Dyrithiopsis lakefuxianensis .
Uapou is a genus of linyphiid spiders with one species that occurs only Ua Pou , one of the Marquesas Islands .
Profundiconus smirna , common name the Smirna cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Hosta kiyosumiensis is a species of Hosta , found in Japan from Kanto south to Chubu and Kansai , and encompassing the entire central part of Honshu .
Asterophrys is a small genus of microhylid frogs with only two species from New Guinea .
Canistrum pickelii is a species in the genus Canistrum .
Camptorrhiza is a genus of plants native to India and southern Africa .
Hygrohypnum styriacum , commonly known as snow brook - moss or hygrohypnum moss is a species of moss found in the Northern Hemisphere .
Bodonida is an order of kinetoplastid flagellate protozoa .
Crossoloricaria venezuelae is a species of armored catfish found in the Lake Maracaibo drainage of Venezuela and Colombia .
Cayratia mollissima is an evergreen species of climber plant found in Indochina , Malaysia and the Philippines .
Haliastur is a genus of medium - sized diurnal birds of prey .
Crangonyx hobbsi is a species of troglobitic amphipod in the family Crangonyctidae .
Deuterosaurus is a genus of dinocephalian therapsid , one of the nonmammalian synapsids dominating the land during the late Palaeozoic .
Salmo aphelios is a species of trout , a salmonid fish endemic to Lake Ohrid in Macedonia and Albania in the Balkans .
Dromiceiomimus is a genus of ornithomimid theropod from the Late Cretaceous ( early Maastrichtian ) of Alberta , Canada .
Colletteichthys dussumieri is a species of toadfish of the Batrachoididae family .
Zachrysia trinitaria is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Camaenidae or Pleurodontidae .
Aculepeira ceropegia , the oak spider , is an orb - weaving spider species with Palearctic distribution .
Pleiospilos simulans ( liver plant , split rock plant ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Aizoaceae , once endemic to the Eastern Cape of South Africa .
Pachyaena ( literally , `` Thick Hyena '' ) was a genus of heavily built , relatively short - legged mesonychids that originated from Asia and spread to North America .
Psilocerea wintreberti is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Bombus vagans is a common species of bumblebee with a medium - length tongue .
Rivea is a genus of plants in family Convolvulaceae .
†Partula dolichostoma was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Puentemys is an extinct genus of bothremydid turtle from the Paleocene - age Cerrejón Formation in Colombia .
Pedicularis verticillata , the whorled lousewort , is a species of flowering plant from the order of Lamiales which can be found in Alaska , North - Western Canada , and everywhere in China at the elevation of 2,100 - -4,400 metres ( 6,900 - -14,400 ft ) .
Discocotyle sagittata is the freshwater monogenean gill ectoparasite of Salmo and Oncorhynchus fish species .
Brachinus angustatus is a species of ground beetle from the Carabinae subfamily that can be found in Spain and North African countries such as Algeria and Morocco .
Cichla monoculus , sometimes known as the tucanare peacock bass ( `` peacock bass '' is also used for some of its relatives ) , is a very large species of cichlid , and a prized game fish .
Trigonospila is a small genus of true flies in the family Tachinidae .
The genus Mimetodon was named by Jepsen G.L. in 1940 .
Rivetina asiatica is a species of praying mantis in the genus Rivetina , native to Western Asia .
Crataegus arcana , the Carolina Hawthorn , is a rare and poorly known species of hawthorn in the rose family .
Harpactes is a genus of birds in the Trogonidae family found in forests in South and Southeast Asia , extending into southernmost China .
Asparagus racemosus ( satavar , shatavari , or shatamull ) is a species of asparagus common throughout Nepal , Sri Lanka , India and the Himalayas .
Haematopota bigoti is a species of fly in the horse - fly family that can be found in such European countries as Austria , Croatia , Denmark , Hungary , Italy , Montenegro , Poland , Portugal , Romania , Slovakia , Spain , and the Netherlands .
The Sillaginidae , commonly known as the smelt - whitings , whitings , sillaginids , sand borers and sand - smelts , are a family of benthic coastal marine fish in the order Perciformes .
Carinostoma elegans is an harvestmen species in the genus Carinostoma found in Hungary .
Nardophyllum is a genus of South American flowering plants in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
It contains the single species Palaeoagaracites antiquus .
Rhadinesthes decimus , the Slender snaggletooth , is a species of barbeled dragonfish found in the ocean depths reaching to 4,900 metres ( 16,100 ft ) .
Carayonemidae is a family of scale insects commonly known as carayonemids .
Carex sodiroi is a species of sedge known from a single collection made by Luis Sodiro at some time before 1886 .
Eucalyptus nitens , commonly known as shining gum , is a Eucalypt species native to Victoria and eastern New South Wales , Australia .
Adelphotectonica reevei is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Architectonicidae , known as the staircase shells or sundials .
Xyris brevifolia , the shortleaf yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Lasthenia , commonly known as goldfields , is a genus of the botanical family Asteraceae .
Discus textilis is an extinct species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Discidae , the disk snails .
Macrotritopus defilippi , commonly known as the Lilliput longarm octopus or the Atlantic longarm octopus , is a small species of octopus , a marine cephalopod mollusc of the order Octopoda .
The family Polychelidae contains thirty - eight extant species of blind , benthic lobster - like crustaceans .
Psammophis angolensis , sometimes known as the dwarf sand snake , is a species of snake in the family Lamprophiidae reaching a maximum length of 50 cm , but averaging 30 cm . The snake actively forages for lizards and frogs .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Lobosporangium transversale , found in the USA and Mexico .
Mirognathus normani , Norman 's Smooth - head , is a species of slickhead native to the north - east and western Atlantic Ocean .
Suzanniwana is an extinct genus of iguanian lizards that lived in western North America during the earliest Eocene , approximately 56 million years ago .
Pseudophoenix vinifera ( Cacheo , Katié ) is a palm species endemic to Hispaniola .
Chionanthus albidiflorus ( syn . Linociera albidiflora ( Thwaites ) C.B.Clarke ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Oleaceae .
Acousmaticus magnicornis is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Acousmaticus .
Isolepis is a cosmopolitan genus of sedge containing around 70 species .
Chalcosoma is a genus of Southeast Asian rhinoceros beetles , comprising three species :
†Partula dolorosa was a species of air - breathing tropical land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Partulidae .
Rhynchostylis coelestis is a species of orchid endemic to Indochina .
Bateidae is a family of amphipod crustaceans , comprising the single genus Batea , which in turn contains thirteen species :
Lophiaspis is an extinct genus of chalicothere endemic to Europe during the Eocene living from 55.8 - -37.2 Ma and existed for approximately 18.6 million years .
Dinomenia is a genus of cavibelonian solenogaster , one kind of small , shell - less mollusk .
Magnolia obovata ( Japanese bigleaf magnolia and Japanese whitebark magnolia ) is a species of Magnolia , native to Japan and the adjacent Kurile Islands .
Theristicus is a genus of birds in the Threskiornithidae family .
Tetraponera allaborans , is a species of ant of the subfamily Myrmicinae , which can be found in many Asian countries .
The Japanese fire belly newt ( Cynops pyrrhogaster ) is a species of newt in the Salamandridae family endemic to Japan .
Plagiolabra is a neotropical genus of potter wasps currently containing 2 species found in the Gran Chaco biogeographical province of central South America .
Flexopecten hyalinus , the Hyaline Scallop , is a species of saltwater clams , a scallop , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Pholisma arenarium is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by several common names , including desert Christmas tree , scaly - stemmed sand plant , and purple sand food .
Dendrotrochus ponapensis is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Euconulidae , the hive snails . This species is endemic to Micronesia .
Diuris chryseopsis , commonly known as the Small Snake Orchid or Common Golden Moths , is a species of orchid that is endemic to south - eastern Australia .
It consists of only one species , Parasthena flexilinea , which is found on Sulawesi , the Philippines and Borneo and possibly on Seram and Papua New Guinea .
Conus guinaicus is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk .
Eriogonum davidsonii is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Davidson 's buckwheat .
Acantholycosa sayanensis is a species of wolf spider found only in the Western Sayan Mountains in Russia .
Bothrops itapetiningae , or the São Paulo lancehead , is a species of venomous snake in the Viperidae family .
Calliandra is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae , subfamily Mimosoideae .
Gilia yorkii is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names Boyden Cave gilia and monarch gilia .
Bulinus nasutus is a species of tropical freshwater snail with a sinistral shell , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails and their allies .
Jeholops is an extinct genus of notostracan which existed in the Yixian Formation , inner Mongolia , China during the early Cretaceous period ( Barremian age ) .
Dupouyichthys sapito is the only species of banjo catfishes in the genus Dupouyichthys .
Penicillium daejeonium is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from grape and schisandra fruit in Korea .
Neoparrya lithophila , also known by the common names Bill 's neoparrya and rock - loving aletes , is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family .
Diaethria euclides is a species of butterfly of the Diaethria genus .
Platymantis mamusiorum ( Nakanai wrinkled bamboo frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
Muscina levida is a species of fly from the family Muscidae .
Cressa cretica is a species of flowering plant in the morning glory family .
Villalobosius is a genus of crabs in the family Pseudothelphusidae , containing a single species , Villalobosius lopezformenti .
Mictocaris halope is the only species of freshwater crustacean in the monotypic genus Mictocaris .
Fitchia is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to certain islands in the Pacific .
Paraspinibarbus alloiopleurus is a species of cyprinid fish that is found in the eastern Asian countries of China , Laos and Vietnam .
Raphanus ( Latin for `` radish '' ) is a genus within the flowering plant family Brassicaceae .
Agyneta albomaculata is a species of sheet weaver found in the Galapagos Islands .
Galium muricatum , Humboldt bedstraw , is a species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Synodontis dhonti is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it is only known from Lake Tanganyika .
Picea glehnii , the Sakhalin spruce or Glehn 's spruce , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
The Kerguelen shag ( Phalacrocorax verrucosus ) is a species of cormorant endemic to the Kerguelen Islands in the southern Indian Ocean , one of the most isolated places on Earth .
Hypsipyla robusta , the cedar tip moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Hypsipyla .
Thelesperma filifolium , commonly known as stiff greenthread , or plains greenthread , is a species of flowering plant in the aster family , Asteraceae .
It contains the single species Lepidoneiva erubescens , which is found in Brazil ( São Paulo ) .
Seorsumuscardinus is a genus of fossil dormice from the early Miocene of Europe .
Dimetrodon ( i / daɪˈmiːtrədɒn/ ; meaning `` two measures of teeth '' ) is an extinct genus of synapsid that lived during the Early Permian period , around 295 - -272 million years ago ( Ma ) .
Lamoria adaptella , the plain lamoria , is a species of snout moth in the genus Lamoria .
Naegleria lovaniensis is a species of Naegleria .
Lycosa is a genus of wolf spiders .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Themisia nuda .
Ribes binominatum is a species of currant known by the common names trailing gooseberry and ground gooseberry .
Wynnea americana , commonly known as moose antlers or rabbit ears , is a species of fungus in the family Sarcoscyphaceae .
Marrubium peregrinum ( Horehound ) is a species of herbaceous perennial plant , with height up to 60 cm , native to south - east Europe , the Balkans , and Asia Minor .
The Arbacioida are an order of sea urchins , consisting of a single family , the Arbaciidae .
Hyastenus elatus is a species of crab in the family Epialtidae .
Dioryctria taedivorella , the lesser loblolly pineconeworm moth , is a species of snout moth in the genus Dioryctria .
Habenaria fordii is a species of plant in the Orchidaceae family .
Draconectes narinosus is a species of troglobitic stone loach known only from a cave on Van Gio Island in Halong Bay , Vietnam .
Cheiracanthium occidentale is a spider species found in Minorca .
Gammarus pecos is a species of crustacean in family Gammaridae .
Penicillium parvulum is a monoverticillate species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil of a peanut field in Georgia .
Physopsis is a genus of plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1849 .
Sepia mirabilis is a species of cuttlefish native to the western Indian Ocean .
Mycterus curculioides is a species of beetles belonging to the family Mycteridae .
Conuber sordidum ( originally described as Natica sordida by Swainson ) is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk family Naticidae , the moon snails .
Heliconius hermathena , the Hermathena Longwing , is a species of butterfly of the Nymphalidae family .
Ivesia jaegeri , is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Jaeger 's mousetail , or Jaeger 's ivesia .
Periophthalmus gracilis is a species of mudskippers native to marine and brackish waters of the eastern Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean where it is an inhabitant of the intertidal zone , capable of spending time out of water .
Tilloglomus spectabilis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Tilloglomus .
Tradescantia fluminensis is a species of spiderwort native to South America .
Amantis fumosa is a species of praying mantis native to India .
Ptychochromis insolitus , also known as the Mangarahara cichlid , is a species of cichlid endemic to certain river systems in northern Madagascar .
The Plicatulidae are a family of saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks , known commonly as kitten 's paws or kittenpaws .
Eleutherodactylus maurus ( Spanish : Rana - fisgona Café ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family .
Aphanostephus riddellii is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family , with the common name Riddell 's lazydaisy .
Ceuthophilus elegans is an insect species in the genus Ceuthophilus .
Pernagera gatliffi is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Charopidae .
Triops newberryi is a species of Triops found on the western coast of North America , commonly in valleys throughout the states of Washington , Oregon , California , and small areas of Nevada , Utah , New Mexico , and Mexico , with at least one disjunct population in Kansas .
Anemone jamesonii is a species of plant in the Ranunculaceae family .
Eriophorum vaginatum L. ( hare's - tail cottongrass , tussock cottongrass , sheathed cottonsedge ) is a species of perennial herbaceous plant in the family Cyperaceae , native to bogs and other acidic wetlands throughout the Holarctic Kingdom .
Ribeiroclinus eigenmanni is a species of clinid found along the Atlantic coast of South America from southern Brazil to central Argentina where it has been found at a depth of about 17 metres ( 56 ft ) .
Potamanthidae is a family of Mayflies ( Ephemeroptera ) with 3 genera in which there are 23 species .
Elimia macglameriana was a species of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pleuroceridae .
The Thermoactinomycetaceae are a family of Gram - positive endospore - forming bacteria .
Jorunna funebris , common name the dotted nudibranch , is a large species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusc in the family Discodorididae .
Psorospermum febrifugum is a flowering plant species in the genus Psorospermum occurring in Zimbabwe and Mozambique .
Aeshna ellioti , the highland hawker or Elliot 's hawker , is a species of dragonfly in the family Aeshnidae .
Atrocalopteryx atrata is a species of damselfly belonging to the family Calopterygidae .
Hypselodoris placida is a species of sea slug or dorid nudibranch .
Fessonia is a genus of mites belonging to the family Smaridiidae .
Balistomorphus is an extinct genus of prehistoric triggerfish that lived a marine environment during the early Oligocene epoch in what is now Canton Glarus , Switzerland .
Gaillardia coahuilensis , bandanna daisy , is a North American species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Mesoponera is an Old World genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Elachisinidae is a family of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Rissooidea and the clade Littorinimorpha .
Tropaeolum leptophyllum is a species of perennial plant in the Tropaeolaceae family .
Alternaria brassicae is a plant pathogen able to infect most Brassica species including important crops such as broccoli , cabbage and oil seed rape .
Elachistocleis ovalis ( common name : common oval frog , Spanish : sapito apuntado bicolor ) is a species of frog in the Microhylidae family .
Tolumnia guianensis is a species of orchid endemic to Hispaniola .
Oberea breviantennalis is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered in 2006 .
Eriophyllum jepsonii is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Jepson 's woolly sunflower .
Hylarana signata , commonly known as the striped stream frog , spotted stream frog , or Matang frog , is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
Thoracochromis is a fish genus of haplochromine cichlids that are endemic to Africa .
Lavandula lanata is a shrubby lavender species native to southern Spain .
Mangifera casturi ( also called Kalimantan Mango or Kasturi ) is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Calochortus spatulatus is a Mexican species of plants in the lily family .
Nososticta solitaria is an Australian species of damselfly in the family Protoneuridae , commonly known as the fivespot threadtail .
Schleinitzia fosbergii is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name strand tangantangan .
Kentiopsis magnifica ( formerly Mackeea magnifica ) is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family .
The superfamily Glypheoidea comprises five families .
Megalagrion molokaiense , common name Molokai damselfly , is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Sorex araneus grantii is a subspecies of the shrew Sorex araneus , found only on the Scottish island of Islay .
Austrocactus coxii is a plant species in the genus Austrocactus from the cactus family ( Cactaceae ) , indigenous to southern Argentina and southern Chile .
Isodendrion laurifolium is a rare species of flowering plant in the violet family known by the common names rockcliff isodendrion and aupaka .

Pediocactus bradyi is a rare species of cactus known by the common names Brady 's pincushion cactus , Brady 's hedgehog cactus , and Marble Canyon cactus .

Gastridium is a small but widespread genus of African and Eurasian plants in the grass family .
Icaronycteris is an extinct genus of microchiropteran ( echolocating ) bat that lived in the early Eocene , approximately 52.2 million years ago , making it the earliest known definitive bat .
Calyptranthes elegans , the bashy guava , bois baguette , bois petite feuille , is a flowering plant species in the genus Calyptranthes endemic to the Lesser Antilles .
Myrmeciites is an extinct form genus of bulldog ants in the subfamily Myrmeciinae of the family Formicidae , which contains three described species and two fossils not placed beyond the genus level .
Chinemesa is a little - known genus of thread - legged bug ( Emesinae ) apparently endemic to Borneo .
Anabas is a genus of climbing gouramies native to southern and eastern Asia .
Capropygia unistriata , also known as the Black - banded pygmy boxfish , is a species of deepwater boxfish found in the waters over the continental shelf off the southern coast of Australia .

Melica tibetica , is a grass species in the Poaceae family that is endemic to China and can be found in such provinces as Inner Mongolia , Qinghai , Sichuan , and Xizang .

Theledectes is an extinct genus of theledectine procolophonid parareptile from middle Triassic ( early Anisian stage ) deposits of Free State Province , South Africa .

Conus typhon , common name the typhon cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .

Orthalicidae ( orthalicid land snails ) are a family of tropical air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks are classified in the informal group Sigmurethra of the clade Stylommatophora .
