Lepidocephalichthys hasselti is a species of cobitid loach native to southeastern Asia and western Indonesia .
Craspidospermum is a monotypic genus of plant in the Apocynaceae family endemic to Madagascar .
Acanthosaura crucigera is a species of lizard commonly known as Boulenger 's pricklenape or masked horned tree lizard .
Paratomoxia agathae is a species of beetle in the Paratomoxia genus that is in the Mordellidae family .
Dendrophylax porrectus is a species of epiphytic orchid native to Mexico , El Salvador , Guatemala , Florida , Cayman Islands , Cuba , Hispaniola , Jamaica , and Puerto Rico .
The Palau fruit dove ( Ptilinopus pelewensis ) is a species of bird in the family Columbidae .
Rhinecanthus assasi is a species of fish in the family Balistidae , the triggerfishes .
Haplomastodon is an extinct genus of proboscidean endemic to South America during the Pleistocene from 1.810 Ma--11,000 years ago , living for approximately 1.789 million years .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Pubigera subvillosula .
Shastoceras is a genus of extinct ammonite cephalopod found in Lower Aptian sediments in Northern California .
Thorius pennatulus is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae and one of the smallest tetrapods , with adults reaching a length of about 15 to 21 millimetres ( 0.59 to 0.83 in ) .
Sphenorhynchia plicatella is an extinct species of brachiopods belonging to the family Prionorhynchiidae .
Galeopsis speciosa ( Large - flowered Hemp - nettle or Edmonton hempnettle ) is a species of annual herbaceous plants in the family Lamiaceae .
Cyathea callosa is a species of tree fern endemic to Luzon in the Philippines , where it grows in midmontane forest .
The Madagascan wagtail ( Motacilla flaviventris ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Adansonia kilima is a species of baobab tree native to Africa , described in 2012 .
Leptura longipennis is an extinct species , that is included to incertae sedis of the Lepturinae subfamily in long - horned beetle family .
Acanthemblemaria balanorum is a species of fish in the family Chaenopsidae known by the common names clubhead blenny and clubhead barnacle blenny .
Kaunia is a genus of South American shrubs or small trees in the sunflower family .
Hierodula is a genus of praying mantises found throughout Asia .
Naso vlamingii is a species of unicornfish in the surgeonfish family known by the common names bignose unicornfish , scibbled unicornfish , Vlaming 's unicornfish , and zebra unicornfish .
Garcinia gardneriana ( Bacupari ) is an evergreen , dioecious species of the genus Garcinia .
The Coronophorales are an order of fungi in the class Sordariomycetes .
Schindalmonotus is a genus of bristle millipede containing the sole species Schindalmonotus hystrix known from South Africa and Mozambique .
Euleia basihyalina is a species of tephritid or fruit flies in the genus Euleia of the family Tephritidae .
In areas endemic for heartwater there is likely to be use of dips against other ticks of domestic animals , such as Rhipicephalus ( Boophilus ) and Hyalomma species and this will usually contribute to control of vectors of Ehrlichia ruminantium .
Galeamopus is a genus of herbivorous diplodocid sauropod dinosaurs .
Sanagia velifera is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Sanaga River in Cameroon .
Ilbiidae is a family of marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the clade Cephalaspidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Lycus trabeatus , common name Tailed net - winged beetle , is a species of beetle belonging to the Lycidae family .
Telmatobius is a genus of frogs native to the Andean highlands in South America , where they are found in Ecuador , Peru , Bolivia , northwestern Argentina and northern Chile .
Dectobrycon armeniacus is a species of characin endemic to Peru .
Andrena lauracea is a rare bee species from the United States .
The Bembicini , or sand wasps , are a large tribe of crabronid wasps , comprising 20 genera .
Acrachne is a genus of Asian , African , and Australian plants in the grass family .
Gigantophis garstini is an extinct , giant snake which may have measured more than 10 m ( 33 ft ) , larger than any living species of snake .
The Formosan woolly horseshoe bat is a species of bat from the family Rhinolophidae .
Agapetus montanus is a species of Caddisfly .
Canthigaster axiologus is a species of marine fish in the family Tetraodontidae .
Neodihammus pici is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neodihammus .
Tamarix aphylla is the largest known species of Tamarix ( height : to 18 metres--60 ft ) .
Cochliopina compacta is a species of very small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .
Kleinella is a small genus of sea snails , pyramidellid gastropod mollusk or micromollusks .
Mephisto fraserbrunneri is a species of spikefish known from the Bay of Bengal near the Andaman Islands where it has been found at a depth of 291 metres ( 955 ft ) .
Phaulomyrma is a genus of ants in the subfamily Leptanillinae containing a single species , Phaulomyrma javana .

Cryptantha nevadensis is a species of wildflower in the borage family known by the common names Nevada catseye and Nevada forget - me - not .
Protognathosaurus ( meaning `` early jaw lizard '' ) is a genus of herbivorous dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic .
Homo is the genus that comprises the species Homo sapiens , which includes modern humans , as well as several extinct species classified as ancestral to or closely related to modern humans -- as for examples Homo habilis and Homo neanderthalensis .
The only known species is Canadanthus modestus , native to northern North America ( Alaska , Yukon , British Columbia , Alberta , Manitoba , Saskatchewan , New Brunswick , Quebec , Ontario , Washington , Oregon , Idaho , Montana , North and South Dakota , Minnesota , Wisconsin , Michigan ) .
Fimbristylis polytrichoides is a species of fimbry known by the common name rusty sedge , native to east Africa , Madagascar , China , Southeast Asia , New Guinea and Australia .
Upogebiidae is a family of mud shrimp in the order Decapoda .
Thogotovirus is a genus of enveloped RNA viruses , one of six genera in the virus family Orthomyxoviridae .
Aspergillus ( /ˌæspərˈdʒɪləs/ ) is a genus consisting of a few hundred mold species found in various climates worldwide .
Pseudosamanea cubana is a tree species in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) .
Clythraschema chabrillacii is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Clythraschema .

Hylarana montivaga ( sometimes known as Langbian Plateau frog or Chantaburi stream frog ) is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
Euryades duponchelii is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae that is found in Brazil , Argentina , Paraguay , Uruguay , and Bolivia .
Oberea auriventris is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Breuning in 1961 .
Rhodothemis lieftincki , common name Red arrow , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Hypocnemoides is a genus of passerine bird in the antbird family , Thamnophilidae .
Carex distans , commonly known as distant sedge , is a plant species in the sedge family , Cyperaceae .
Simulium is a genus of black flies , which may transmit diseases such as onchocerciasis ( river blindness ) .
Micropholcus fauroti is a cellar spider species with Pantropical distribution .
Tritylodon ( Greek for 3 cusped tooth ) was a genus of tritylodont , one of the most advanced group of cynodont therapsids .
Diuris longifolia is a species of orchid which is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Rana basaltica is an extinct species of long - legged frog from Early Miocene of China .
Graphoceras is an extinct ammonite genus included in the hildoceratacean family Graphoceratidae that lived during the Bajocian stage , Middle Jurassic in what is now Europe , north Africa , and Iran .
Nabokovia is a Neotropical genus of butterflies , named by Arthur Francis Hemming in honour of Vladimir Nabokov , who extensively studied the Polyommatinae subfamily .
Sanicula hoffmannii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the parsley family known by the common names Hoffmann 's blacksnakeroot and Hoffmann 's sanicle .
Paramphistomum cervi , the type species of genus Paramphistomum , is an parasitic flat worm belonging to the class Trematoda .
Tricyrtis latifolia , the toad lily , is an East Asian species of plants in the lily family .
Colchicum kotschyi is a species native to Iran , Iraq and Turkey .
Mastigoproctus is a genus of whip scorpions .
Astatotilapia is a genus of haplochromine cichlids from Africa , with a single species in Israel and Syria .
Phoxocephalidae is a family of small , shrimp - like crustaceans in the suborder Gammaridea described by Georg Ossian Sars in 1891 .
Zygopetalum pedicellatum , commonly known as the Mosen 's Zygopetalum , is a species of orchid native to southeastern Brazil .
Meryta is a genus in the flowering plant family Araliaceae .
Trachelipus camerani is a species of woodlouse in the genus Trachelipus belonging to the family Trachelipodidae that can be found in Italy , Greece and the former Yugoslavia .
Vaccinium scoparium is a species of huckleberry known by the common names grouse whortleberry , grouseberry , and littleleaf huckleberry .
Discoplax hirtipes is a species of terrestrial crab .
Gordonia hirtella is a species of plant in the Theaceae family .
Arthrosaura is a genus of spectacled lizards ( family Gymnophthalmidae ) .
Thescelosaurinae is a subfamily of Ornithopod Dinosaurs from the Early Cretaceous of Asia and the Late Cretaceous of North America .
Araragi is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . It is a small east Asian hairstreak genus .
Triplophysa lacustris is a species of stone loach endemic to China .
Mesochorista proavita is an extinct species of scorpionfly from the Triassic period of Queensland , Australia .
Bauhinia lunarioides is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae , native to Southwestern Texas in the United States and Northern Mexico .

The Green Rock - plant , Lithops viridis , is a species of plant in the Aizoaceae family .

Miacids are extinct primitive carnivoramorphans within the family Miacidae that lived during the Paleocene and Eocene epochs , about 62 - -33 million years ago .
The Lanai island - aster or Lanai hesperomannia ( Hesperomannia arborescens ) is a species of flowering plant in the Asteraceae family .
The Tarabundí vole ( Microtus oaxacensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Squatina squatina , the angelshark or monkfish , is a species of shark in the family Squatinidae ( known generally also as angel sharks ) , once widespread in the coastal waters of the northeastern Atlantic Ocean .
Melanalis perfusca is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Melanalis .
Habenaria distans ( hammock bog orchid ) is a species of orchid .
Ranunculus fluitans , the river water - crowfoot , is a species of buttercup .

Aristoceratoides is an extinct ammonoid genus belonging to the goniatitid family Thalassoceratidae that lived during the Middle Permian .
Opisthoteuthis californiana , also known as the flapjack octopus , is a species of octopus .
Macrocystis integrifolia is one of four species of kelp ( large brown algae ) in the genus Macrocystis which grows to about 6 metres ( 20 ft ) long .
The Stylocellidae are a family of harvestmen with about 30 described species , all of which occur from India to New Guinea .
Chionoecetes is a genus of crabs that live in the northern Pacific and Atlantic Oceans .
Annuloceras ( `` Ringed Horns '' ) is an extinct genus of ammonite cephalopod .
Margarites vahlii , common name the Vahl margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Margaritidae .
The Pholcoidea or pholcoids are a superfamily of araneomorph spiders .
Homoeosoma electellum , the American sunflower moth , is a species of moth of the family Pyralidae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Felisbertia melastomacearum .
Sphaerodactylus klauberi is a species of gecko endemic to the archipelago of Puerto Rico .
Psaronius was a Marattialean tree fern which grew to 10 m in height , and is associated with leaves of the organ genus Pecopteris and other extinct tree ferns .
Microtuban is an extinct genus of azhdarchoid pterosaur known from the Late Cretaceous of northern Lebanon .
Lepidotrigla kishinouyi is a species of fish in the sea robin family
Campanula rapunculus , common name rampion bellflower , rampion , or rover bellflower , is a species of bellflower ( Campanula ) in the family Campanulaceae .
Phyllospadix torreyi , Torrey 's surfgrass , is a plant species found along the Pacific Coasts of British Columbia , Washington , Oregon , California and Baja California ( including Guadalupe Island ) .
Strobilomyces strobilaceus , also called Strobilomyces floccopus and commonly known as old man of the woods , is a species of fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Cynthiacetus is an extinct genus of basilosaurid early whale that lived during the Upper Eocene ( Bartonian - Priabonian , 40.4 to 33.9 million years ago . )
Lepidozamia is a genus of two species of cycad , both endemic to Australia .
Indosaurus ( meaning `` Indian lizard '' ) is a genus of theropod dinosaur once living in what is now India .
Muracypraea mus , common name the mouse cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Hydrocina chaetocladia .
Wangosaurus is an extinct genus of basal pistosauroid known from the Middle Triassic ( late Ladinian stage ) Falang Formation of Xingyi in Guizhou Province , southwestern China .
Percina roanoka ( common name Roanoke darter ) is a species of darter native to Virginia , West Virginia and North Carolina in the United States .
Awaous acritosus , the Roman nose goby , is a species of goby that is native to fresh water rivers and streams of Queensland , Australia and the Laloki River drainage of New Guinea .
Hispaniachelys is an extinct genus of paracryptodire or basal testudines turtle known from southern Spain .
Tillandsia geissei is a plant species in the genus Tillandsia .
The Ogilvie Mountains collared lemming ( Dicrostonyx nunatakensis ) is a species of rodents in the family Cricetidae .
Conus sandwichensis , common name the Hawaiian cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Atomiscala islandica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tofanellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Trichodes alvearius is a species of Soldier or Checkered beetle belonging to the family Cleridae , subfamily Clerinae .
Hylotelephium is a genus of family Crassulaceae .
The Autostichinae are a subfamily of moths in the superfamily Gelechioidea .
Pyrgina umbilicata is a species of small , tropical , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Subulinidae , the `` awl snails '' .
Homalium longifolium ( locally known as petaling gajah ) is a species of plant in the Salicaceae family .
Lutzomyia is a genus of phlebotomine sand flies consisting of nearly 400 species , at least 33 of which have medical importance as vectors of human disease .
Coreopsis auriculata ( lobed tickseed or mouse - ear tickseed ) is a North American plant species of the sunflower family .
Gobiodon histrio , the Broad - barred goby , is a species of goby native to the Indian Ocean from the Red sea to the western Pacific Ocean to southern Japan , Samoa and the Great Barrier Reef .
Diplodocinae is an extinct subfamily of diplodocid sauropods that existed from the Late Jurassic to Early Cretaceous of North America , Europe and South America , about 155 to 136.4 million years ago .
Halichoeres maculipinna ( common name clown wrasse ) is a species of tropical fish that lives throughout the Caribbean Sea and adjacent parts of the western Atlantic Ocean .
Aspasia silvana is a species of orchid , exclusively and endemic in the eastern Brazilian Serra do Mar mountains , from Rio de Janeiro to Bahia .
Anubias barteri var . glabra is a variety of A. barteri that was first described by N. E. Brown in 1901 .
Cherax holthuisi is a species of crayfish from the Bird 's Head Peninsula in New Guinea .
Phyllanthus urinaria , commonly called chamber bitter , gripeweed , shatterstone , stonebreaker or leafflower , is a herb species in the family Phyllanthaceae .
Entomophthoromycota is a fungus division .
Palaeoephippiorhynchus is an extinct genus of large stork from the Oligocene and Miocene .

Abrocoma is a genus of abrocomid rodents found in the Andes of South America , from southern Peru to central Chile .

Rhinosolea microlepidota is a species of sole native to the Pacific Ocean from around the Ryukyu Islands .

Omoiosicista is an extinct genus of dipodid rodent which existed in central Nei Mongol , China , during the early Miocene ( middle Burdigalian age ) .

Eosphargis is an extinct genus of sea turtles from the Eocene of Africa , Europe , and North America .
Pseudhipparion is an extinct genus of horse endemic to North America during the Miocene .

Prunus maritima , the beach plum , is a species of plum native to the East Coast of the United States , from Maine south to Maryland .
Sineleotris is a genus of freshwater sleepers native to eastern Asia , where found in Hainan , Hong Kong , Laos and Vietnam .
Timorichthys is a genus of viviparous brotulas so far known from the East China Sea and the Timor Sea .
Nyctosauridae ( meaning `` night lizards '' or `` bat lizards '' ) is a family of specialized soaring pterosaurs of the late Cretaceous Period of North America and , possibly , Europe .
Prunus tenella Batsch , dwarf Russian almond , is a species of deciduous shrubs in the genus Prunus , native to steppes of Eastern Europe and Western Siberia , as well as dry open sites of Caucasus , Western and Central Asia .
Hydrophilus acuminatus , common name Dark Diving Beetle , is a species of water scavenger beetles belonging to the Hydrophilidae family .

Pelasgus stymphalicus is a threatened species of small freshwater fish .
The crocodile icefish or white - blooded fish ( Channichthyidae ) comprise a family of notothenioid fishes found in the cold waters around Antarctica and southern South America .
Cladium californicum is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common name California sawgrass .
Penicillium calidicanium is a fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from soil in Taiwan .

Opsilia varentzovi is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family that can be found in Caucassus , Iran , and South Caucasus .

Calochortus nudus is a North American species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common name naked mariposa lily .
Macropoma ( from Greek μακρός `` large '' + πόμα `` cover '' , after its large operculum ) is an extinct genus of coelacanth in the class Sarcopterygii .
Bulinus barthi is a species of small tropical freshwater snail with a sinistral shell , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Planorbidae , the ramshorn snails and their allies .

Quercus diversifolia is an uncommon North American species of oak native to Mexico .
Polyrhachis lucidula is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae , found in Cambodia , Myanmar , and China .
Rhodocyclus purpureus is a species of bacteria .
Artemisia frigida is a widespread species of flowering plant in the aster family , which is known as the sunflower family .
Sagartia elegans is a species of sea anemone in the family Sagartiidae .
Urosticte is a genus of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family , which is restricted to humid forests growing on Andean slopes in north - western South America .
The Oxalidaceae , or wood sorrel family , are a small family of eight genera of herbaceous plants , shrubs and small trees , with the great majority of the 900 species in the genus Oxalis ( wood sorrels ) .
Tealliocaris is an extinct genus of pygocephalomorphan from the Carboniferous .
Angadenia is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1878 .
Xinghaiornis is an extinct genus of toothless basal ornithothoracine dinosaur known from the Early Cretaceous Yixian Formation ( Aptian stage ) of western Liaoning Province , northeastern China .
The Ascocorticiaceae are a family of fungi in the Ascomycota , class Leotiomycetes .
Helioceratops is a genus of neoceratopsian dinosaur from the Middle Cretaceous of China .
Tassiliodus is an extinct genus of euselachian chondrichthyan known from the Early Devonian of southern Algeria .
Causus bilineatus is a venomous viper species endemic to south central Africa .
Galium virgatum , common name southwestern bedstraw , is a North American species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Crataegus punctata is a species of hawthorn known by the common names dotted hawthorn or white haw that is native to most of the eastern U.S. and eastern Canada .
Pteris lydgatei is a rare fern species in the Pteridoideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Andinobates altobueyensis ( synonyms ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Niesslia is a genus of fungi within the Niessliaceae family .
Drymophila is a bird genus in the antbird family ( Thamnophilidae ) .
Clematis paniculata ( In Māori : Puawhananga ) is one of seven species of clematis that is native to New Zealand .
Uca perplexa is a species of fiddler crab .
Amalocalyx is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae consisting of lianas often found clinging to trees .
Durvillaea antarctica , commonly known as cochayuyo , is a large , robust bull kelp species and the dominant seaweed in southern New Zealand and Chile .
Dupontia poweri is a species of small air - breathing land snail , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Euconulidae , the hive snails .
Victaphanta compacta , common name the Otway black snail , is a species of carnivorous air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Rhytididae .
Memecylon myrtiforne is a species of plant in the Melastomataceae family .
Hyloxalus maculosus ( spotted rocket frog ) is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family .
Arion vejdorskyi or Arion vejdowskyi is a taxon with unclear taxonomic position and probably a synonym for other species .
The Sula megapode or Sula scrubfowl ( Megapodius bernsteinii ) is a species of bird in the Megapodiidae family .
Boletellus emodensis , commonly known as the shaggy cap , is a species of fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Chlidonoptera lestoni is a species of praying mantis in the genus Chlidonoptera in the order Mantodea .
Claytonia palustris is a species of wildflower in the purslane family known by the common names Jonesville springbeauty and marsh claytonia .
Gautieria monticola is a species of hypogeal fungus in the family Gomphaceae .
Gallicolumba is a mid - sized genus of ground - dwelling doves ( family Columbidae ) which occur in rainforests on the Philippines , Indonesia , and in the Pacific region .
Bradinopyga geminata is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae known commonly as the granite ghost .
Silene coronaria is a species of flowering plant in the carnation family Caryophyllaceae , native to Asia and Europe .
Alloporus is a genus of giant millipedes that live in deserts .
Wikstroemia johnplewsii , common name Hiva Oa Ohelo , is a plant species endemic to the island of Hiva Oa in the Marquesas Islands , French Polynesia .
Mimulus leptaleus is a species of monkeyflower known by the common name slender monkeyflower .
Pittosporum patulum , referred to as pitpat particularly botanists , is a species of plant in the Pittosporaceae family endemic to the South Island of New Zealand .
Discolocrinus thieli is a species of sea lily , a crinoid in the family Bathycrinidae .
Serissa is a genus of flowering plants in the family Rubiaceae , containing only one species , Serissa japonica .
Heteractis aurora , also known as the beaded sea anemone , aurora host anemone , sand anemone , carpet anemone , flat anemone , corn anemone , ritteri anemone , saddle tip anemone , adhesive sea anemone , and the white beaded anemone , is a species of sea anemone in the family Stichodactylidae .
Corythucha tuthilli is a little - known species of lace bug Tingidae native to Colorado and Arizona .
Orthetrum azureum is a freshwater dragonfly species , occurring on Madagascar .
Eltroplectris the Long - claw Orchid , is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
The Jalapan pine vole ( Microtus quasiater ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Agrobacterium tumefaciens ( updated scientific name Rhizobium radiobacter , synonym Agrobacterium radiobacter ) is the causal agent of crown gall disease ( the formation of tumours ) in over 140 species of eudicots .
Allograpta obliqua is a common North American species of hoverfly .
Percrocuta is an extinct genus of hyena - like feliform carnivores .
Mycena aurantiomarginata , commonly known as the golden - edge bonnet , is a species of agaric fungus in the family Mycenaceae .
Hoplocorypha perplexa is a species of praying mantis found in Angola , Namibia , Tanzania , Zimbabwe and the Congo River area .
Gardenia gordonii is a species of plant in the Rubiaceae family endemic to Fiji .
Phenacocoelus is an extinct genus of oreodont of the family Merycoidodontidae , subfamily Merycoidodontinae , endemic to North America during the Late Oligocene - Early Miocene subepochs ( 24.8 - -20.6 mya ) , existing for approximately 4.2 million years .
Rubus segnis is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Anthracosauria is an order of extinct reptile - like amphibians that flourished during the Carboniferous and early Permian periods , although precisely which species are included depends on one 's definition of the taxon .
Taeniolethrinops laticeps is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it occurs over sandy substrates .
Arundinella is a widespread genus of plants in the grass family , common in many tropical and subtropical regions .
Crepis intermedia is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name limestone hawksbeard .
Wentletraps are small , often white , very high - spired , predatory or ectoparasitic sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Epitoniidae .
Datnioides is a genus of fish known commonly as the freshwater tripletails .
Streptocaulon is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1834 .
Proischnura polychromatica , the mauve bluet , is a small species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae .
Haustrum haustorium , common name : the brown or dark rock shell , is a large species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Acromyrmex pubescens is a species of New World ants of the subfamily Myrmicinae of the genus Acromyrmex .
It contains only one species , Atsusina curiosissima , which is found in Vietnam .
Siphonaria zelandica is a species of medium - sized air - breathing sea snail or false limpet , a marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Siphonariidae , the false limpets .
Dugesia notogaea is a species of dugesiid triclad that inhabits freshwater bodies of north Queensland , Australia .
Hyalophysa clampi is a species of freshwater protist known as an apostome ciliate .
Helanthium tenellum is species of plants in the Alismataceae .
Quercus serrata ( Chinese : 枹栎 ; pinyin : bāolì ) is an East Asian species of tree in the beech family .

Aegilops columnaris ( syn . Triticum columnare ( Zhuk . ) Morris & Sears , comb . nov . ) is a species in the Poaceae family .
Moraea bituminosa is a species of the genus Moraea in family Iridaceae .
Xyletinus longitarsis is a species of beetles in the genus Xyletinus of the family Anobiidae .
Blastocystis is a genus of single - celled protozoan parasites belonging to a group of organisms known as the Stramenopiles ( also called Heterokonts ) that includes algae , diatoms , and water molds .
Parakuhlia macrophthalmus , the dara , is a species of grunt native to the Atlantic coast of Africa from Senegal to Angola .
Scolymus ( golden thistle or oyster thistle ) is a genus of plants in the dandelion tribe within the daisy family , native to the Mediterranean region and western Europe north to northwestern France .
Cyanolyca is a genus of small jays found in humid highland forests in southern Mexico , Central America and the Andes in South America .

Hyalobagrus flavus is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Indonesia where it is known only from the Batang Hari drainage in Sumatra and the Mentaya River basin in southern Borneo where it inhabits brown water habitats that are closely associated with blackwater peat swamps .
It contains only one species , Oiophassus nycterus , which was described from Shanwang Bed sw2 in the Linchu district , Shantung province in China , which is part of an Astaracian lacustrine sandstone / mudstone in the Shanwang Formation .
Penicillium albidum is an anamorph fungus species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from volcanic soils in the south of Chile .
Decliniidae is a family of beetles in the large suborder Polyphaga .
Anisopeplus perplexa is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Anisopeplus .
Papilio wilsoni belongs to a clade called the nireus species - group with 13 members .
Cyperus eragrostis is a species of sedge known by several common names , including tall flatsedge , nutgrass , tall nutgrass , umbrella sedge , chufa , Earth almond , zula nuts , edible galingale and pale galingale .

The daggertooths ( genus Anotopterus ) are a genus of aulopiform fish , the sole genus of the family Anotopteridae .
Unio turtoni is a species of medium - sized freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Haworthia cymbiformis is a species of the genus Haworthia in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , endemic to the Eastern Cape Province in South Africa .
Amietia vandijki ( Van Dijk 's river frog ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family .
Platyoides grandidieri is a spider species in the genus Platyoides found in Kenya , Madagascar , Aldabra and Réunion .
Otteissa sericea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Otteissa .
Allium flavescens is a Eurasian species of wild onion native to Bulgaria , Romania , Ukraine , European Russia , Western Siberia , Altay Krai , and Kazakhstan .
Scelophysa trimeni , commonly known as the blue monkey beetle , is a species of scarab beetles in the monkey beetle subfamily Rutelinae .

Erigeron miser is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names starved daisy or starved fleabane .

Alopecosa is a spider genus in the family Lycosidae ( wolf spiders ) , with about 140 species and several subspecies .
Callicarpa pedunculata is species of beautyberry native to Australia .
Apis mellifera iberiensis , or the Spanish bee ( commonly misspelled as iberica ) , is a Western honey bee subspecies native to the Iberian Peninsula .

Economidichthys is a genus of freshwater gobies endemic to Greece .
Maoricolpus finlayi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Turritellidae .

The San Marcos salamander ( Eurycea nana ) is a small species of aquatic , lungless salamander native to the United States , endemic to Spring Lake and a small region of the headwaters of the San Marcos River near Aquarena Springs , in Hays County , Texas .
Caprichthys gymnura , also known as the Rigid boxfish , is a species of deepwater boxfish native to the waters of the continental shelf off the western and southern coasts of Australia .

Rhizobium loessense is a root nodule bacteria , first isolated from nodules of Astragalus and Lespedeza species .

This suborder is paraphyletic in relation to the Pterodactyloidea , which arose from within the Rhamphorhynchoidea , not from a more distant common ancestor .
Synodontis guttatus is a species of upside - down catfish native to the Niger River basin of Niger and Nigeria .
Zygosignata is a genus of moths belonging to the family Tineidae .
Diloma nigerrima , common name the bluish top shell , is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Cicurina madla is a rare species of spider in the family Dictynidae known by the common name Madla Cave meshweaver .
Compsospiza is a genus of South American birds known as mountain finches ( a name shared with several other species such as Poospiza caesar and Leucosticte ) .
Meiacanthus grammistes ( the striped blenny , striped fang blenny , grammistes blenny , line - spot harptail blenny or striped poison - fang blenny ) is a species of combtooth blenny from the western Pacific Ocean .
Ixiolirion is a genus of flowering plants native to central and southwest Asia , first described as a genus in 1821 .
Cactobrosis insignatella is a species of snout moth in the genus Cactobrosis .
Chaudhuria is a genus of spineless eels native to Southeast Asia .
Arctosa tbilisiensis is a wolf spider species in the genus Arctosa found in Europe ( Bulgaria , Greece to Georgia ) .
It consists of only one species , Pyloetis mimosae , which is found in Asia , including Japan and Taiwan .
Dionaea flavisquamis is a European species of fly in the family Tachinidae .
The only described species Pseudoplexippus unicus is endemic to Tanzania .
Schizomida ( common name shorttailed whipscorpion ) is an order of arachnids , generally less than 5 millimetres ( 0.20 in ) in length .
Pronycticebus was a genus of adapiformes primates that lived during the middle to middle late Eocene .
Trichosirocalus is a genus of true weevil , native to the Old World , placed alternatively in the subfamily Ceutorhynchinae or in the tribe Ceutorhynchini of the subfamily Baridinae .
†Opisthonematidae is an extinct family of paleozoic gastropod mollusks .
Quercus conspersa is a Mesoamerican species of oak tree in the beech family .
Synchiropus rubrovinctus is a species of dragonet native to the western Pacific where it has been found around Japan , New Caledonia and Hawaii .
Branchiosauridae is an extinct family of temnospondyl amphibians .
Hexapodidae is a family of crabs , the only family in the superfamily Hexapodoidea .
Holothuria forskali , the black sea cucumber or cotton - spinner , is a species of sea cucumber in the family Holothuriidae .
Philochortus zolii is a species of lacertid lizard in the family Lacertidae .
Eohupehsuchus is a genus of extinct hupehsuchian diapsids from the Lower Triassic of China .
Encyclia fehlingii is a species of orchid that was named for Gladys Fehling who lived on Andros Island in the Bahamas and spent much of her time searching for the orchids of the area and growing them for her own pleasure .
Leptotyphlops macrolepis , or the Big - scaled blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
Zabrus foveipennis is a species of ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that is endemic to Turkey .
Kitchingnathus ( Kitchings ' mandible ) is an extinct genus of basal procolophonid parareptile from Early Triassic ( early Olenekian stage ) deposits of Eastern Cape Province , South Africa .
Thoracica is a superorder of crustaceans which contains the most familiar species of barnacles found on rocky coasts , such as Semibalanus balanoides and Chthamalus stellatus .
The genus Geomys contains nine species of pocket gophers often collectively referred to as the eastern pocket gophers .
Gibberula ramsi is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod micromollusk in the family Cystiscidae .
Trifolium medium , the zigzag clover , is a flowering plant species in the bean family Fabaceae .
Erica urna - viridis ( the Sticky Heath or Bottle - green Heath ) is a species of erica that was naturally restricted to the city of Cape Town , South Africa , in particular the Peninsula Sandstone Fynbos of Table Mountain .
Phyllorhinichthys balushkini is a species of dreamer found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Cephalaralia cephalobotrys is a species of epiphytic vine of the family Araliaceae , endemic to Australia .
Nepomorpha is an infraorder of insects in the `` true bug '' order ( Hemiptera ) .
Phaedyma is a genus of Asian butterflies distributed from India to New Guinea and the Bismarck Archipelago .
Megalagrion xanthomelas ( orangeblack Hawaiian damselfly ) is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae that is endemic to Hawaii .
Syringodium filiforme , commonly known as manatee grass , is a species of marine seagrass .
Pristiapogon is a genus of cardinalfishes native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Mycobacterium arosiense is a newly described species of Mycobacterium .
Ichthyophis khumhzi , the Khumhzi striped ichthyophis , is a species of caecilian found in India .
Carruanthus is a genus of flowering plants from the ice plant family Aizoaceae .
Eupsophus is a genus of frogs in the Alsodidae family .
Onoba aculeus , common name the pointed cingula , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
The shining tree iguana , Liolaemus nitidus , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Pediomelum californicum is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name California Indian breadroot .
Erinus alpinus ( fairy foxglove , starflower , alpine balsam , liver balsam ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Plantaginaceae , native to Central and Southern Europe .

Bolinopsis infundibulum , the common northern comb jelly , is a species of comb jelly in the family Bolinopsidae .
Pyrophorus punctatissimus is a species of click beetle ( family Elateridae ) .
Dipteryx is a genus containing nine species of shrubs and trees .
Parahepialus nebulosus is a species of moth of the family Hepialidae .
Olivaichthys mesembrinus is a species of velvet catfish endemic to Argentina where it is found in the Chubut and Senguer River basins .
Seychellum alluaudi is a species of freshwater crab endemic to the Seychelles , and the only true freshwater crab in that country .
Eresus sandaliatus is a species of spider found primarily in northern and central Europe .
The Russian tortoise ( Agrionemys horsfieldii ) , also commonly known as Horsfield 's tortoise or the Central Asian tortoise , is a species of tortoise and a popular pet .
Cicurina rhodiensis is a spider species found in Rhodes .
Lophophora is a genus of spineless , button - like cacti native to the southwestern United States ( Texas and New Mexico ) through Northeast Mexico and South to Querétaro in central Mexico .
Blepharipappus is a North American plant genus in the daisy family containing the single known species Blepharipappus scaber , known by the common name rough eyelash , or rough eyelashweed .
Cissus anisophylla is a plant species known from lowland rainforests of Panamá , Colombia , Chiapas , Brazil , Perú , Costa Rica and Ecuador .
Schistura montana is a species of stone loach endemic to Himachal Pradesh , India .
Penicillium implicatum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which causes postharvest rot on pomegranate .
The umbilicate pebblesnail , scientific name Clappia umbilicata , was a species of small freshwater snail that had an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Tidestromia is a genus with about six or seven species of annual or subshrub perennial plants native to desert and semi - arid regions of the western United States , Mexico and tropical America in the family Amaranthaceae .
Gnathothlibus collardi was described as a species , but by combining barcodes , morphology and a nuclear marker , research has shown that it is actually an F1 hybrid between two closely related species .
Ipomoea hederifolia is a species of herbaceous annual vine native to the Americas .
Zonitidae , common name the true glass snails , are a family of mostly rather small , air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Zonitoidea .
Conophytum elegans is a succulent plant species in the genus Conophytum .
Lobophytum is a genus of soft corals commonly known as devil 's hand corals or devil 's hand leather corals .
Vectisuchus is a genus of goniopholidid mesoeucrocodylian , known from the Early Cretaceous - age Wealden Group of the Isle of Wight , England .
Pyrgulopsis castaicensis is a species of very small freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Veronica derwentiana ( Derwent speedwell ) is a flowering plant species of the family Plantaginaceae , endemic to south - eastern Australia .
Melica serrana , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to Cerro de las Ánimas , Uruguay and southern South America .
Uropeltis broughami , commonly known as Brougham 's earth snake or the Sirumallay Uropeltis , is a species of snake in the family Uropeltidae .
Tremellodendropsis tuberosa , commonly known as the ashen coral , is a species of coral fungus in the family Tremellodendropsidaceae .
Homalometron pallidum is a species of marine fluke in the class Trematoda .

Tangasauridae is a family of eosuchian diapsids .
Compsognathidae is a family of small carnivorous dinosaurs , generally conservative in form , from the Jurassic and Cretaceous Periods .
Tatankaceratops was described by Christopher J. Ott and Peter L. Larson in 2010 and the type species is Tatankaceratops sacrisonorum .
Campanula scabrella is a species of bellflower known by the common name rough bellflower .
Rehderodendron macrocarpum is a species of flowering plant in the family Styracaceae , native to southwestern China ( Guangxi , Sichuan , Yunnan ) and northern Vietnam , where it grows at altitudes of 1,000 - -1,500 m. It is threatened by habitat loss .
Nemoptera bipennis is a species of slow flying insect in the family Nemopteridae or spoonwings .
Macroplea pubipennis is a species of leaf beetle of the subfamily Donaciinae that is endemic to Finland .
Delphastus pusillus is a small ladybird beetle which preys on all species and stages of whitefly , but prefers eggs and nymphs .
Megateuthis gigantea is the largest known belemnite species .
Paracentrotus lividus is a species of sea urchin in the family Parechinidae commonly known as the purple sea urchin .
Synclera traducalis , the variegated pearl , is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .
Nebria germari is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Austria , Germany , Italy , Liechtenstein , Switzerland , and in every state of former Yugoslavia , except for Republic of Macedonia .
Danionella is a genus of danionin fish found in freshwater habitats in Myanmar and West Bengal , India .
Helcystogramma is a genus of moths in the family Gelechiidae .
Opsilia schurmanni is a species of beetle from a Cerambycidae family that is endemic to Republic of Macedonia .
Wahlenbergia roxburghii ( Roxburgh bellflower or dwarf cabbage tree ) is an extinct member of a group of four species of Wahlenbergia once known from the island of Saint Helena , in the South Atlantic Ocean .
Eleocharis vivipara is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by several common names , including umbrella hairgrass , sprouting spikerush , and viviparous spikerush .
Kritosaurus is an incompletely known genus of hadrosaurid ( duck - billed ) dinosaur .
Pennisetum purpureum , also known as Napier grass , elephant grass or Uganda grass , is a species of perennial tropical grass native to the African grasslands .
Chilobrycon deuterodon is a species of characin endemic to Peru , where it is found in the Tumbes River .
Monanthes muralis is a species in the genus Monanthes , forming small , succulent bushes with green flowers .
Brachionus is a genus of planktonic rotifers occurring in freshwater , alkaline and brackish water .
Typhlops microstomus , or the Yucatán blind snake , is a species of snake in the Typhlopidae family .
Esperia oliviella is a species of gelechioid moth from Europe and the Near East .
Eria is a large genus of orchids with more than 500 species distributed in China , the Himalayas , the Indian Subcontinent , Southeast Asia , New Guinea , Polynesia , Melanesia and Micronesia .
The genus Cacalia L. is a nomen rejiciendum ( rejected name ) under the International Code of Nomenclature for algae , fungi , and plants .
Atherion is a small genus of silversides .

The Paddyfield Parasol , ( Neurothemis intermedia ) is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Bornella anguilla is a species of sea slug , a nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bornellidae .
Anthaster valvulatus is a species of sea star in the family Orestieridae .
Chilabothrus chrysogaster , commonly known as the Turks Island boa or the Southern Bahamas boa , is a species of snake found in the Southern Bahamas ( Inagua , Crooked Island and Acklins ) and the Turks and Caicos Islands .
Allium flavidum is an Asian species of onions native to Xinjiang , Altay Krai , Mongolia and Kazakhstan .
Recilia acuminatus is a species of bugs from Cicadellidae family that is endemic to India .
Gerbera jamesonii is a species of flowering plant in the genus Gerbera .
Echinomastus erectocentrus is a species of cactus known by the common names redspine fishhook cactus , redspine butterfly cactus , acuña cactus , needle - spine pineapple cactus , red pineapple cactus , and purple - spine viznagita .
Papilio microps is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Ethiopia and Somalia .
Cirsium loncholepis is a rare species of thistle known by the common name La Graciosa thistle .
Ubristes is a genus of hoverflies , with 61 known species .
Streptomyces albiaxialis is a halotolerant bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from an oil field in Russia .
Hemiphragmoceratidae is a family of endogastrically brevconic oncocerids characterized by elaborately visored apertures in which the hyponomic sinus in mature specimens is on a spout - like process and there may be lateral and dorsal salients .
Palaeorhincodon is an extinct genus of prehistoric whale shark from the Paleocene and Eocene of Africa and North America .
Paedophryne amauensis is a species of frog from Papua New Guinea discovered in August 2009 and formally described in January 2012 .
Lentipes whittenorum is a species of goby endemic to marine , brackish and fresh waters of Indonesia .
Benedictia maxima is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusc in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Helicocranchia is a genus of glass squids including Helicocranchia papillata , Helicocranchia pfefferi , and Helicocranchia joubini
Santalum ellipticum , commonly known as ʻIliahialoʻe ( Hawaiian ) or coastal sandalwood , is a species of flowering plant in the European mistletoe family , Santalaceae , that is endemic to the Hawaiian Islands .
Podoliacanthus is an extinct genus of Acanthodii ( `` spiky sharks '' ) which existed in what is now Greenland and Ukraine during the early Devonian period .
Raorchestes coonoorensis , also known as the Coonore bushfrog or Coonoor bush frog , is a species of frog endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
Chriacus is an extinct genus of prehistoric mammal which lived in North America around 63 million years ago .
Abies beshanzuensis ( Baishanzu fir , Baishan fir ) is a species of fir ( genus Abies ) in the family Pinaceae .
Notogramma cactipeodes is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Notogramma of the family Tephritidae .
Amphiesma khasiense , commonly known as the Khasi Hills keelback , is a species of colubrid snake endemic to southeastern Asia .
Leptospermum scoparium , commonly called mānuka , manuka myrtle , New Zealand teatree , broom tea - tree , or just tea tree , is a species of flowering plant in the myrtle family Myrtaceae , native to southeast Australia and New Zealand .

Novaculichthys taeniourus ( rockmover , dragon , or reindeer wrasse ) is a species of wrasse mainly found in coral reefs and lagoons in the Indo - Pacific region .
Acharagma is a genus of two small cactus species from northern Mexico .
Leiostyla cassida is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Lauriidae .
Fruticicola fruticum is a species of medium - sized , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Bradybaenidae .
Myromexocentrus tibialis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Myromexocentrus .
Lambdotherium ( `` Wave Beast '' ) is a genus of North American brontothere .
Pareiasaurs ( meaning `` cheek lizards '' ) are an extinct group of anapsid reptiles classified in the family Pareiasauridae .
Veronica bullii ( syn . Besseya bullii ) is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common names kittentails and Bull 's coraldrops .
Kingsnakes are colubrid snakes , members of the genus Lampropeltis , which include milk snakes and four other species .
Pristiterebra tuberculosa , common name : the tuberculate auger , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Terebridae , the auger snails .
Velezia rigida is a species of flowering plant in the pink family .
It contains only one known species , Colebrookea oppositifolia , native to India , Pakistan , Nepal , Bhutan , Assam , Bangladesh , Myanmar , Thailand and Yunnan .

Amphisphaeria is a genus of fungi in the family Amphisphaeriaceae .
Myrmecia analis is a species of the Myrmecia genus .
Kalanchoe rhombopilosa is a succulent plant species in the Crassulaceae family .
Anacyclus ciliatus , the ciliated German pellitory , is a species of pellitory that is endemic to Azerbaijan .
Catathelasma evanescens is a species of fungus in the Tricholomataceae family , and the type species of the genus Catathelasma .
Talbotia elegans is the sole species in the monotypic genus of monocotyledonous flowering plants , Talbotia .
The Aganainae are a small subfamily of moths in the Erebidae family .
Medusafishes are a family , Centrolophidae , of perciform fishes .
Keckiella lemmonii ( formerly Penstemon lemmonii ) is a species of flowering plant in the plantain family known by the common name Lemmon 's keckiella .
Pantherophis is a proposed genus of nonvenomous colubrid snakes endemic to North America and Central America , commonly called ratsnakes or rat snakes .
The Clytrini are a tribe within the leaf beetle subfamily Cryptocephalinae , though historically they were often treated as a distinct subfamily , Clytrinae .
Stillingia linearifolia is a species of flowering plant in the euphorb family known by the common name queen's - root .
Aprasia aurita , also called the mallee worm - lizard , is a species of lizard in the Pygopodidae family endemic to Australia ; and listed on Schedule 1 under the Commonwealth 's Endangered Species Protection Act .
Pseudovates peruviana , common name Peruvian stick mantis , is a medium - sized species of praying mantis native to South America .
Chionanthus pygmaeus is a rare species of flowering plant in the olive family known by the common name pygmy fringetree .
Trichomycterus argos is a species of pencil catfish endemic to Brazil , where it occurs in the Rio Doce basin , situated in the Serra do Brigadeiro range , Minas Gerais .
Cynoglossus capensis , commonly known as the Sand tonguesole is a species of tonguefish .
Paralaudakia is a genus of lizards , commonly known as Asian rock agamas , which are endemic to Eurasia .
Phemeranthus calcaricus , the limestone fameflower , is a species of flowering plant in the family Montiaceae .
Zabrus seidlitzi is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that is endemic to Spain .
Tetramorium smaug is a species of myrmicine ant native to Ambatovy , Amber Mountain National Park , and Ivohibe in Madagascar .
It contains only one species , Cubotinea orghidani , which is found on Cuba .
Bembradium is a genus of deep - water flatheads native to the Pacific Ocean .
Argopecten purpuratus , common names the `` Peruvian scallop '' , is an edible species of saltwater clam , a scallop , a marine bivalve mollusk in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Histriasaurus ( HIS - tree - ah - SAWR - us ) ( meaning `` Istria lizard '' ) was a genus of dinosaur from the Early Cretaceous ( Hauterivian to Barremian stages , around 130 million years ago ) .
Chilobrachys jingzhao , commonly known as Chinese earth tiger tarantula or Chinese fawn tarantula , is a species of venomous tarantulas belonging to a family of Theraphosidae .
Borichthys is an extinct genus of prehistoric , ray finned bony fish .
Thioalkalimicrobium aerophilum is an obligately alkaliphilic and obligately chemolithoautotrophic sulfur - oxidizing bacteria , the type species of its genus .
Procyclotosaurus is an extinct genus of stenotosaurid capitosaurian temnospondyl .
Sphoeroides is a genus of pufferfishes .
Silene spaldingii is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names Spalding 's silene , Spalding 's catchfly and Spalding 's campion .
Phragmipedium klotzschianum is a species of orchid found from southeastern Venezuela to Guyana and northern Brazil .
Rhamnus purshiana ( cascara buckthorn , cascara , bearberry , and in the Chinook Jargon , chittem and chitticum ; syn . Frangula purshiana , Rhamnus purshianus ) is a species of buckthorn native to western North America from southern British Columbia south to central California , and eastward to northwestern Montana .
Cicindela puritana , commonly referred to as the Puritan tiger beetle , is a federally listed threatened species of beetle in the United States .
Navarretia jaredii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names mitrefruit pincushionplant and Paso Robles navarretia .
Restrepia schizosepala is a species of orchid endemic to northeastern Ecuador .
Rubus suus is an uncommon North American species of brambles in the rose family .
Mentzelia springeri is a species of flowering plant in the family Loasaceae known by the common name Santa Fe blazingstar .
The grass Tuctoria mucronata , which is known by several common names including prickly spiralgrass , Solano grass , and Crampton 's tuctoria , is a federally listed endangered plant species endemic to two counties in northern California .
Bidens micrantha is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name grassland beggarticks .
The Eleonora cockatoo , Cacatua galerita eleonora , also known as medium sulphur - crested cockatoo , is similar in appearance to other subspecies of the sulphur - crested cockatoo .
Ormia depleta , sometimes called the Brazilian red - eyed fly , is a species of fly in the family Tachinidae .
Anigozanthos humilis is a species of Anigozanthos in the family Haemodoraceae , known as common cat 's paw or catspaw .
Cervus elaphus acoronatus is an extinct subspecies of deer belonging to the family Cervidae .
Archegozetes longisetosus is a species of tropical moss mite in the family Trhypochthoniidae .
Hoplosuchus is a genus of crocodylomorph .
Hydroporus is a genus of water beetle native to the Palearctic ( including Europe ) , the Nearctic , the Near East , and North Africa .
Lisserpeton is an extinct genus of prehistoric amphibian of the Hell Creek Formation .
Carex multicaulis is a species of sedge known by the common name manystem sedge .
Large odorous frog , Odorrana graminea , is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Allosyncarpia ternata , commonly known as An - binik , is a species of rainforest trees constituting part of the botanical family Myrtaceae and included in the Eucalypts group .

Atlantosaurus ( meaning `` Atlas lizard '' ) is a dubious genus of sauropod dinosaur .

Girardinus falcatus is a species of Cuban tropical fish .
Phylloporus rhodoxanthus , commonly known as the gilled bolete , is a species of fungus in the Boletaceae family .
The Central American least shrew ( Cryptotis orophila ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Nocticolidae is a small family in the order Blattodea ( cockroaches ) .
Labeobarbus cardozoi is a species of cyprinid fish found in the Congo Democratic Republic and Angola in Africa .
Adrianites is an extinct genus of the Adrianitidae family .
The California least tern , Sternula antillarum browni , is a subspecies of least tern that breeds primarily in bays of the Pacific Ocean within a very limited range of Southern California , in San Francisco Bay and in and extreme northern Mexico .
Arctostaphylos glauca is a species of manzanita known by the common name bigberry manzanita .
Phyllodactylus angelensis is a species of lizard , or more precisely gecko , that is in genus Phyllodactylus ( or leaf - toed geckos ) .
Ionactis linariifolia also known as the flax - leaf ankle - aster , flaxleaf whitetop or simply aster is a North American species of plants in the daisy family .
Hainald 's rat ( Rattus hainaldi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Bivalvia , in previous centuries referred to as the Lamellibranchiata and Pelecypoda , is a class of marine and freshwater molluscs that have laterally compressed bodies enclosed by a shell consisting of two hinged parts .
Eucalyptocrinites is an extinct genus of crinoid that lived from the Silurian to the Middle Devonian .
Chironius laurenti is a species of nonvenomous colubrid snake found in Brazil and Bolivia .
Buenellus higginsi is the only known species in the genus Buenellus ( i.e. , the genus is monotypic ) .
Myrmecia brevinoda is a species of bull ant which is only native to Australia .
Rhynchelmis is the genus of 30 species of aquatic oligochaetes from the Northern Hemisphere , with 11 species from North America and 19 from Eurasia .
Quercus hemisphaerica ( sand laurel oak , laurel oak , Darlington oak , laurel - leaf oak ) is a species of oak native to the southeastern and south - central United States , from Texas to Delaware .
Leucocythere helenae is a species of crustacean in the family Limnocytheridae .
Myotis aurascens , known commonly as the steppe whiskered bat , is a species of mouse - eared bat .
Neopetrosia is a genus of marine petrosiid sponges .
Schoenocrambe argillacea ( syn . Hesperidanthus argillaceus ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common names clay reed - mustard , Uinta Basin plainsmustard , and clay thelypody .
Coenobita cavipes is a species of land hermit crab native to the eastern parts of Africa , the Philippines , China , Japan , Malaysia , Taiwan , Polynesia , and Micronesia .
Adiposphaerion rubrum is a species of longhorn beetle in the Elaphidiini subfamily , the only species in the genus Adiposphaerion which was described my Martins and Napp in 1992 .
Eriogonum latifolium is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common names seaside buckwheat and coast buckwheat .
Nannamoria is a small taxonomic genus of small - sized sea snails , predatory marine gastropod molluscs in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Zabrus validus is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Pterostichinae subfamily that is endemic to Greece .
Fleurydora is a genus of plant in family Ochnaceae .
Persoonia laurina was one of five species described by Christiaan Hendrik Persoon in his 1805 work Synopsis Plantarum , from material collected by John White in 1793 and 1794 .
Aspidelaps is a genus of venomous elapid snakes found in Africa .
Mexipyrgus carranzae is a species of very small freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Cochliopidae .
Pedetes surdaster was recognised by Matthee and Robinson in 1997 as a species distinct from the southern African spring hare ( Pedetes capensis ) .
The Bakır shemaya ( Alburnus attalus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
Jaltomata procumbens ( creeping false holly ) is a plant species native to Arizona , USA , Mexico , Central America , Colombia , Ecuador , and Venezuela .
The Spotted Catasetum ( Catasetum maculatum ) is a species of orchid found from Central America to Venezuela .
Trichodesmium , also called sea sawdust , is a genus of filamentous cyanobacteria .
Drosanthemum ( `` dewflowers '' ) is a genus of succulent plants in the ice plant family native to the winter - rainfall regions of southern Africa .
Kazacharthra is an extinct order of branchiopod crustaceans that appear to be closely related to the living order Notostraca ( the tadpole shrimp ) .
Panagaeus is a genus of ground beetle native to the Holarctic ( including Europe ) , the Near East , and North Africa .
Protostelium okumukumu is a species of Protostelium .
Trycherus kinduensis is a species of beetle from the Endomychidae family .
Nesodes insularis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Nesodes .
Colostethus agilis is a species of frog in the family Dendrobatidae .
The sole species is Octomeles sumatrana .
Ivesia aperta is a species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Sierra Valley mousetail .
Trachycorystes cratensis is a species of driftwood catfish endemic to Brazil where it is found in the state of Ceará in the Granjeiro River basin .
Indotriplophysa choprai is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Indotriplophysa .
Melica patagonica is a species of grass in the Poaceae family that is endemic to South America .
Scotinotylus alienus is a species of sheet weaver found in Alaska , Canada and Russia .
It contains only one known species , Rhododon ciliatus , the Texas sandmint endemic to the State of Texas in the United States .
Oeceoclades analavelensis is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to southwestern Madagascar .
Dendrobates is a genus of poison dart frogs native to Central and South America .
Habenaria macroceratitis ( big - horn bog orchid or long - horned false rein orchid ) is a species of orchid closely related to H. quinqueseta and often mistaken for it .
The Pel 's fishing owl ( Scotopelia peli ) is a large species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Gibbestoloides compacta is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Gibbestoloides .
Chilocorus bipustulatus , the heather ladybird , is a beetle species belonging to the family Coccinellidae , subfamily Chilocorinae .
Micropterix cypriensis is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae , and was first described by John Heath in 1985 from specimens collected in Cyprus .
Mexipedium is a monotypic genus of the Orchid family Orchidaceae , subfamily Cypripedioideae , consisting of only one species , Mexipedium xerophyticum .
Longitarsus eminus is a species of beetle from the Chrysomelidae family that can be found everywhere in Europe ( except Portugal ) .
Erigeron radicatus is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Hooker 's fleabane and taproot fleabane The species grows in central Canada ( Alberta , Saskatchewan ) and parts of the north - central United States , primarily the northern Rocky Mountains and the Black Hills .
Astrophytum caput - medusae is an species of cactus native to the Americas .
Glyphyalinia pecki is a species of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Zonitidae .
Zorotypus absonus is an extinct species of insect in the genus Zorotypus .
Ophiuridae are a large family of brittle stars of the suborder Ophiurina .
Bridled Bent - toed Gecko , Cyrtodactylus fraenatus , also known as Sri Lanka Bent - toed Gecko , is a species of gecko endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Chamaelirium is a genus of flowering plants containing the single species Chamaelirium luteum , commonly known as Blazing - Star , Devil 's Bit , False Unicorn , Fairy Wand , and Helonias .
Acyperas aurantiacella is a species of snout moth in the genus Acyperas .
Bothriodon is an extinct genus of anthracotheriid artiodactyl from the late Eocene of Asia , Europe , and North America .
Schiedea attenuata is a rare species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common name Kalalau schiedea .
Hymenochirus feae , also known as Gaboon Dwarf Clawed Frog , is a species of frog in the Pipidae family .

Melica amethystina is a grass species in the grass family that can be found in southern Europe .
Quercus uxoris is an uncommon Mexican species of trees in the beech family .
Agonum impressum is a species of ground beetles in the Platyninae subfamily .
Haplochromis worthingtoni is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Kyoga in Uganda .

Coryphagrion grandis is a species of damselfly found in coastal forests and on the lower slopes of the Eastern Arc Mountains in Kenya , Tanzania and Mozambique .
Bufonaria echinata , the spiny frog shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Circaeaster agrestis is a flowering plant species and one of only one to two species in its family , the Circaeasteraceae .
Quercus pungens , commonly known as the sandpaper oak or scrub oak , is a North American species evergreen or sub - evergreen shrub or small tree in the white oak group .
Archimantis latistyla , commonly known as the large brown mantis ( also known as the stick mantis or Australian mantis ) is a species of mantid native to Australia .

Pissodes is a genus of weevils described by Ernst Friedrich Germar in 1817 .
Triunia is a genus of medium to tall shrubs or small trees found as understorey plants in rainforests of eastern Australia .
Pleuropogon is a genus of Arctic and North American plants in the grass family known generally as semaphore grass .

Astragalus curtipes is a species of milkvetch known by the common name Morro milkvetch .
Howellia aquatilis ( water howellia ) is a small plant in the family Campanulaceae and is considered to a threatened species since 1994 .
The phylogenetic and genotypic analysis shows that Methylobacillus pratensis is a novel species of the genus Methylobacillus .
Galaxea fascicularis is a species of colonial stony coral in the family Oculinidae , commonly known as octopus coral , fluorescence grass coral , galaxy coral among various vernacular names .
The Scophthalmidae are a family of flatfish found in the North Atlantic Ocean , Baltic Sea , Mediterranean Sea , and Black Sea .
Streptomyces eurythermus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil from Cuanza in Angola .
The Pink Heelsplitter ( Potamilus alatus ) is a species of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , commonly known as the river mussels .
Papilio delalandei is a member of the dardanus species - group .
Sinusonasus is a genus of dinosaurs from the Early Cretaceous Period , recovered from the Yixian Formation .
Ligusticum apiifolium is a species of plant in the carrot family known by the common names celery - leafed lovage and celery - leaf licorice - root .
Sirenia ( commonly referred to as sea cows ) are an order of fully aquatic , herbivorous mammals that inhabit swamps , rivers , estuaries , marine wetlands , and coastal marine waters .
Heliopsis decumbens is a rare South American species of flowering plant in the family sunflower family .
Salacca ramosiana is a species of palm in the genus Salacca .
Cnemosioma innominata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Cnemosioma .
Cibaomyces is an agaric fungal genus found in China , Japan , France , and Germany in forests containing Fagaceae .
Eschmeyer nexus is a species of cofish known only from the Pacific Ocean from near Fiji where it is found at depths of from 27 to 43 metres ( 89 to 141 ft ) .
Neurachne , commonly called mulga grass , is a genus of Australian plants in the grass family .

The Cinchoneae are a tribe of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family containing about 125 species in 9 genera .
Carsidaridae is a bug family in the superfamily Psylloidea .
Amelanchier australis is a plant species native to Mexico and New Mexico .
Guildfordia triumphans , common name the triumphant star turban , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae , the turban snails .

Geosmithia morbida is a species of anamorphic fungus that causes thousand cankers disease in species of walnut trees ( Juglans spp . )
Titanopsis is a genus of about 10 species of succulent plants of the family Aizoaceae , indigenous to the arid regions of South Africa and Namibia .
Lechriodus melanopyga , the Wokan Cannibal Frog , is a species of frog in the Myobatrachidae family .
Campaea honoraria , known commonly as the embellished thorn , is a species of moth in the Geometridae family .
Ichthyophis is a genus of caecilians ( limbless amphibians , sometimes called the Asian caecilians ) found in Southeast Asia , the southern Philippines , and the western Indo - Australian Archipelago .
Ilex brachyphylla is a type of Holly - a species of plant in the Aquifoliaceae family .
Genidens is a genus of sea catfishes found along the Atlantic coast of South America .
Littorina sitkana is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Littorinidae , the winkles .
Acidimicrobium is a genus of Actinobacteria , given its own subclass ( Acidimicrobidae ) .
Metriopelia is a genus of ground doves containing four species that live in the dry , upland habitats along the Andean mountain chain in South America .
The first Cassin 's sparrow was described in 1852 by Samuel W. Woodhouse from a specimen collected near San Antonio , Texas , and given its species name in honor of John Cassin , a Philadelphia ornithologist .
Hollowaya is a genus of tiger moths in the Erebidae family and is strictly endemic for New Caledonia .
Neofabricia is a genus of shrubs and small trees in the Myrtaceae family , first described as a genus in 1788 , with the name Fabricia .
Catathelasma imperiale is a large species of mushroom in the Tricholomataceae family .
It contains only one species , Syngeneta sordida , which is found in Tanzania .
Arixeniidae is a family of earwigs ; it is the only family in the suborder Arixeniina ( one of the four suborders of the order Dermaptera ) .
Coluber vittacaudatus is a species of snake found in Darjeeling , India .
Inocybe salicis is an uncommon species of fungus found in association with willow in Europe .
In taxonomy , Treubaria is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Treubariaceae .
Tiliacora triandra is a species of flowering plant native to mainland Southeast Asia and used particularly in the cuisines of northeast Thailand and Laos .
Abralia grimpei is a species of enoploteuthid cephalopod known from the western North Atlantic Ocean , including the West Indies and the Sargasso Sea .
Haliotis kamtschatkana , common name the northern abalone or pinto abalone , is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Eoborus fusiforme is a fossil species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Strophocheilidae , from the Paleocene deposits of the Itaboraí Basin , in the state of Rio de Janeiro , Brazil .
Omiodes telegrapha , the telegraphic hedyleptan moth , is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .
The clade Sauria was traditionally a suborder for lizards which originally ( before 1800 ) comprised crocodilians too .
Aboriginella is an extinct genus of brachiopod found in Aksayan to Batyrbaian strata in Kazakhstan .
Melanochromis dialeptos is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from rocky habitats near Masinje .
Belonopelta is a Neotropical genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Bathymophila is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Solariellidae .
Euonymus pendulus ( syn . E. lucidus D.Don ) is a species of Euonymus native to the Himalaya region , from Pakistan east to northern Assam .
Plateosaurus ( probably meaning `` broad lizard '' , often mistranslated as `` flat lizard '' ) is a genus of plateosaurid dinosaur that lived during the Late Triassic period , around 214 to 204 million years ago , in what is now Central and Northern Europe .
Cardiograptus is a genus of graptolite , which is easily recognised even when poorly preserved by the form of the thecae .
Anacanthobatis is a genus of smooth skates native to the Indian , Atlantic and Pacific oceans .
Wild rice ( also called Canada rice , Indian rice , and water oats ) are four species of grasses forming the genus Zizania , and the grain that can be harvested from them .
Hedleya macleayi is a species of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Pupinidae and the superfamily Cyclophoridae .
Millettia nitida is a legume species in the genus Millettia .
Plectranthias is a genus of rather small serranid fishes with large mouths and eyes close together .
Langloisia setosissima ( bristly langloisia , bristly - calico , Great Basin langloisia or lilac sunbonnets ) is a flowering plant , the sole species in the genus Langloisia in the family Polemoniaceae .
Cindarella is genus of trilobite - like Cambrian arthropod known from the Chengjiang biota of China .
Blethisa is a genus of ground beetle native to the Palearctic .
Mesobuthus eupeus is a polymorphic scorpion species belonging to the well - known family Buthidae .
Actinotocarcinus is an extinct genus of crab .
Arenocoris fallenii is a herbivorous species of True Bug in the family Coreidae .
Ralfsia verrucosa is a species of crustose brown seaweed in the family Ralfsiaceae .
Pterocryptis furnessi is a species of catfish in the Siluridae family ( the sheatfishes ) endemic to Malaysia , where it occurs in the Niah and Baram river basins in Sarawak , on the island of Borneo .
Xerocomus subtomentosus , commonly known as suede bolete , brown and yellow bolet , boring brown bolete or yellow - cracked bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae .
