Xenasmatella is a genus of corticioid fungi in the order Polyporales .
Octodontotherium is an extinct genus of ground sloth of the family Mylodontidae , endemic to South America during the Oligocene - Miocene .
Amphitherium is an extinct genus of holotherian mammal that lived during the Middle Jurassic period .
Turbo argyrostomus , common name the silver - mouthed turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
Progradungula otwayensis , commonly known as the odd - clawed spider , is a species of cribellate spider endemic to the Great Otway National Park of Victoria , Australia .
Brachysternaster chesheri is a species of sea urchins of the Family Paleopneustina incertae sedis B. Their armour is covered with spines .
Pseudochazara lydia ( Staudinger 1878 ) is a species of butterfly in the Nymphalidae family .
Hylocharis is a genus of hummingbird in the Trochilidae family .
Gadilida is an order of very small tusk shells , marine scaphopod molluscs .
Atriplex plebeja is a species of plant in the Chenopodiaceae family .
Malinae ( incorrectly Pyrinae ) is the name for the apple subtribe in the rose family , Rosaceae .
Plagiobothrys mollis is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name soft popcornflower .
Rodgersia pinnata is a species of flowering plant in the family Saxifragaceae , native to the Sichuan and Yunnan provinces of China .
Oberea curtilineata is a species of longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Pic in 1915 .
Pitcairnia aurea is a plant species in the genus Pitcairnia .
The Halfmoon picassofish species is often also named Halfmoon triggerfish .
Dendrochirus is a genus of scorpionfishes that are mostly known as dwarf lionfishes .
Taxillus kaempferi ( Chinese : 小叶钝果寄生 xiao ye dun guo ji sheng ) is a parasitic plant species in the genus Taxillus found in China ( Anhui , Fujian , W Hubei , S Jiangxi , Sichuan , S Zhejiang ) , Bhutan and Japan .
Xyliphius kryptos is a species of banjo catfish endemic to Venezuela where it is found in the Lake Maracaibo basin .
Phalium areola , common name the checkerboard bonnet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the subfamily Cassinae , within the family Cassidae the helmet and bonnet shells .
Chrysobrycon is a genus of characins endemic to South America .
Rostanga aliusrubens is a species of sea slug , a dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Discodorididae .
The Seram friarbird ( Philemon subcorniculatus ) , also known as the grey - necked friarbird , Ceram friarbird , grey - necked honeyeater and gray - necked honeyeater , is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Prosopis kuntzei ( synonym Prosopis casadensis ) is a South American leguminous tree species that inhabits the westernmost Gran Chaco forests covering areas of Argentina , Bolivia , and Paraguay , where it acts as natural component .
Yaverlandia is a genus of theropod dinosaur .
Nassa francolina , common name : the Francolina Jopas , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the nassa mud snails .
Austrolittorina unifasciata , common name the banded periwinkle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Sphaerotheca maskeyi is a species of frog in the Ranidae family found in Nepal and possibly Bhutan and India .
Aethes biscana , the reddish aethes , is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae .
Persicaria hydropiperoides is a New World species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common names swamp smartweed and false waterpepper .
Rangaeris is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , naive to sub - Saharan Africa .
The genus consists of the single species Styletoctopus annae , which lived approximately 95 million years ago .
Sclerotium cepivorum is the asexual reproductive form of Stromatinia cepivora and is a plant pathogen , causing white rot in Allium species , particularly onions , leeks , and garlic .
Rhagoletis ochraspis is a species of tephritid or fruit fly in the genus Rhagoletis of the family Tephritidae .
Begonia nelumbiifolia is a species of flowering plant in the Begoniaceae family .
The family Dimeroceratidae was established for the genus Dimeroceras which was previously included in the Cheiloceratidae in the Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology Part L , but differing from the similar subglublar to thickly lentiuclar Cheiloceras in having a large lateral lobe and the umbilical lobe outside the umbilucus .
Uropeltis dindigalensis , commonly known as the Sirumalai Hills earth snake or the Dindigul Uropeltis , is a species of snake in the family Uropeltidae .
Chicoreus maurus , common name the Maurus murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Mutilla europaea is a species of parasitoid wasp belonging to the family Mutillidae .
Pteris tripartita is a species of fern native to Africa , Indonesia , and the Marquesas .
Dipodium is a genus of about 25 species of orchids native to tropical , subtropical and temperate regions of south - east Asia , New Guinea , the Pacific Islands and Australia .
Christianoconcha quintalia is a species of small air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Punctidae , the dot snails .
Neocorestheta baloghi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neocorestheta .
The Pelagornithidae , commonly called pelagornithids , pseudodontorns , bony - toothed birds , false - toothed birds or pseudotooth birds , are a prehistoric family of large seabirds .
Crenicichla is a genus of cichlids native to South America commonly known as the Pike cichlids .
Nephelomys pirrensis , also known as the Mount Pirre rice rat , is a species of rodent in the genus Nephelomys of family Cricetidae .
Scirpus pendulus is a species of flowering plant in the sedge family known by the common names pendulous bulrush , rufous bulrush , and nodding bulrush .
Ophiogomphus howei , the pygmy snaketail , is a species of dragonfly in the family Gomphidae .
Aethalochroa insignis , common name Indian stick mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in India that was originally identified as a variety of A. ashmoliana .
Hiekeia pedunculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Hiekeia .
Encephalartos pterogonus is a species of cycad that is native to Mount Mruwere ( Monte Urueri ) and adjacent mountains in the Manica province of Mozambique .
Lophyra is a genus of predatory beetles in the family Carabidae capable of flight .
Garra notata , the Tenasserim garra , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Garra .
Paralcidion bilineatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Paralcidion .
Ryuthela nishihirai is a species of spider in the family Liphistiidae .
The Wyoming ground squirrel ( Urocitellus elegans ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Lysimachia punctata , the dotted loosestrife , large yellow loosestrife or spotted loosestrife , is a plant species in the genus Lysimachia .
Algrizea is a genus in the plant family Myrtaceae first described as a genus in 2006 .
Hypselodoris iacula is a species of very colourful sea slug or dorid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Chromodorididae .
The Guatemala plateau frog ( Rana macroglossa ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family .
Acanthocalyx delavayi is a small perennial plant species that grows in stony ground .
Hemerocallis citrina , common names citron daylily and long yellow day lily , is a species of herbaceous perennial plant in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae .
Rhododendron veitchianum is a rhododendron species native to Burma , Thailand , and Laos , where it grows at altitudes of 900 - 2400 meters .
Agave gracilipes , common names Maguey de pastizal or Slimfoot Century Plant , is a plant species native to western Texas , southern New Mexico and Chihuahua .
Tessaria is a genus of South American plants in the stinkwort tribe within the daisy family .
Mertensophryne usambarae ( common name : Usambara forest toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Calliandra angustifolia is a small , riparian tree species of the Amazon Basin .
Allosaurus ( /ˌæləˈsɔːrəs/ ) is a genus of large theropod dinosaur that lived 155 to 150 million years ago during the late Jurassic period ( Kimmeridgian to early Tithonian ) .
Rubia cordifolia , often known as common madder or Indian madder , is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family , Rubiaceae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Spororminula tenerifae .
Spathiopterygidae is an extinct family of wasp .
Discoteuthis discus is a species of squid in the family Cycloteuthidae .
Estaingia bilobata is a species of trilobite from the lower Cambrian period .
Psathyrotes ramosissima is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name velvet turtleback , or turtleback .
Dendronephthya klunzingeri is a species of soft coral in the family Nephtheidae .
The Solomons white ibis or Solomon Islands white ibis ( Threskiornis molucca pygmaeus ) , known locally as the tagoa , is a distinct , dwarf subspecies of the Australian white ibis .
Proteroiulus hispanus is a species of millipede in the genus Proteroiulus .
Apollonias barbujana , the canary laurel or barbusano , is perhaps the only species of flowering plants belonging to the Apollonias genus , in the laurel family , Lauraceae .
Mesolambdolophus is an extinct genus of small odd - toed ungulate known from the Bridgerian North American Stage ( late Early to early Middle Eocene ) of Wyoming , USA .
Boerhavia coccinea is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family which is known by many common names , including scarlet spiderling , red boerhavia , hogweed , and in Spanish , hierba del cancer and hierba de la hormiga .
Chamaecyparis lawsoniana , known as Port Orford cedar or Lawson cypress , is a species of conifer in the genus Chamaecyparis , family Cupressaceae , native to Oregon and California .
Mezium affine is a species of beetle in the family Anobiidae .
Corumbataia is a genus of armored catfishes native to South America where they are only known from Brazil .
Madia sativa , known by the common names coast tarweed and Chilean tarweed , is a species of flowering plant in the aster family found in parts of western North and South America .
Conus virgatus , common name the virgate Panama cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Astragalus falcatus is a species of milkvetch known by the common names Russian milkvetch , sickle milkvetch , sicklepod milkvetch , and silverleaf milkvetch .
Scotinotylus alpinus is a species of sheet weaver found in Canada , Greenland , Mongolia , Russia and the United States .
Obutobea chrysophora is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Obutobea .
Nemamyxine is a genus of hagfish .
Longodus is an extinct genus of thelodont , placed in its own family --
Pilumnus hirtellus , the bristly crab or hairy crab , is a species of European crab .
Neuroglossum is a genus of marine red algae .
Acropyga glaesaria is an extinct species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae known from a group of possibly Miocene fossils found on Hispaniola .
Cherninia is an extinct genus of mastodonsauroid temnospondyl .
Cudonigera houstonana , the juniper budworm moth , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Galium circaezans , common name licorice bedstraw , is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Anisomeles , with common name catmint , is a genus of herbaceous plants of the family Lamiaceae first described in 1810 .
Limonium arborescens is a species of sea lavender known by the common name tree limonium and siempreviva .
Brahmaea japonica , the Japanese owl moth , is a species of moth of the Brahmaeidae family .
Herpele squalostoma is a species of amphibian in the Herpelidae family .
Sphingobacteriia , Kämpfer 2011 , is a taxonomic class composed of a single order of environmental bacteria that are capable of producing sphingolipids .
Daruma sagamia is a species of sculpin native to the Pacific Ocean waters around Japan .
There are many species in the plant genus Cynoglossum ( /ˌsɪnoʊˈɡlɒsəm , ˌsaɪ- , -nə-/ ) .
Evorthodus is a genus of gobies native to the Atlantic coast from Chesapeake Bay , USA , to northern South America and along the Pacific coast of Panama and Ecuador .
Kurixalus naso ( common names : uphill tree frog , long - snouted treefrog , Annandale 's high altitude frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Houstonia acerosa , the New Mexico bluet or needleleaf bluet , is a plant species native to Chihuahua , Coahuila , Nuevo León , Tamaulipas , San Luis Potosí , Texas and New Mexico .
The Egyptian weasel ( Mustela subpalmata ) is a species of weasel that lives in northern Egypt .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Fluminicola bipolaris .
Gracilidris humiloides is an extinct species of ant in the genus Gracilidris .
Wyethia longicaulis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Humboldt mule 's ears .
Burnupia ingae is a species of minute freshwater snail or limpet , an aquatic gastropod mollusc or micromollusk that is traditionally placed in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Lomatium erythrocarpum , known by the common name redfruit desertparsley , is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family .
Indognorimus costipennis is a species of scarab beetle in the family of Cetoniinae .
Idotea is a genus of isopod crustaceans , mostly from cold temperate waters .
Jan Kobow ( born 1966 ) is a German classical tenor in concert , Lied , and Baroque opera .
Gabriela Eibenová is a Czech soprano in opera and concert , specializing in music of the Baroque and classical period in historically informed performance .
José Sosa Esquivel ( March 22 , 1923 in Santiago de Querétaro , Querétaro -- June 15 , 1968 in Tampico , Mexico ) was a Mexican tenor .
Antonietta Meneghel ( 27 June 1893 -- 26 January 1975 ) , better known by her stage name Toti Dal Monte , was a celebrated Italian operatic soprano .
Aile Asszonyi ( born 22 July 1975 in Väike - Maarja ) is an Estonian soprano lirico - spinto who has an active career as an opera and concert singer .
Audrey Mildmay ( 19 December 1900 -- 31 May 1953 ) was an English and Canadian soprano and co - founder , with her husband , John Christie , of Glyndebourne Festival Opera .
Gerd Nienstedt ( 10 July 1932 -- 14 August 1993 ) was a German and Austrian opera singer , bass and bass - baritone .
Ada Cherry Kearton ( born Ada Forrest ; 17 July 1877 -- 19 January 1966 ) was a South African classical soprano who sang in concert and oratorio .
Thomas Davis Cunningham ( May 7 , 1916 -- June 19 , 1984 ) was an American tenor who had prominent career in operas , musicals , concerts , and on television from 1949 through 1973 .
Christiane Karg ( born 6 August 1980 in FeuchtwangenGermany ) is a soprano opera singer .
Eduard Haken ( 22 March 1910 -- 12 January 1996 , Prague ) was a Czech operatic bass who had a lengthy career at the National Theatre in Prague during the 20th century .
Vincenzo Calvesi ( fl . 1777 - -1811 ) was an Italian operatic tenor and impresario .
Melanie Kurt ( January 8 , 1880 in Vienna -- March 11 , 1941 in New York City ) was an Austrian opera singer ( soprano ) .
Topi Lehtipuu ( born 24 March 1971 in Brisbane , Australia ) is a Finnish operatic tenor .
Gaetano Ricciolini ( 27 August 1778 , Florence -- 9 October 1845 , Rio de Janeiro ) was an Italian bass - baritone and a choreographer who helped introduce opera and dance in South America .
Mario Filippeschi ( June 7 , 1907 , Montefoscoli - December 25 , 1979 , Florence ) was an Italian tenor , particularly associated with the Italian repertory , renowned for his ringing upper register .
Renée Fleming ( born February 14 , 1959 ) is an American opera singer and soprano whose repertoire encompasses Richard Strauss , Mozart , Handel , bel canto , lieder , French opera and chansons , jazz and indie rock .
Brenda Boozer ( born January 25 , 1948 ) is an American mezzo - soprano who has had an active international career performing in operas and concerts since the mid 1970s .
Joseph Carl Breil ( 29 June 1870 -- 23 January 1926 ) was an American lyric tenor , stage director , composer and conductor .
Mats Lillhannus ( born 1972 Korsholm , Finland ) is a Finnish tenor singer .
Agnès Mellon is a French soprano who specializes in baroque music .
Graziella Pareto ( May 15 , 1889 -- September 1 , 1973 ) was a Catalan soprano leggiero , one of the leading sopranos of the inter - war years .
Susan Eichhorn Young is a Canadian soprano , actress , voice - over artist , voice teacher , and writer .
Bernhard Bötel ( 1883 - -1953 ) was a German operatic tenor and actor who had an active career in Germany and Austria during the first half of the 20th century .
Ivan Kusnjer ( born 1951 in Rokycany ) is a leading Czech baritone .
Dorothy Dow ( 8 October 1920 -- 26 February 2005 ) was an American classical soprano who had an active international career in concerts , operas , and recitals during the 1940s through the 1960s .
Anthony Laciura ( born September 27 , 1951 ) is an American operatic tenor , noted for his abilities as a comprimario and actor .
Paul Kandel ( born February 15 , 1951 ) is an American musical theatre actor and tenor singer best known for his only film role in Disney 's The Hunchback of Notre Dame ( 1996 ) as the voice of the Gypsy leader Clopin .
Lucilla Udovich ( September 7 , 1930 -- September 23 , 1999 ) was an American soprano of Croatian ancestry .
Marta Domingo ( née Ornelas ) is a Mexican opera soprano , stage director and designer .
Alice Gentle ( June 30 , 1885 , Chatsworth , Illinois - February 28 , 1958 , Oakland , California ) was an American operatic mezzo - soprano .
Brett Polegato ( born 1968 in Niagara Falls , Ontario , Canada ) is an operatic baritone .
Rosetta Pampanini ( 2 September 1896 -- 2 August 1973 ) was an Italian soprano , particularly associated with Puccini roles , especially Madama Butterfly .
Lucille Tostée ( probably died 1874 ) , was a French soprano , associated with opéra - bouffe in Paris and the USA in the mid-19th century , particularly in the works of Offenbach .
Franz Fehringer ( 7 September 1910 , Nussloch - 15 March 1988 , Heidelberg ) was a German operatic tenor , particularly associated with light lyric roles in the German , Italian , and French repertories .
Edith Mathis ( born 11 February 1938 ) is a Swiss soprano and a leading exponent of the works of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart .
Aksel Schiøtz ( 1 September 1906 -- 19 April 1975 ) was a Danish tenor and later baritone , who was considered one of Europe 's leading lieder singers of the post - World War II period .
Gabriel - Vincent Thévenard ( 10 August 1669 - 24 August 1741 ) was a French operatic baritone ( basse taille ) .
Franz Anton Spitzeder ( 1735 - -1796 ) was a German tenor and keyboard teacher .
Marta Krásová ( 16 March 1901 -- 20 February 1970 ) was a Czech operatic mezzo - soprano who had an active international career with major opera houses in Europe from 1922 - -1966 .
Fernando Carpi ( 22 January 1876 -- 3 August 1959 ) was an Italian operatic tenor and later professor of singing .
Jean Kraft ( January 9 , 1940 ) is an American operatic mezzo - soprano .
Walter Cassel ( May 15 , 1910 -- July 3 , 2000 ) was a renowned American operatic baritone and actor .
Gustave Huberdeau ( 10 May 1874 -- 31 May 1945 ) was a French operatic bass - baritone who had a prolific career in Europe and the United States during the first quarter of the twentieth century .
Clara Petrella ( March 28 , 1914 in Greco Milanese -- November 19 , 1987 in Milan ) was an Italian operatic soprano , particularly associated with the Italian repertory , an outstanding singing - actress nicknamed the `` Duse of Singers '' .
Nolan Van Way ( born January 31 , 1931 ) is an American operatic baritone and tenor whose stage career , in opera and Broadway musicals , spanned half a century .
Susanna Andersson ( born December 7 , 1977 ) is a Swedish soprano and the winner of the 2003 Guildhall School of Music and Drama 's Gold Medal Competition .
Robert Merwald ( born 1971 in Munich ) is a German baritone active in opera , oratorio , and lied , primarily in Germany and Austria .
Patricia Brooks ( November 7 , 1937 -- January 22 , 1993 ) , was a lyric soprano , actress , and opera singer , who performed primarily with the New York City Opera .
Francesco Albanese ( 13 August 1912 , Torre del Greco , Naples -- 11 June 2005 , Rome ) was a lyric tenor , particularly associated with the Italian repertory .
María - Luz Álvarez ( Madrid ) is a Spanish soprano known for performance and recording of early music .
Inge Borkh ( born 26 May 1917 or 1921 ) is a German soprano .
Jean - Émile Diogène Marcoux ( June 12 , 1877 -- October 22 , 1962 ) was a French operatic bass - baritone , known professionally as Vanni Marcoux ( sometimes hyphenated as Vanni - Marcoux ) .
Willy Clément was a French baritone ( born in Cairo on 19 July 1918 , died in Paris on 7 March 1965 ) , who was noted in light baritone roles and operetta .
Justino Díaz ( born January 29 , 1940 ) is a Puerto Rican operatic bass - baritone .
César Vezzani ( 8 August 1888 -- 11 November 1951 ) was a French / Corsican operatic tenor who became a leading exponent of French grand opera through several decades .
Khori Dastoor is an American operatic soprano and actress .
Martha Mödl ( 22 March 1912 , Nuremberg -- 17 December 2001 , Stuttgart ) was a German soprano , and later a mezzo - soprano .
Mýa possesses a mezzo - soprano vocal range which spans approximately three octaves and four notes ( B2-F6 ) & The Whistle Register ( as used in `` Go Hard or Go Home '' . )
Giovanni Guicciardi ( 12 January 1819 -- 4 October 1883 ) was an Italian opera singer who sang leading baritone roles in the opera houses of Italy and Portugal .
Angel Blue ( born May 3 , 1984 ) born Angel Joy Blue is an American operatic soprano and classical crossover artist .
Nedda Casei ( born September 9 , 1932 ) is an operatic mezzo - soprano .
Eileen Küpper is a South Africa - born soprano singer , known for her work with metal bands Therion and The Kovenant .
Wolfgang Brendel ( born 20 October 1947 , in Munich ) is a German opera singer ( baritone ) , and a professor of voice at the Munich Hochschule für Musik und Theater .
Inez Fabbri ( 26 January 1831 -- 30 August 1909 ) , née Agnes Schmidt , was an Austrian American soprano , voice teacher and impresaria .
Miroslav Dvorský ( born 16 May 1960 ) is a Slovak operatic tenor of international renown who has had an active career since the early 1980s .
Evelyn Herlitzius ( born 27 April 1963 ) is a German opera singer , a dramatic soprano .
Vasco Campagnano ( 1910 - -1976 ) was an Italian operatic tenor , particularly associated with the Italian repertory .
Simone Alaimo ( born 3 February 1950 ) is an Italian bass - baritone .
Cynthia Haymon - Coleman is an American soprano , born September 6 , 1958 in Jacksonville , Florida .
Selma Kurz ( October 15 , 1874 in Biala , Galicia -- May 10 , 1933 in Vienna ) was an Austrian operatic soprano known for her brilliant coloratura technique .
Zulma Madeleine Boufflar , known as Zulma Bouffar , ( 24 May 1841 - 20 January 1909 ) , was a French actress and soprano singer , associated with the opéra - bouffe of Paris in the second half of the 19th century who enjoyed a successful career around Europe .
Pietro Spagnoli ( born 22 January 1964 ) is an Italian operatic baritone , born in Rome .
Sarah Brightman ( born 14 August 1960 ) is an English classical crossover soprano , actress , songwriter and dancer .
Guan Guimin is an award - winning operatic tenor who rose to fame in China in the 1980s before eventually moving to the United States .
Rockwell Blake ( born January 10 , 1951 ) is an American operatic tenor , particularly known for his roles in Rossini operas .
Jeanette Scovotti ( born December 5 , 1936 in New York City ) is an American coloratura soprano .
Ruth Fernández ( 23 May 1919 -- 9 January 2012 ) was a Puerto Rican contralto and a member of the Puerto Rican Senate .
Maxim Mironov ( born in 1981 in Tula ) , is a Russian tenor , best known for his interpretation of the bel canto repertoire .
Amalia Riégo ( 26 March 1850 -- 27 December 1926 ) was a Swedish soprano opera singer .
Loren Driscoll ( April 14 , 1928 -- April 8 , 2008 ) was an American tenor who had an active international career from the 1950s through the mid-1980s .
Stella Zambalis is an American spinto soprano born in Cleveland , Ohio .
Georg Unger ( 1837 -- 1887 ) was a German tenor most famous for playing Siegfried in Der Ring des Nibelungen written by Richard Wagner .
Betsy Joslyn ( born April 19 , 1954 in Staten Island , New York ) is a Broadway musical and dramatic actress and soprano .
